title: praline grahams
directions: Separate each graham cracker into four sections.
Arrange in a glass pan with edges touching.
Melt butter in a saucepan, stir in sugar and pecans.
Bring to a boil, cooking 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Spread mixture evenly over graham crackers.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes, remove from pan and let cool on wax paper.

title: manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti according to package directions; drain.
Mix the 2 cheeses together.
Stuff shells with cheese; line bottom of square baking dish with them.
Pour can of sauce on top.
Spread remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in Bundt pan on 350° for 40 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: corn pudding
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine eggs and milk; mix well.
Add corn, green pepper, onion, parsley and seasonings.
Turn into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until firm.
Serves 6.

title: ginger molasses cookies
directions: Combine sugar and shortening; beat until creamy.
Add molasses and sour milk, mixing well.
Combine ginger, soda, cinnamon and salt with flour and add gradually to creamy mixture, then add vinegar and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 12 to 20 minutes.
(Baking time and temperature will depend on your oven.)
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: mrs. jarrell's chicken pie
directions: Put chopped chicken in casserole dish.
Put egg onto and mix all other ingredients together and pour over and bake at 350° until brown.

title: rice krispie candy
directions: Boil together sugar, peanut butter and honey; remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies and marshmallows, if desired.
Put in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.

title: traditional cut-out cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, sugar, eggs and flavoring.
Blend in flour, baking powder and salt.
Cover; chill at least 1 hour. Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured cloth-covered board.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until very light brown (roll thicker for a softer cookie).
Makes about 3 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: spiral pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain and cool. Add other ingredients and toss lightly. Better if refrigerated overnight before serving.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Tie spices in a bag.
Place ingredients in large saucepan. Slowly bring to a boil.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Garnish with orange slices.
Serve from a crock mixing bowl.

title: microwave chocolate sundae
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in 9 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Add milk, oil, vanilla and nuts.
Mix to make batter.
Sprinkle over this the brown sugar and cocoa combined.
Gently pour boiling water over the top.
Microwave for 8 to 10 minutes (High), turning dish after 4 minutes.
Chocolate syrup will go to the bottom.
Serve with ice cream and spoon sauce over ice cream.

title: sticky buns
directions: Soften loaves of bread.
Cut up into 1-inch pieces.
Roll into cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Place in Pam sprayed Bundt pan, piece by piece.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Salt and pepper pork chops to taste, then place 4 in bottom of ovensafe pan. Slice enough potatoes to cover pork chops, then top with sliced onion. Pour soup that has been diluted with water over onion layer. Repeat for next 4 chops. Cover and bake for 1 hour or until chops are tender.

title: meat loaf with tomato sauce(microwave)
directions: Break bread into milk; soak.
Combine other ingredients except butter, tomato sauce and oregano.
Drain off excess milk from bread and mix bread into meat mixture.
Shape into a loaf and place in a baking dish.
Dot with butter and place sheet of waxed paper loosely over dish to prevent splattering.
Cook 5 minutes; turn dish.
Cook 5 minutes more on High.
Remove paper; add tomato and oregano.
Cook 10 minutes more
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Melt butter; mix with salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix the remaining ingredients, except M&M's.
Stir in sauce.
Mix until all pieces are coated.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Then add M&M's.

title: jolly green bean casserole
directions: Combine green beans, mushroom soup and almonds.
Put into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle on top the dry stuffing mix. Pour over top the 2 tablespoons oleo.
Bake
at 350° for 20 minutes, uncovered.

title: buckeye balls
directions: Shape the first 4 ingredients into balls and place on cookie sheet on wax paper or foil.
Refrigerate until firm.
In top of double boiler over simmering water, melt semi-sweet chocolate chips and shortening.
Pour into small bowl.
Remove balls from refrigerator.
Insert toothpicks into balls and dip into chocolate.
Place on waxed paper; return to refrigerator until set and firm.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese and brown sugar.
Make flat patty in center of tray.
Pour caramel topping over patty and sprinkle with pecans.
Arrange apple slices around patty.

title: japanese fruit pies
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into uncooked pie shells and bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel, cook and mash potatoes.
Add sour cream, cream cheese, garlic and regular salt.
Whip.
Put in greased baking dish and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: texas potato wedges
directions: Slice unpeeled potatoes into wedges (12 to 14 per potato). In a small bowl, beat egg and milk.
In another bowl, combine flour and seasonings.
Dip potato wedges into milk mixture; dust with flour mixture.
Place in a single layer on an ungreased baking sheet.
Drizzle with oil.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown and tender.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: citrus peel dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in 1-quart casserole.
Cook, covered, on Full power for 2 or 3 minutes or until bubbling; stir 2 or 3 times with wire whip during cooking time.
Cool.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter and combine with graham cracker crumbs.
Mold into the bottom of a 12 x 12-inch pan.
Layer coconut on top of graham cracker crumbs.
Layer chocolate chips over coconut.
Drizzle Eagle Brand over entire mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Add sugar, molasses and egg to oil and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to first mixture and mix well.
Chill several hours.
Form 1-inch balls; roll in sugar and place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 4 to 5 dozen.

title: fish or crab cakes
directions: Mix eggs, pepper, mustard, onion and parsley.
When all mixed, add salad dressing and crab meat.
Mix and shape for cakes and fry until brown in oil.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add tomato sauce, pepperoni and mushrooms and simmer for 20 minutes.
Lightly grease a 2-quart casserole.
Layer dish with half of noodles, half of mixture, half of Cheddar cheese and half of Mozzarella cheese; repeat except for cheeses.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Remove and place rest of cheese on top and cook for 5 minutes.

title: cheesecake buffet tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In medium mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in sugar, lemon juice and vanilla. Add egg, beating well. Place tart crusts on baking sheet and pour in filling.
Bake 15-20 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream butter, add sugars gradually, beat well.
Add eggs, peanut butter, syrup, vanilla; beat well.
Add oats, soda, and salt.
Stir well.
Add remaining ingredients.
(Dough will be stiff.)
Drop dough 4 inches on greased cookie sheet.
Lightly press onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12 - 15 minutes. Center of cookies will be soft.

title: banana fruit cake
directions: You will need 4 bowls.
In the first bowl, cream the margarine, oil and sugar.
In second bowl, mash bananas and set aside.
In third bowl, combine chopped nuts, raisins, cut up pineapple and cherries.
In fourth bowl, sift flour, soda, salt and spices together.
Add 4 eggs to first bowl mixture.
Add bananas and vanilla and rum flavoring.
Add flour, soda, salt and spices.
Mix.
Stir in nut mixture.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes, then at 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: dropped danish
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix margarine, sugar and Bisquick or Jiffy mix.
Stir until dough forms.
Beat about 15 strokes.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart onto lightly greased pan. Make a shallow well in center of each with the back of a spoon. Fill with preserves.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes, until golden brown. While warm drizzle with glaze.
Makes 12 Danish.

title: apple-cinnamon snack mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine the cereal, nuts and chow mein noodles.
In a small bowl, combine the sugar, cinnamon and salt; stir in egg white.
Pour over the cereal mixture and toss to coat. Transfer to a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes. Yield: 6 cups.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Mix all together in an electric mixer.
Pour in pan.
Freeze. Cut in squares when ready to use while still frozen.

title: chicken durkee
directions: Wash and skin chicken.
Place in a baking dish.
Mix soup and sauce together.
(Rinse soup can and sauce jar with a small amount of water.)
Blend well and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: double delicious cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter in oven. Sprinkle crumbs evenly over butter; pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs. Top with chips; press down firmly with spoon. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool. Cut into bars. Store, covered, at room temperature.

title: mounds cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Bake in rectangular pan.
While still hot, pierce all over with a fork.
Pour cream of coconut and sweetened condensed milk all over cake.
Let cool. Spread with Cool Whip and sprinkle with frozen coconut.

title: reduced sodium apple rice pudding
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Soak apricots in boiling water for 30 minutes; drain.
Cook rice in 4 cups boiling water for about 12 minutes or until soft.
Drain well.
Mix milk, apples, apricots and spices into cooked rice.
Grease 1 1/2-quart baking dish with the oil.
Pour pudding into dish.
Bake for 1 hour or until browned.
Makes 6 servings at 168 calories per serving.

title: delicious pie
directions: Mix coconut, almonds and margarine.
Toast in oven at 400° until golden brown.
Mix Eagle Brand milk, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread coconut mixture over bottom of each crust.
Drizzle caramel sauce over coconut.
Top with Cool Whip mixture.
Sprinkle with rest of coconut and nuts.
Drizzle remaining caramel sauce over this.
Freeze.
Makes 2 pies.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Frying pan or griddle should be heated to 325° to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spray griddle with Pam and 2 tablespoons oil.
Spoon mixture on pan (large spoon) and fry until golden brown, turning once.

title: easy brownies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a bowl.
Add next 3 ingredients and stir well.

title: world famous chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in large skillet, stirring until ground beef is crumbly; drain.
Add garlic, pepper, salt and water; mix well.
Add undrained tomatoes and kidney beans, tomato sauce, chili powder, catsup and hot pepper sauce.
Simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add additional water, if necessary, for desired consistency.
Break spaghetti into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Cook, using package directions; drain.
Add to chili just before serving.
Mix well.
Serves 10.

title: monster mash party mix(for halloween)
directions: In a large bowl, combine ingredients.
Makes 15 cups party mix.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar and eggs together.
Add mashed bananas to creamed mix.
Sift soda, baking powder and flour together; add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts to mixture just before putting into loaf pan.

title: chewy noels
directions: Start your oven at 350° or moderate.
Melt butter or margarine in a 9-inch square pan over low heat.
Then take off stove.
Beat eggs slightly.
Combine sugar, flour, soda and nuts and stir into beaten eggs.
Then add the vanilla extract.
Pour this mixture over the butter or margarine.
Don't stir.
Then slide into the oven and bake 20 minutes.
Turn out of pan onto rack.
Cut in oblongs and dust bottom side with confectioners sugar.
If you want to be fancy, you can write NOEL across the top using any type of white frosting.
Makes 18 and they are delicious.

title: garlic green beans
directions: Fry bacon. Do not discard grease. Add to green beans. Add other ingredients. Boil for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and sugar together in a large pot. When mixture is melted and runny, add Rice Krispies.
Mix well. Let cool until easy to handle.
Form into balls and chill to set.

title: homemade apple dumplings
directions: Peel and cut apples into quarters.
Roll out biscuits and place apple in center.
Pull up around apple.
Pour margarine over dumplings.
Mix sugar, water and cinnamon, then pour over apples. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients, except potato chips and cheese, well.
Pack into casserole dish; top with crushed potato chips
and Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions; add spices.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: elvira's potato potato
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until golden and slightly crispy on edges.
Delicious! Serves 10.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift flour, salt and sugar together.
Cut in the Crisco until texture
is meal-like.
Add water, vinegar and egg; mix well. Press
into a ball and chill.
Roll into crusts.
Makes 2.
See recipe for Apple Pie.

title: raw apple cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and 1 cup flour, then the apple.
Don't drain off the juice.
Add remaining ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls.
Bake at 350° on a greased cooking sheet 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken doritos casserole
directions: Cook chicken breast and shred.
Combine soup, chicken and Ro-Tel; bring to a boil.
Layer chips, cheese and soup mixture. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add the flour alternately with the half and half.
Beat well.
Add vanilla.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Arrange chiles in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Layer cheese on top.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over chiles.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: copper carrots
directions: Mix tomato soup, oil, sugar and vinegar; bring to boil and pour over vegetables.
Serve cold.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat Wesson oil in large skillet.
Saute rice.
Add onions and bell pepper.
Mix garlic powder and cumin powder with tomato sauce and water together.
Add mixture to rice.
Let mixture come to a bubble.
Add salt and pepper to mixture.
After it bubbles for a minute, turn heat to low setting and cover with tight lid.
Cook until steam stops coming out of lid, or for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not uncover until almost completed cooking.
Serves 6 persons.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix soft butter and sugar.
Add baking powder to graham cracker crumbs and add all to mixture.
Add milk and eggs, a little at a time.
Add coconut and pecans.
Place into 2 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Cook for 40 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: cheese swirl
directions: Swirl mixture in the blender until very smooth and creamy, stirring down with rubber spatula occasionally. Serve with crisp vegetables, such as carrot and celery sticks, cauliflowerets and cucumber strips. Also may be served with curried potato chips or crisp crackers. Makes about 2 cups.

title: aunt frankie's texas hash
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and set aside.
Saute onion, garlic and green pepper.
Add beef and all remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer about 15 minutes until rice is cooked.
Stir occasionally.

title: banana bread
directions: Measure and sift together flour, soda and salt.
Set aside. Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Fold in dry ingredients, nuts and chocolate chips.
Place in a well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 60 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Deseed and chop jalapenos; deseed tomatoes.
Saute jalapenos and onion in oil in large skillet until onion is soft.
Add green chilies and tomatoes; cook 2 minutes.
Add cream cheese until melted; remove from heat.
Press spinach between layer of paper towels until dry.
Add spinach, Monterey Jack, half and half, cayenne pepper, salt and pepper.
Stir well; put in baking dish and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve warm with Tostitos.

title: chicken tacos
directions: Boil chicken until done, about 30 to 45 minutes.
While chicken cooks, put butter and onion in glass oblong dish and cook in microwave until onion is tender.
In large bowl, mix butter, onion, soups, green chilies and chicken, cut up in bite size pieces.
In glass dish, crumble about 2 or 3 handfuls of chips on bottom.
Pour bowl of ingredients on top of chips and sprinkle with 1/2 cup of grated cheese.
Put in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Put chips on plate; chicken tacos on chips and top with tomatoes, lettuce, cheese and hot sauce.

title: goo cake
directions: Blend German chocolate cake mix, melted margarine and 2 eggs. Pat out in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar.
Spread over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind pears, onions, and peppers (grind peppers and let drain in colander while grinding pears and onions).
Add sugar, vinegar, salt, turmeric, and pickling spices (tie pickling spices in bag). Cook over medium heat until ingredients are tender.
Pack in clean hot jars and seal.

title: elegant sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan; set aside.
Combine cake flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a medium mixing bowl.
Cream together butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add egg yolks one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add dry mix to the egg mixture alternating with sour cream, beginning and ending with the flour mixture, stirring just until mixed; set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff, gently fold into the batter.
Spoon batter into prepared pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours, or until the center is set. Cool for 10 minutes, then remove from the pan and cool completely on wire rack.

title: candied kosher dill pickles
directions: Drain kosher dills; discard juice.
Rinse pickles.
Slice like bread and butter pickles and put in large bowl.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Let stand 3 days at room temperature (covered), stirring occasionally.
Refrigerate after 3rd day.

title: cranberry raisin chutney
directions: In medium pan, combine preserves, brown sugar and spices. Bring to a boil; cook until sugar dissolves, stirring occasionally. Add cranberries, pear, apple and raisins. Cook over medium heat about 25 minutes or until mixture is thickened, stirring occasionally. Stir in walnuts; cool slightly. Pour into clean jars or bowl or non-metal containers. Cover with tight-fitting lid. Store in refrigerator up to 3 weeks. Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all (dice apples) ingredients to taste.

title: apple cabbage slaw
directions: In large bowl toss cabbage and apples.
In small bowl combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over cabbage mixture and toss to coat.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli
8 minutes in boiling water.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients
together
(reserve
a little cheese for top). Put in casserole.	Top with cheese and saltine cracker crumbs. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit punch or rum punch
directions: Mix the four juices.
Add ginger ale and 1/2 of sherbet last. Stir until sherbet is nearly melted.
Add a frozen ring of lemonade.
Add rest of sherbet and let float on top.
This recipe is easy to cut in half.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding black pepper to taste.
Make into medium size patties and fry in deep fat until brown.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Beat together ingredients.
Stir in apples.
Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Preheat oven to 400° and bake for about 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle topping over top and bake another 20 minutes.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt chips with sweetened condensed milk, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Chill 2 hours or until firm enough to hold shape.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in choice of coatings.
Chill 1 hour or until firm. Store covered at room temperature.
For longer storage, refrigerate or freeze.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: extra-easy lasagna
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook beef until thoroughly cooked and no pink remains, stirring to separate meat. Spoon off fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Heat through.

title: baked squash
directions: Cook squash 25 minutes or until tender.
Mash and drain; add butter, onion, bouillon, salt and pepper.
Stir in egg and sour cream.
Put in greased casserole.
Top with crumbs and cheese (mixed).
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: dark fruit cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the flour, soda and eggs in a pot.
Bring to a boil and continue boiling for 5 minutes.
Watch carefully and don't scorch.
Remove from stove and add 3 teaspoons of baking soda.
Cool mixture.
When cold, add 2 eggs (beaten) and the 3 cups of flour.
Add to greased loaf pans.
Makes 2 loaves. Bake at 325° until done.
This does cook slowly and can take more than 1 hour.
Test with toothpick for doneness.
Makes a moist cake.
Comes out more like a bread.

title: soda fountain favorites
directions: Put the fresh strawberries and ice cream in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Freeze in a container for 1 hour.
Before serving, blend a few seconds until smooth.
Spoon into tall glasses; garnish with whole strawberries.

title: korean fried egg rolls
directions: *Can use 1/2 of a bag of shredded pre-packaged.

title: old fashioned creme pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and add 1 cup boiling water and beat
together.
Add
cream
and nutmeg.
Bake one hour at 350° in unbaked pie shell.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together and pour evenly into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 - 40 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes.
Place a layer of potatoes in a baking dish, layer of white sauce, layer of bread crumbs, layer of cheese. Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Combine beans, tomato sauce and water in large boiler.
Cook on high for approximately 20 minutes.
Brown ground beef in skillet and drain excess grease.
Stir chili mix in 3/4 cup water until powder is dissolved.
Add seasoning and ground beef to mixture.
Boil for approximately 40 minutes on low heat.
If it is too thick, add more water.

title: chops with mushroom gravy
directions: In a large resealable plastic bag, combine the first four ingredients.
Add pork chops, one at a time; toss to coat.
Set remaining flour mixture aside.
In a large skillet, saute chops in butter until golden brown; transfer to a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

Saute the mushrooms in the same pan for 1 minute. Stir in reserved flour mixture; gradually add milk until blended. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Remove from the heat; stir in lemon juice.
Pour over chops. Cover and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until the meat is no longer pink.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: fisherman's chowder
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the fish, in a large pot. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 15 minutes. Add fish.
Cover and simmer 5 more minutes.
Yields 4 servings. Has 275 calories, 2 g. fat.

title: halibut zucchini sauté
directions: Sprinkle halibut with salt and pepper. Saut zucchini, onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon oil for 2 minutes. Then add tomatoes and parsley. Cook, covered, 1 minute. Remove from pan. Saute halibut in 2 tablespoons oil until brown on both sides. Allow a total cooking time of 10 minutes or until halibut flakes easily when tested. Return vegetables to pan. Add lemon juice. Heat briefly. Makes 2 servings.

title: ranch potato salad
directions: While still warm, cook potatoes into 1-inch cubes.
Gently toss together potatoes, onions and salad dressing.
Dust with paprika or pepper.
Garnish with chives.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: fudge
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; let boil for 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add the marshmallows and chocolate chips.

title: party potatoes
directions: Place frozen hash brown squares in baking dish; season with salt and pepper.
Mix butter, soup and sour cream in bowl.
Pour mixture over hash browns, then sprinkle with lots of cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, or until bubbly brown.

title: angela's dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, dump and spread pineapple.
Layer cherry pie filling (do not mix).
Spread (unprepared) cake mix (no lumps).
Sprinkle with pecans, then dot with butter.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes, until brown.
Serve warm. Makes 15 to 20 servings.

title: georgia peach cobbler
directions: *To make your own self-rising flour add 1 teaspoon baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt to 3/4 cup all-purpose flour.

title: western meat loaf
directions: Lightly mix all ingredients; form into loaf in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Spread additional 1/4 cup hickory catsup over loaf and bake 30 minutes longer.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: carrot cheddar cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by rounded tablespoon on greased cookie sheet; flatten slightly.
Bake at 375° for 16 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Store in tightly covered container in refrigerator or loosely covered container at room temperature. Serve at breakfast or as snack.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and vanilla together.
Tear bread into small pieces.
Mix everything together.
Lay pats of butter on top. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: jiffy popovers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stir well with a spoon.
Fill well-greased muffin pan (with 10 to 12 muffin cups) 3/4 full. Iron pan is best.
Put in unheated oven.
Turn temperature to 450°.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes and try not to open door until nearly done.
Serve immediately.

title: chocolate syrup brownies
directions: Cream together the oleo, eggs and sugar, then add the Hershey's syrup, flour and nuts.
Put in greased 16 x 11-inch jelly roll pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Combine water, oil, raisins, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Boil together for 3 minutes.
Let cool.
Dissolve salt and soda in liquid sweetener and 1 tablespoon water.
Add beaten egg.
Stir into the cooled mixture.
Add flour and baking powder.
Drop on to cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies(yummy, more like candy)
directions: In sauce pan, mix well the milk, cocoa, sugar; then heat. Break up butter into mixture and stir until it melts. Bring to a boil and boil for 4 minutes. Take off of the stove.

Add vanilla, salt, oatmeal and pecans. Drop quickly on wax paper and let cool. (I usually put newspaper under the wax paper to keep table or counter from being marred from the heat) These are always a hit.

title: church salad
directions: Mix ingredients well and chill.
Makes a large number of servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place all ingredients but vanilla in top of double boiler. Stir until smooth and bubbly.
Add vanilla and beat with whisk. Quickly pour into buttered baking pan.
Cool and cut into squares. Refrigerate.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Beat shortening until creamy.
Gradually add sugar and continue beating until fluffy.
Add eggs (well beaten).
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together.
Mash bananas.
Alternately add flour mixture and mashed bananas to egg mixture.
Beat until well blended.
Grease an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Pour batter into pan and bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Makes one loaf.

title: strawberry cream delight
directions: Mix first five ingredients well.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix the cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread over cool crust.
Arrange whole strawberries on top of filling. Combine chopped strawberries, sugar, cornstarch and water and cook on stove top until thick.
Cool some and pour over fresh strawberries.
Chill.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and sprinkle with instant lemon pudding mix.

title: coconut macaroons '98
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and fold in coconut and then Post Toasties.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookiesheet.
(They dooooo stick so use teflon if you have it and be prepared to scoop them off the pan quickly while warm.)
(We tried putting waxed paper on the pan too but that was even worse.)
Bake 350 F. oven for 20 minutes or until they start to get golden on edges.
Yield about 20 macaroons.
I double the recipe as a minimum.
Will freeze nicely if you have any left.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Unwrap caramels and place in pot with water and margarine on low heat.
Stir occasionally until melted and smooth.
In a separate bowl, combine sugar, salt, vanilla and beaten eggs.
Gradually add caramel mixture, mixing well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: rhubarb dessert(hand me downs)
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Pat into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Combine rhubarb and rest of ingredients.
Pour over crust.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°. Beat 6 egg whites until foamy.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla; beat until stiff peaks are formed.
Spread meringue on top.
Brown in oven until golden.

title: tuna sandwich melts
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients, except rolls.
Fill rolls with 1/3 cup tuna mixture.
Wrap in foil and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Melt butter; add milk, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix together; add nuts.
Scoop mixture out with the small end of a melon baller.
Roll quickly in palms and place on baking sheet covered with waxed paper.
Refrigerate for 12 to 24 hours.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt margarine and pour into a bowl.
Add sifted dry ingredients and nuts.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Have candied fruit chopped and coated with flour.
Save 1/2 cup fruit and 1/2 cup nuts to decorate tops of cakes.

title: parmesan salad
directions: Layer salad in bowl in this order: lettuce, cauliflower, onion slices and bacon.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar; mix thoroughly.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix in sifted dry ingredients.
Slowly stir in carrots and nuts.
Pour in greased and floured 9-inch layer or oblong pan. Bake at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top with cream cheese frosting.

title: foolproof pound cake
directions: Bring margarine and butter to room temperature.
Cream the margarine, butter and Crisco real well.
Add sugar and eggs (beating well after each addition).
Sift flour and salt together; add alternately with cup of milk.
Add flavorings.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in greased and floured cake pan.

title: german chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine wafer crumbs and butter, mixing well.
Press into bottom and 1 3/4-inches up sides of 9 to 10-inch spring-form pan. Set aside.

title: pizza crust
directions: Warm milk slightly, then mix all ingredients together.
Knead mix on slightly floured surface.
For best results, let this lie for 2 to 3 hours.
Knead onto pan, making small crust edge on outside of pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until baked through.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Toss salad with oil until leaves glisten.
Add vinegar and salt.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Toss and serve.

title: dill oyster crackers
directions: Combine Ranch mix with other ingredients and mix thoroughly. Pour over crackers and toss to coat.
Place in warm oven for approximately 40 minutes.
Toss every 10 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Spread evenly in well greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve hot.

title: palm desert stuffed date drops
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Stuff dates with nut halves.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together into a bowl.
In a large bowl, beat shortening until creamy.
Add brown sugar and beat until smooth.
Add egg and beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternating with sour cream.
Stir dates in gently.
Scoop mixture by tablespoonfuls (including a date in each tablespoonful) and drop on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Frost cookies if desired with Golden Frosting (see recipe).
Store in airtight container.
Makes approximately 5 dozen cookies.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix the sugar, cocoa, milk and oil.
Boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in the peanut butter and oatmeal.
Add the nuts and vanilla.
Drop on waxed paper.
(Be sure to bring to a rolling boil before you start timing.)

title: french cherry pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Whip cream and add vanilla; fold with other mixture.
Put into a baked pie shell.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Chill.

title: poor boy cookies
directions: Simmer raisins, sugar, water and cube butter for 10 minutes. Add nuts and vanilla.
Mix and spread in greased 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Bake for 17 to 20 minutes.
Spread on glaze.
Cut into squares.

title: zippy beef onion dip
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Serve on crackers.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Heat soup; add cheese and simmer until cheese is melted.
Pour over beans in a buttered casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cover with onion rings.
Bake for 15 minutes longer.
Makes 12 servings.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Layer on serving platter.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix.
Follow order to layer.

title: yum-yum-setta
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients together, then add tomato soup, cream of chicken soup and milk.
Cook one package of egg noodles and drain.
Add this mix to noodles.
Layer noodle mix top with meat mixture.
Then layer these with sliced cheese and top off with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: polynesian fruit salad
directions: Blend thoroughly and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: "salvation salad"(cucumber salad)
directions: Blend sliced cucumbers in salt and let set for 1/2 hour, then drain.
Mix all ingredients, then thoroughly chill.

title: chocolate delight(chocolate lovers will love this dessert.)
directions: In a double boiler, melt chocolate and butter together.
In a bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, then fold in sifted dry ingredients.
Add melted chocolate, nuts and vanilla, and mix well.
Place in a lightly greased shallow pan and bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: easy potato salad
directions: Add potatoes to 1-quart of boiling water; return to a boil. Cover.
Cook 2 minutes or until tender; drain.
Add remaining ingredients to potatoes; mix well.
Season to taste.
Refrigerate. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Spread butter in bottom of casserole dish.
Drain asparagus and set aside for later use.
Arrange asparagus in dish and spread cheese slices over asparagus.
Dice eggs on cheese then make a layer of crackers.
Put another layer of cheese slices and pour juice over this.
Smooth out can of mushroom soup over this layer and arrange crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix together jello, pineapple, cottage cheese and mandarin oranges.
Then gently fold in cool whip and chill.

title: butterfinger popcorn balls
directions: Combine popcorn and chopped butterfinger in a large bowl.
Melt butter in a medium saucepan over low heat.
Stir in marshmallows. Heat, stirring constantly, until marshmallows are melted and mixture is smooth.
Pour over popcorn mixture; quickly toss to coat well.
Spray hands with nonstick cooking spray.
Form popcorn mixture into six 3 inch balls.
Place on waxed paper to cool. Store in and airtight container.

title: impossible broccoli pie
directions: Lightly grease pie plate.
Mix first 4 ingredients and pour into pie plate.
Mix thoroughly the next 5 ingredients and pour over the top.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: marinara sauce
directions: In hot oil in large skillet, saute garlic and parsley 3 minutes.
Add the tomatoes, oregano, salt and pepper.
Mix well, mashing the tomatoes well.
Bring the mixture to boiling, then reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally for 30 minutes or until sauce is thickened.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil together the first 3 ingredients for 5 minutes; remove from heat.
Add the next 3 ingredients.
Pour mixture over popcorn in large pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Turn out onto waxed paper; work apart.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.
Grease loaf pan.

title: beet salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water and beet juice.
Combine ingredients; chill until firm.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix your Crisco, sugars and eggs together until the texture is smooth and blended, then add corn flakes and oatmeal.
Blend, then the remainder and mix until well blended.
Shape the mixture in 1 to 1 1/2-inch balls, depending on your choice of the size of cookies you desire.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until brown, approximately 12 minutes (I think).

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix together all the above ingredients and refrigerate.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Cook oriental noodle soup according to package directions but do not add flavor packet.
After cooking noodles, mix with shredded cabbage and chopped scallions.
Then mix together sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper and canola oil.
Combine altogether and sprinkle oriental seasoning packet over all.
Add toasted almonds and sesame seed.
Chill and serve cold.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: marinated beef kabobs
directions: Cut beef in 1-inch pieces.
Combine next 6 ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour over beef in bowl.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator 24 hours.
Cook green peppers, onions and zucchini until tender-crisp.
Drain.
Thread beef, vegetables and mushrooms on skewers.
Broil about 5 minutes.
Turn as needed.
Baste with marinade frequently.
Beef is better if medium done.
Serve over rice.

title: marinated stone crab
directions: Combine thoroughly all of the ingredients.
Allow to marinate overnight in the refrigerator.
Serve very cold as an appetizer.

title: fruit punch
directions: Make ahead and let stand.

title: mini bleu cheese rolls
directions: Melt butter and Bleu cheese over low heat.
Unroll dough and cut each bread stick into 6 pieces.
Place bread stick pieces in foil lined 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour cheese mixture over dough.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until butter is absorbed. Carefully lift foil out of pan.
Place in serving dish and serve hot.

title: lentils and pasta - healthy style!
directions: Brown lightly onion and garlic in olive oil.
Then add wine; cook 2 minutes.
Add lentils and tomato sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes. In the meantime, cook pasta in boiling water.
Drain when done according to package time.
Add to lentil mixture and let sit for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve with grated cheese and tossed salad.

title: strawberry or cherry refrigerator pie
directions: Prepare instant pudding pie filling according to box directions.
Place a layer of graham crackers in glass dish.
Mix cool whip and vanilla pudding together.
Place a layer of cool whip and vanilla mixture over graham crackers.
Another layer of graham crackers.
Pour the other half of cool whip and vanilla mixture over graham crackers.
Another layer of crackers.
Pour the 2 cans of pie filling over the top.
Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: easy buttered veggies
directions: Peel skin from all 3 veggies. Slice horizontally. Put small amount of water in bottom of medium size pot, then put steamer basket in pot. Put veggies in steamer basket and cover. Cook 15 to 20 minutes over medium heat.
Vegetables should be tender. Put veggies in bowl and pour melted butter over them.

title: love pudding
directions: Bring water, brown sugar and butter to a boil in saucepan. Pour into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, salt, baking powder and milk.
Drop by spoonfuls over liquid in pan. Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: yellow angel food cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored. Add water, beat 4 minutes. Add sugar and beat another minute. Sift together, flour, baking powder and salt, add to egg mixture. Add vanilla. Beat egg whites until stiff, add cream of tartar and fold in to cake mixture. Pour into ungreased angel food cake pan and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: rice and spinach saute
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
In large skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Add red pepper and garlic. Cook until red pepper softens and garlic is lightly browned, about 4 minutes.
Add spinach.
Cook, stirring, until spinach is wilted, 3 to 4 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and cooked rice.
Heat through. Makes 4 servings.

title: 3 ingredient bread mix
directions: Mix beer, sugar and self-rising flour in medium size mixing bowl and let rise for approximately 45 to 60 minutes at room temperature (65°).
Form in shape of bread loaf and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
(Tastes like sourdough.)

title: ham cuts
directions: Lay one slice of ham flat on cutting board.
Spread Philadelphia cheese on top.
Then spread mustard on.
Take pickle and roll up inside of the ham.
Cut into 5 pieces.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry 5 or 6 strips bacon and crumble.
Saute chopped onion in the bacon grease.
Mix all ingredients except 3 strips uncooked bacon.
Pour in casserole and place 3 strips uncooked bacon on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fried squash and potatoes
directions: Heat oil in iron skillet.
Slice all other ingredients and cook over medium heat until tender, about 25 to 30 minutes. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Combine oil, carrots, sugar, eggs and nuts.
Add sifted ingredients; mix well.
Bake in a greased 9-inch tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Cool.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: fruitful ham slice
directions: In the bottom of a glass baking dish, scatter raisins.
Score edges of ham slice in several places to prevent curling.
Put ham on top of raisins.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together with a mixer, then pat it out in a round serving platter.
Sprinkle crabmeat over the top and serve with crackers.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Cover and bake at 325° for one hour.
Uncover and pour tomato sauce over casserole.
Then bake 1 hour more.

title: date nut roll
directions: Combine sugar, milk, margarine and corn syrup in saucepan. Over medium heat, bring to boiling, stirring.
Add dates.
Boil to soft ball stage (cook, stirring often, to 238° on candy thermometer or until a little cold water forms a soft ball). Remove from heat.
Add walnuts and vanilla; beat until thick.

title: peanut chews
directions: Mix dry ingredients and set aside.
Over low heat, melt caramels with water.
Pour over dry ingredients and melt well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet and chill until firm.

title: ruth's chocolate coffee cake
directions: Mix cocoa and boiling coffee.
Set aside.
Cream oleo, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix soda with buttermilk (dissolve).

title: baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Top with lean bacon strips and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs and melted oleo.
Press in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat together 15 minutes the powdered sugar, eggs and softened oleo.
Spread over crust.
Slice bananas over filling. Spread pineapple over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple. Sprinkle pecans and cherries over Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: black bean tortilla pinwheels
directions: Beat cream cheese and sour cream in medium bowl until well blended.
Stir in Monterey Jack cheese, olives, onion, salt and garlic powder.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Place beans in food processor or blender.
Process until smooth.
(Do this step only if using the black beans.)
Spread thin layer of cream cheese mixture over beans.
Roll up tortillas tightly.
Wrap in plastic wrap, refrigerate until chilled.
Cut tortillas in 3/4 inch slices. Serve with salsa.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix together and freeze in jello mold.
You can double the recipe and use an 8 x 9-inch pan.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and celery.
Add 1 cup rice (cooked in salted water), soups and soy sauce; mix well.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.
Serves 10 to 12 people.
A good potluck dish.

title: homemade egg noodles
directions: Measure flour into bowl; make a well in the center and add egg yolks, whole egg and salt.
Use a fork and mix well by hand.
Add water, a little at a time, to form dough into a ball.
Put dough on a well-floured table and knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Cover; let rest 10 minutes.
Divide dough in half.
Roll dough until thin. Cut noodles.
(I use a table knife with the blade side up.)
Let dry 1 to 2 hours.
Cook.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cut pork, potatoes and onions in quarters and grind into a pan.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Cook on medium or low heat, stirring frequently to prevent scorching (do not cook fast).
Cook about 1 hour. Makes about 1 gallon.

title: million dollar salad
directions: Combine marshmallows and drained pineapple.
Mix cream cheese with sugar and mayonnaise until smooth.
Add to marshmallow mixture.
Add rice and cherries.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts. Chill.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
In a casserole dish place layers of meat, sliced potatoes and onions.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese.
Put another layer of each.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: easy custard pie
directions: Thoroughly mix eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Slowly stir in hot milk and pour immediately into unbaked pie shell.
To avoid spills, fill at oven.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg or pumpkin pie spice.
Bake about 20 minutes, or until silver knife inserted 1 inch from side of filling comes out clean.
The center may still be a bit soft, but will set later.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Whip together sweet potatoes, vanilla and 1/3 cup margarine. Put in buttered casserole.
Mix together brown sugar, coconut, pecans, flour and 1/3 cup margarine.
Spread over top of sweet potatoes.
Cover 25 minutes, then uncover 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
For full flavor, refrigerate overnight. Serve with chips, crackers or vegetables.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Mix margarine, 1/2 cup sugar and egg. Add flour, baking powder and nutmeg alternately with milk. Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes. Take from pan, and while hot, roll in 6 tablespoons melted butter. Then roll in cinnamon sugar made by mixing 1 teaspoon cinnamon with 1/2 cup sugar.

title: old fashioned ice cream
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Stir in hot water as directed on package.
Add evaporated milk, water and condensed milk; stir well.
Add sugar.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Chill in refrigerator before freezing for about 45 minutes to an hour.
Pour mixture in electric ice cream freezer and freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Add fruit to ice cream after ice cream freezer shuts off.
Makes 7 quarts.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook margarine and onions until transparent.
Mix all ingredients, except bacon.
Pour into casserole dish and place bacon on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
(Bush baked beans are very good.)

title: wild rice and leek pilaf
directions: Cook wild rice in a large amount of boiling water 10 minutes. Drain well.
Melt butter in heavy large saucepan over medium heat. Add leeks and carrots and cook until beginning to soften, about 5 minutes.
Mix in wild and converted rice. Add 3 1/2 cups stock, salt and thyme and bring to simmer.

Reduce heat to low, cover and cook until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender, adding more stock if necessary, 30 to 35 minutes. Mix in pepper. Adjust seasoning. (Can be prepared 20 minutes ahead, covered and kept warm.)
Makes 6 servings.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in gallon freezer.
Finish filling freezer with regular milk and freeze.

title: pecan cream pie
directions: Scald milk in heavy saucepan. Gradually add sugar, flour and salt, which had been mixed together.

title: neiman-marcus bars
directions: Mix together the cake mix, 2 eggs and butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and confectioners sugar. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown on top.
Cool and enjoy.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Check like a pumpkin pie.

title: sparkling lemonade
directions: Place lemonade concentrate into a large pitcher. Add ginger ale; stir well. Score lemon; cut into thin slices. Add lemon slices and raspberries to lemonade mixture.

title: curried lamb shanks
directions: Sprinkle shanks with salt and pepper, then flour.
Brown slowly in a little oil or bacon fat, turning as needed.
Take off heat.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle oregano over shanks and combine the curry powder, paprika, garlic powder, marjoram, savory and the orange juice.
Pour over the shanks.
Add the bay leaf. Cover shanks with chutney.
Cover dish and cook at 350° for about 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours, basting occasionally.

title: fruit fluff
directions: Mix well. Refrigerate overnight.

title: beef and beans for lil don
directions: Fry beef in saucepan. Drain excess grease. Add the beans. Stir.
Add the ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and dash of pepper. Stir. Add margarine. Stir and simmer for 7 minutes. Serve over rice or plain with fries.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll out crescent rolls in a pizza pan or cookie sheet to form pizza crust.
Bake as directed on package.
Mix cream cheese, Ranch dressing and mayonnaise until creamy; spread over cooked crescent rolls.
Top with vegetables of your choice.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Cut into squares.

title: crazy berry blue pie
directions: Combine gelatin with cold water and set aside.
Mix Eagle Brand
milk with the lemon juice.
Add gelatin, Eagle Brand mixture and sour cream and stir very lightly.
Pour into the crumb crust and cover with blueberry pie mix.
(This is good as is but adding whipped topping makes it better.) Place in cool place until ready to serve.
This is very rich and can make 2 small pies.

title: fruit roll
directions: Cook 1 1/2 cups sugar and water 5 minutes.
Make a dough.

title: poppy seed-swiss cheese bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in cheese and poppy seed.
Make a well in center of mixture. Combine eggs, milk and mustard.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, tenting with aluminum foil after 50 minutes, if necessary.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Yield: 1 loaf.

title: pretzel jello
directions: Mix water, Jell-O and strawberries.
Let chill until thickened.

title: hatcher crackers
directions: Place crackers neatly in an 11 x 16-inch cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.
Trim the last row and column to fit the pan.
Crackers must fit together tightly.
Sprinkle crackers lightly with red pepper.
Coarsely grate the cheese directly over the crackers as evenly as possible.
Turn on broiler.
Place pan on bottom rack and leave door open.
After a few minutes, the cheese will begin to bubble.
When the cheese begins to dry out and most of the bubbles are firm on top, remove the pan from the oven.
Allow the oven to cool.
Return the pan to the oven set at 150°.
Bake and close oven door.

title: potato casserole
directions: Crumble crackers on top and dot with margarine.
Bake until done.

title: apple casserole
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture.
Add apples; mix well.
Place in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple bars
directions: Preheat heat oven to 350°. Combine first 6 ingredients in large bowl; mix well. Pour into greased 9 by 13 inch baking pan. Bake for 35 minutes. Let cool in pan. Combine next 3 ingredients in mixing bowl; mix well. Spread on cooled cake. Garnish with almonds. Yield 24 bars.

title: "lesueur" salad
directions: In a large salad bowl or a 9 x 13-inch pan, alternate layers of lettuce, peppers, onions, celery and carrots.
Simmer frozen peas for approximately 5 minutes and drain.
Put over layers of other ingredients.
Sprinkle tablespoons of sugar over mayonnaise.
Spread shredded cheese and bacon bits to taste as a topping.
Seal bowl or pan tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush 1 package Oreo cookies and put in bottom of 8-inch flowerpot with foil under it to keep from spilling.
Mix melted margarine, Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Put layers alternately with 1 package crushed cookies, ending with cookies on top.
Decorate with gummy worms and flowers.
Chill well before serving.

title: farmer's breakfast
directions: Cook and drain sausage. Wipe skillet with paper towels. Melt margarine in skillet. Add onions, peppers and sausage until tender. Add cooked potatoes and sausage; mix well. Beat eggs and milk. Add to skillet, turning until eggs are done. Add seasonings. Serve with biscuits.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute vegetables in oil.
Add tomato paste, water and seasonings.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add shrimp and heat through.
Serve on hot rice.
Other seafood could be used.

title: italian beef and potato casserole
directions: Brown chuck; drain and add onion, garlic, spaghetti sauce, water, basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil, then simmer for 10 minutes.
Spoon 1/3 of meat mixture into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with half of potato slices.
Add remaining potato slices and remaining meat mixture.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender. Remove foil; sprinkle cheese over casserole.
Bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: breakaway cake
directions: Scald milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add teaspoon sugar and yeast. Let stand for 15 minutes.

title: cinnamon pecans
directions: Combine the first five ingredients and cook until sugar is dissolved.
Add pecans and continue to cook stirring frequently. Cook until pecans are completely sugared with no syrup left in pan.
Spread on wax paper to cool.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw, rinse, drain and squeeze spinach.
Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate.
Serve with Hawaiian bread or pumpernickel bread.

title: potatoes george
directions: Slowly add milk to flour, salt and mustard.
Cook over low heat until smooth and thick.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Peel and cook potatoes to fill 1 1/2-quart casserole 3/4 full.
Cook until nearly done about 15 minutes.
Slice.
Put a bit of sauce in bottom of greased casserole.
Add a layer of potatoes and onions, then more sauce until all used.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes until bubbly.

title: oreo cookie pie
directions: Let ice cream soften.
Mix ice cream, Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip in bowl.
Mix well to get lumps out.
Spread bottom of pan with crumbled up Oreo cookies.
Pour in ice cream mixture. Spread crumbled Oreos on top and put some whole Oreos around sides to decorate.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add 3 cups milk.
Heat over medium-low heat.
When warm, dip out small amount of heated mixture and add to beaten egg yolks.
Stir and pour back into heated mixture. This keeps pudding smooth.
Stir constantly until desired thickness.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding.
Repeat.

title: fresh peach pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix sugar, flour and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add butter and orange juice.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Add orange peel, pecans and peaches.
Place in pie shell. Bake 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°.
Bake 30 minutes or more. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken and rice supreme
directions: Lay chicken in bottom of large pan.
Salt and pepper to taste. Pour uncooked rice over chicken.
Cook onion soup according to directions and pour over chicken.
Pour mushroom soup, uncooked, over chicken.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: emergency steak
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Press well the meat mixture out on a cookie sheet.
Chill 1 hour, then cut in strips (like steak fingers).
Fix a batter mixture (mix 2 eggs, 1/4 cup milk and season with salt and pepper).
Dip strips in flour, then in batter mixture, then the flour again.
Fry the steaks until golden brown.

title: strawberry angel food cake
directions: Crumble cake and put in an oblong dish.
Pour dry Jell-O over cake.
Pour mixed pudding over Jell-O.
Add drained pineapple over all.
Top with Cool Whip.
Add fresh strawberries on top if you wish.

title: taco dip
directions: Use as much of ingredients to your desired thickness.
Layer ingredients in the order listed in an 8 x 8 baking dish. Bake in 375° oven until cheese on top melts.

title: chili
directions: Melt shortening in heavy skillet or Dutch oven.
Add ground beef, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until meat is beginning to brown.
Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Continue cooking until onions are translucent, about 5 minutes more.
Stir in tomato puree and juice.
Cover and simmer gently for about 20 minutes.
About 15 minutes before time to serve, stir in kidney beans, sugar, chili powder and additional salt and pepper to taste.
Heat piping hot.
Blend 2 tablespoons water into cornstarch.
Gradually stir into chili and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Serve very hot with crisp crackers or over boiled rice.
Garnish with green pepper rings if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mrs. hammond's rolls
directions: Put yeast in warm water.
Cream shortening, sugar and salt. Stir until well mixed.
Let cool a little and add yeast and 1 egg that has been well-beaten.
Add flour and mix well.
Butter the top of the dough and leave in covered bowl overnight in refrigerator.

title: scampi a la marinara
directions: In hot oil, in skillet, cook garlic just until golden.
Add tomatoes, parsley, basil, salt and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, 1/2 hour.
Stir in oregano and tomato paste and cook, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Stir in garlic salt and shrimp.
Heat, stirring to combine.
Serve topped with grated cheese over spaghetti or rice if desired.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream the butter and vanilla together, then beat in both sugars and the egg.
Mix the flour, cream of tartar, salt and spices together; add to fruit mixture, combine well.
Shape into a roll about 2-inches in diameter and wrap in greased wax paper.
Chill overnight.
Store in refrigerator until ready to bake.
Dough will keep well for at least a week and may even be frozen.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mash berries to measure 1 cup.
Stir together sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in water and crushed berries.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in a few drops red food color.
Let cool.
Beat cream cheese until cool. Spread on bottom of pie shell.
Fill shell with berries.
Pour berry mixture over top.
Chill 3 hours.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray 10 x 15-inch pan with Baker's Joy.
Put pecans and coconut in bottom.
Mix cake mix as directed and pour over.
Soften margarine and cream cheese and mix well.
Mix with confectioners sugar.
Spoon in globs over cake and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fresh vegetable relish
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Put in covered container and refrigerate several hours or up to 3 months.

title: fluffy corn bread(very good!!!)
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cornmeal. In a separate bowl, beat eggs with a fork, then stir in milk and butter or margarine.
Add the liquid ingredients to the dry ingredients and stir just to combine.
The batter may be lumpy, but that's okay.
Pour the batter into a 9-inch square lightly greased baking pan.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Be careful not to overbake or the bread will be dry.
If you use a food processor, be careful not to overprocess the mixture.
I stir by hand.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add lemon juice and vanilla. Mix in eggs.
Add cream, then dry ingredients.
Roll out, a little at a time, to desired thickness on floured surface.
Cut with fancy cutters and bake in a quick oven (400°).

title: basic pie filling
directions: Sift flour and sugar together. Beat egg yolks well. Add sugar and flour mixture to well beaten eggs. Gradually add milk slowly to the egg, flour and sugar. Pour this into top of double boiler and cook over boiling water until thick. Remove from fire and add butter. Add vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell. Cover with Meringue.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Rinse beans and set aside.
In a large pot over medium heat, saute onions, pepper, celery and garlic in oil.
Add oregano.
Add drained beans, red wine, red wine vinegar, basil, celery salt, bay leaves, garlic salt, salt, pepper and hot sauce to taste.
Add enough water to cover beans by 1/4-inch and simmer about an hour.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Put sausage in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In layers, add the bread, then the cheese.
Mix together the milk, eggs, dry mustard, salt and diced chilies, blending eggs well.
Pour over layers.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cover with foil and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Take the foil off and bake for 15 minutes more.

title: french meat pies ii(for two 9 inch meat pies)
directions: Simmer meat and onions.
Drain and add seasonings and simmer for 15 minutes more.
Mix in potato.
Fill pie crust with meat mixture.
Cover with top crusts and bake at 400° for 40-45 minutes.

title: whole wheat muffins
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat the eggs and add the applesauce, vegetable oil and vanilla. Add to the dry ingredients.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then turn to 350° and bake for 5 more minutes.

title: salted nut chews
directions: Combine cake mix, butter
and
egg;
beat
on low until crumbly.
Press into ungreased 9
x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 18 minutes.
Remove
from oven; sprinkle with marshmallows. Return to oven for 1 to 2 minutes until marshmallows puff;
cool.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Measure oil, sugar and eggs into large bowl and beat well. Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
After getting poured in pan, drop a few butterscotch morsels on top.

title: post toasties cookies(no bake)
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir until melted.
Mix together Post Toasties, coconut, vanilla and salt.
Mix both mixtures together quickly and drop onto waxed paper while still very warm.
Allow to set.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Cook potatoes, peel and cut into a large bowl.
Stir in sour cream, onions, 1 cup cheese, salt and pepper.
Turn mixture into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate chip sheet cake with icing
directions: Mix all together, and then add eggs.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool cake slightly, and pour icing over cake in pan.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl.
Season with salt and pepper. Pour in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with crushed potato chips (last 10 minutes).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. (Another topping:
2 cups crushed cornflakes mixed with 1/4 cup melted margarine.)
Serves 8 to 10.

title: baked five soup chicken
directions: Put the French onion soup on the bottom of a glass (9 x 13-inch) baking dish.
Combine the cream soups in a bowl and pour on top of the French onion soup.
Place the chicken breasts on the soups.
Cover the chicken with Cheddar cheese soup.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is done.
Serve with rice or pasta.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar in saucepan, bring to a boil, remove from heat and add jello, stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese and stir until melted.
Add ice water and let cool.
Add celery and nuts.
Refrigerate until mix thickens, then fold in Cool Whip. Refrigerate.
Salad is better if allowed to set for 24 hours.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together with hands and save out 3/4 cup for icing.
Put last 3 ingredients with first 3 and mix well. Pour into greased pan and sprinkle with part saved out.
Bake in moderate oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix with hands, adding milk until it holds together.
Roll between waxed paper.
Put into pans and prick with fork.
Bake in 425° oven for about 10 minutes or until brown.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mold into a shape.
Pour shrimp cocktail sauce over.
Serve with crackers.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make the cake as directed on box.
Cool about 10 minutes.
Cut or break the cake into little pieces.
Mix up vanilla pudding according to directions and set aside.
In a clear punch bowl, put a layer of cake crumbs, a layer of pineapple, a layer of pie filling, a layer of vanilla pudding and a layer of Cool Whip.
Do another layer the same way, ending with Cool Whip.
Great for covered dish dinners.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop popcorn while melting other ingredients, stirring until marshmallows are melted.
Pour over popcorn and stir well, then eat!
Delicious!

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients, including nuts, in large mixing bowl.
In smaller mixing bowl, put all remaining ingredients and beat with egg beater until it is well mixed.
Pour wet ingredients into bowl with dry ingredients and stir until well mixed.
Pour into 2 greased and floured bread pans and bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Crack in top of loaf is normal.

title: strawberry spinach salad
directions: Rinse spinach leaves thoroughly; tear into bite-sized pieces. Drain on paper towels.
Hull and rinse strawberries.
Cut in half or leave whole, depending on size.
Drain on paper towels.
Blend onion, vinegar, vegetable oil, honey and Worcestershire sauce until smooth.
Stir in sesame seed and poppy seed.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Process the orange and lemon in a food processor until chopped fine. Add cranberries and sugar. Process until coarsely chopped. Pour mixture into bowl. Cover and chill 30 to 45 minutes at least. Makes 3 cups.

title: dried pea soup
directions: Put the peas in cold water first thing in the morning.
At 10 o'clock, put peas in kettle with a gallon of water, salt pork, onion, carrot and the celery.
When simmered for 1 1/2 hours, add the chicken stock and summer savory.
Simmer for another 1 1/2 hours.
Rub through a strainer and enjoy.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: In bowl, combine all ingredients.
Turn into a 9-inch glass pie plate with a glass, open end up, in center of dish, packing lightly.
Cook 6 to 8 minutes, rotating dish halfway through cooking time.
Remove excess drippings.
Pour catsup over top, cover with waxed paper, and cook 6 to 8 minutes, rotating dish. Rest, covered, 10 minutes before serving.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix boiling water with Jell-O; stir until dissolved.
Add 7-Up.
Chill until partially set.

title: cabbage plate
directions: Combine vegetables.
Add sugar, salt and oil; mix.
Add water. Cook until just tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes a pretty dish, also very tasty.
Serves 8.

title: best ever watermelon pickle rind
directions: Cook rind until tender (not real soft) to which 2 tablespoons salt and 1/2 teaspoon powdered alum has been added.
When tender, drain off water and rinse.

title: meat loaf
directions: Place bacon slices on bottom of pan.
Combine loaf ingredients; put on top of bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour uncovered.

title: owens stuffed mushrooms
directions: Turn each mushroom upside down and remove the stem.
Using a spoon, hollow
out the inside of each, making a cup.
Save the hollowed out portion of the mushroom and the tender portion of the stem.
Place the mushrooms on a lightly greased baking pan, cup side up.
Cut each bacon strip into 6 pieces.
In the bottom of each mushroom cap, you will place a piece of bacon.
Next, put one tablespoon of wine in each mushroom and set aside the remaining wine.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine shortening and sugars; cream on medium speed for 5 minutes.
Add egg and vanilla.
Continue beating until blended. Add peanut butter; blend at low speed.

title: cocoa "melt-in-your-mouth" cookie-press cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar,
egg
and	vanilla
in large mixer bowl. Combine flour,
cocoa
and salt; blend in.	Fill cookie press with dough.
Press
cookies
onto
cool ungreased cookie sheet.	Bake at 350°
for
5 to 7 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet; cool on wire rack.	Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: lemon chicken oregano
directions: In small saucepan melt margarine.
Add lemon juice, oregano, salt and pepper and oil.
Reduce heat to low and let simmer for 1 minute.
Transfer to shallow glass bowl and let cool slightly. Add chicken and turn to coat.
Marinate, cover and refrigerate overnight or 1 hour.
Transfer chicken to shallow baking pan that is large enough to hold chicken in single layer.
Broil for 4 minutes on each side.
May be grilled out on grill.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and vanilla.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes in pan.

title: golden nugget cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, soda and cinnamon.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat good after each addition.
Add oil, egg whites, pineapple, carrots and vanilla.
Mix well.
Mix in coconut with hand.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes in greased and floured pans. Makes 3 layers.

title: slaw for 40
directions: Bring ingredients to boil, then cool before pouring over cabbage and stirring well.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 minutes.
Cool on cake rack.
Blend cream cheese with pudding and gradually add milk.
Spread on cooled cake.
Drain pineapple well; spread over pudding cheese mixture. Spread whipped topping over pineapple.
Sprinkle coconut over whipped topping.
Refrigerate.
Makes 15 to 20 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Dice onions and pulverize chipped beef.
Take 1/2 of beef (1 package); set aside.
Combine all other ingredients.
Moisten hands with water to form cheese ball more easily.
Roll in meat previously set aside.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or longer.

title: townhouse
directions: Let stand for at least 5 hours before serving.
The longer it sits, the better.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Layer chunks of chicken in bottom of buttered casserole.
Pour soup (which has been heated) over chicken.
Sprinkle generously with poultry seasoning.
Melt butter and stir in stuffing mix. Spread this mixture on top of chicken and soup.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp fettucine alfredo
directions: In large skillet, melt margarine over medium heat.
Stir in 3/4 cup cream.
Stirring constantly, cook over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes.
Add fettucine to skillet.
Stir in remaining cream, cheese, pepper, salt and shrimp.
Cook 1 minute.
If desired, serve with additional cheese and pepper.

title: world's easiest key lime pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, limeade, sweetened condensed milk and food coloring in large bowl.
Pour into pie crust and refrigerate for 1 hour.
A very rich dessert.
Can be topped with real whipped cream.

title: lite crab crostini
directions: Combine crabmeat, bell pepper, mayonnaise, parsley, chives, lime juice, mustard, Parmesan cheese and hot pepper sauce; blend well.
Spread 1 tablespoon of crab mixture on each slice of bread. Line broiler pan with foil; preheat broiler.
Place the crostini on the broiler pan and broil 4 inches from the heat for 5 to 6 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Each serving contains 88 calories and 2 g fat.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Place large enough piece of foil in baking pan to cover all food.
Place beef in center of foil.
Pour soup over beef.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Unfold foil.
Add vegetables and reseal.
Cook for 30 minutes longer, or until vegetables are tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: kahlua torte
directions: Butter a 9-inch spring-form pan.
In a small bowl, combine crumbs and butter.
Line bottom and sides with crumb mixture. Chill.

title: bubble loaf
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan well.
Sprinkle nuts evenly on bottom.
Place frozen rolls evenly on top of nuts.
Sprinkle brown sugar over top, then dry pudding mix and cinnamon.
Cut butter in small pieces.
Place evenly over other ingredients.
Cover with wax paper.
Let set overnight on kitchen counter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn upside-down on plate to let syrup run through rolls.
Serves 12.

title: pasta salad
directions: Prepare pasta per instruction on box.
Chop all vegetables into equal sizes.
Cut pepperoni into quarters.
Mix all ingredients together, and chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: crock pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in salt water for 6 days; drain.
Rinse in cold water.
Slice and soak in 1/2 cup alum to 1 1/2 gallons of water for 2 days.
Rinse alum water off.
Soak overnight in 1 gallon of vinegar; pour vinegar off.
Put pickling spice (tie up in cloth) in bottom of jar or crock.
Add 1 layer of cucumbers and 1 layer of sugar; repeat until you've used 10 pounds of sugar.

title: mexicali potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In a large skillet, brown the ground beef; drain well.
Add corn, green onions, chili powder, potato slices, contents of sauce mix envelope, boiling water and milk; mix well. Spoon mixture into ungreased 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until mixture bubbles around edges.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake an additional 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Garnish with sour cream, green onions and red pepper rings.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and coarsely chop artichokes.
Set aside.
Combine all other ingredients.
Fold in artichokes.
Sprinkle parsley on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until golden brown.
Serve with crackers.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Melt butter in ovenproof dish.
Combine the flour, sugar and milk; pour in dish.
Spoon apples into mixture; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: gourmet dip
directions: Mix well. Chill and serve as dip or as a tomato-style salad dressing.

title: summer casserole
directions: Place a
layer	of
mixed
vegetable
ingredients
in a buttered casserole.
Top
with a sprinkling of brown sugar and cracker crumbs.
Repeat
layering
and sprinkle with sugar and crumbs.
Dot with butter and bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: norwegian pancakes
directions: Mix together and use a small frypan.
Heat pan; put a little butter to coat bottom of pan.
Pour a little batter and roll to coat bottom of pan.
When firm, turn with spatula.
(Double recipe for 4 people.)

title: my special spice tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Store in airtight container.
When ready to serve, mix 2 teaspoons of mix in 1 cup hot water.
For ice tea, mix 2 teaspoons of mix into 1 glass of ice water.
This makes a nice gift when presented in an attractive container.

title: hamburger and noodle cake
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in 1 tablespoon cooking fat until hamburger loses its red color.
Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Mix the meat and noodles and fry in a skillet with 4 tablespoons butter until brown on the underside. Turn out on plate and melt 1 tablespoon butter in skillet.
Return cake to skillet to brown other side.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese and cut into wedges.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit and save the juice.
Dice up the fruit into bite size pieces. Set aside.

title: kang pao chicken
directions: Combine chicken with egg white and cornstarch.
Heat oil in wok; stir-fry chicken for 4 minutes until done.
Add nuts, onion and remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve hot over rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Beat eggs. Add margarine and sugar. Stir in beans. Add coconut, nuts and vanilla. Pour into the pie shells. Bake in 350° preheated oven for approximately 45 minutes or until firm.

title: mounds bars
directions: Mix
together
ingredients.
Chill until firm enough to work. Roll
into	balls and chill until very stiff.
Dip into melted chocolate pieces and 1/4 block paraffin.

title: "reuben" sandwich
directions: Cook corned beef and cool.
Slice with sharp knife with long way of the meat.
Spread small amount of Thousand Island dressing on slice of rye bread.
Top with thin slices of corned beef (about 2 1/2 ounces), Swiss cheese, then sauerkraut and bread.
Grill until bubbly.
Serve with horseradish, pickle sticks and potato chips.

title: speedy spiced peaches
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat to boiling and simmer 5 minutes.
Drain and cool before serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream together the eggs, sugar and oil; add nuts, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and gradually mix together.
Bake in 9 x 5-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: 3 cheese ball
directions: Get cheeses at room temperature.
