Mix everything with an electric mixer.
Chill overnight.
Form into desired shape (wet hands slightly for better handling).
Roll in crushed nuts or use almonds, for pine cones, starting the layering at the tip and working up to the stem.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients with blender.
Freeze.
Serve slushy. Makes 1 gallon.

title: cheesed orange roughy
directions: Sprinkle onion over greased baking dish; place fish in a single layer over onions.
Add tomatoes.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over fish and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: fresh peach kuchen
directions: Slice peaches and soak in lemon juice.
Mix dry ingredients into eggs.
Beat with milk and lemon.
Add melted butter and mix with fork until smooth, 1 minute.
Butter 9-inch pan.
Spread batter in pan.
Arrange peaches on batter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake for 25 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: nicholson family gazpacho
directions: Mix all ingredients except V-8 juice and let stand 45 minutes, stirring every 5 to 10 minutes.
Add V-8 juice and refrigerate for 24 hours.
You can use the marinade over and over until it gets too weak.
This is like icebox pickles, just keep adding veggies when it gets low.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender. Add ham, eggs, cheese, crackers, milk and pepper. Mix well; pour into a baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: spinach squares
directions: Melt the butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chop the spinach and set aside.
Beat eggs in a large bowl; beat in flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Stir in cheese and spinach.
Pour into pan over butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen squares.

title: salted peanut crunchies
directions: Cream together margarine, shortening and peanut butter.
Beat in gradually the 2 sugars.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each.

title: cowboy beans
directions: In
a large Dutch oven place beans, onion, salt pork or ham butt.
Cover
with
water and cook slow for about 3 hours, adding water as needed.
Then form small meatballs from ground meat
and add to cooking beans along with stewed tomatoes and green
pepper. Cook
another
hour
or
until beans are done. Serve with corn bread and western music.

title: paella
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In 10-inch skillet, heat 2 tablespoons oil over medium heat (1 to 2 minutes).
Add chicken and sausage; cook until chicken is lightly browned and sausage is no longer pink (15 to 20 minutes).
Remove chicken and sausage; set aside.
Drain off fat.
Reserve 2 tablespoons.
Stir rice and onion into fat.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until rice is golden (3 to 5 minutes).
Gradually stir in chicken broth, salt, pepper, oregano, saffron and garlic.
Continue cooking until mixture comes to a full boil (10 to 12 minutes); place mixture in roasting pan. Top with chicken and sausage.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir in peas and tomatoes; top with shrimp and clams.
Cover; continue baking, stirring occasionally until shrimp turn pink and clams open.
Discard any clams that do not open.

title: five hour stew
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in covered pan 5 hours at 250°. Makes its own gravy.

title: elegant chicken
directions: In large bowl, combine chicken strips, salt and pepper.
Cover and let set overnight in refrigerator.
The following day, pour oil over chicken, then stir in cornstarch.
Let set 1/2 hour before preparation.
Whip egg whites until foamy.
Pour over chicken.
Let stand 30 minutes.
In hot skillet, melt margarine and oil.
Add chicken and saute 10 to 15 minutes or until nicely browned.
Put in dish and add parsley and chives.
Can serve alone or with rice.

title: white bread
directions: Scald 1 cup milk then stir in sugar, salt, and shortening. Dissolve yeast in water.
Cool mixture of milk.
Blend with yeast and add 3 cups flour.
Beat until smooth, stir in remaining flour. Turn out on lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl, brush with shortening.
Cover, let rise in warm, draft free place until doubled in bulk (approximately 2 hours).
Punch and turn out again onto board. Divide in half.
Let rest 15 to 20 minutes.
Shape and place in greased bread pan.
Let rise again approximately 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.
To sweeten, add raisins to original dough recipe.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits with water and salt as directed on package.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put into a greased casserole and bake 40 minutes at 325°.
After cooking, sprinkle with sharp cheese and paprika.
Heat about 20 minutes before serving.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Press crushed cookies and melted butter in 9 x 13-inch pan. Add softened ice cream and refreeze.
Combine syrup, milk and butter.
Cook 1 minute.
Cool.
Add to crust and freeze.
Add Cool Whip and nuts.
Refreeze.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix:
flour, walnuts and butter. Spread in 9x13 pan. Bake for 30 minutes then cool.

title: icebox muffins
directions: Cream sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Add molasses, flour, cinnamon, ginger and allspice.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add alternately with flour to first ingredients.
Add raisins, chopped nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes in greased and floured muffin pan.
This dough may be kept covered in icebox for several days and cooked as desired, a few muffins at a time.

title: cinnamon apple coffee cake
directions: Beat the first 5 ingredients for 2 minutes. Pour half of mixture in greased 8-inch square baking dish. Put the apples over mixture. Combine 1/2 cup sugar, chopped walnuts and ground cinnamon. Sprinkle half over apples. Pour in remaining batter, then top with the rest of sugar mixture. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: quick sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs with fork until well blended.
Stir in oil and vanilla.
Blend in sugar.
Mix dry ingredients (flour, baking powder and salt).
Blend dry ingredients into creamed mixture. Drop by teaspoons about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with greased bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.

title: simple shrimp coleslaw
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl with mayonnaise to cover. Chill 4 to 6 hours before serving.

title: custard dessert
directions: Mix eggs, milk and sugar and cook until thickens.
Add vanilla and marshmallows to hot custard.
Let cool.
Add 1/2 container of Cool Whip (fold in).
Add maraschino cherries and nuts to custard.

title: cheddar and bacon cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese and combine with Cheddar cheese and horseradish.
Crumble bacon.
Combine half into cheese mixture. Chill mixture, then form into a ball.
Roll in remaining bacon bits.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: mulligatauny soup
directions: Place chicken, water, tomatoes, onion, apple, mace, salt and curry in saucepan; cover and bring to a boil over moderate heat. Reduce heat; simmer 40 to 45 minutes until chicken is tender. Remove from heat and cool quickly.
Remove chicken; chill broth several hours to allow fat to harden.
Bone and cut chicken into small pieces.
About 30 minutes before serving, discard fat from broth.
Add chicken, carrot and green pepper.
Cover and cook about 15 minutes over moderate heat.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: curried chicken
directions: Bone chicken and discard skin.
Cut each half breast into 10 - 12 strips.
Saute chicken strips in the butter in nonstick coated skillet, stirring until opaque.
Add onion and apple and cook a few minutes.
Stir in flour and seasonings.
Add bouillon and cook, stirring, until slightly thickened.
Add milk, raisins, lemon juice, and salt.
Mix well and heat thoroughly.
Serve with Rice. Serves 8.

title: overnight sweet buns
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, stir until moistened.
Put half of	mixture
into greased Bundt pan.
Arrange rolls over top
of mixture.
Spoon rest of mixture over rolls.
Cover and chill overnight.	Uncover
and
bake
at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool 5 minutes; invert on plate.

title: salisbury steak for 50
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll in heavy foil; make a 4-inch roll.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Slice 1-inch thick. Brown and place in baking dish. Smother with onions and/or mushrooms and mushroom soup.
(I mix half onion soup with mushroom soup.)
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Place rice in 2-quart casserole. Cover with water, salt and pepper.
Dredge chicken in flour.
Place over rice in one layer, if possible.
Sprinkle with onion soup and mushroom soup.
Cover and bake at 325° to 350° for 1 to 2 hours.
Remove cover. Brown for 30 minutes longer.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine eggs, milk, flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour in baked pie shell.

title: fruit pie
directions: Place fruit in casserole dish. Melt butter. Beat egg and sugar together and mix with butter. Place squares of bread over fruit. Spoon butter, egg and sugar mixture over each piece of bread. Be sure to coat each piece well. Put in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until fruit is bubbly. Do not overcook or bread will be too hard.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, butter, milk and cocoa to a boil; keep boiling for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: italian summertime tomato salad
directions: About 1/2 hour before dinner, place in serving bowl: tomatoes (cut in wedges), basil leaves, garlic cloves, onion (cut in thin wedges), salt, pepper and olive oil.
Stir and leave on counter. Stir about every 10 minutes.
Remove garlic and serve in curved bowl with crusty Italian bread for dunking.
Serves 2 to 6 people.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cut cheese into cubes.
Melt in double boiler over hot water, stirring frequently.
Brown sausage in heavy skillet; drain grease.
Place sausage, cheese and Bisquick in large mixing bowl. Mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
May freeze on cookie sheet and store in plastic bags in freezer.

title: gold loaf cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in mixing bowl. Add shortening (preferably butter-flavored Crisco), half of the milk and egg yolks. Stir until flour is dampened, then beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Add remaining milk and beat 1 minute more. Bake in greased and paper-lined loaf pan (10 x 5 x 3-inch) in 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool 5 minutes. Remove from pan. May be served with ice cream or fresh fruit.

title: old fashioned apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Combine cinnamon and brown sugar.
Sprinkle 1/2 of mixture over apples. Combine granulated sugar, flour, egg, salt and baking powder. Spread over apple slices.
Sprinkle remaining cinnamon and brown sugar mixture over the top.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Separate eggs; set egg whites aside.
Mix all other ingredients, except vanilla, and cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and pour in deep casserole dish.
Beat egg whites until stiff and holds peaks; beat in 3 tablespoons sugar. Pour over pudding and be sure it touches the side of dish.
Put in oven at 350°; bake until brown as you like, about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat well.
Bake in a 375° oven until done.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces in mixture of flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Melt fat in shallow baking pan in hot (400°) oven. Remove pan from oven.
Place floured chicken in pan, turning to coat with butter.
Leave skin side down.
Keep chicken in single layer.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake for 30 minutes or until tender.
Serves 4.

title: chicken with caramelized onions
directions: Coat large skillet with cooking spray and place over medium heat until hot.
Add onion.
Cover and cook 10 minutes until deep golden, stirring often.
Combine salt, thyme, red pepper and black pepper.
Sprinkle half the mixture over the onions.
Add 1/4 cup chicken broth and cook 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add 6 tablespoons broth and cook until liquid evaporates.
Repeat procedure with remaining broth.
Add vinegar and cook an additional 2 minutes or until most of the liquid evaporates. Remove from pan and keep warm.
Rub chicken with remaining spice mixture.
Coat skillet with cooking spray, then heat.
Add chicken and cook for 2 minutes on each side.
Serve with onions.
Makes 4 servings.

title: low-fat linguini and clam sauce
directions: Saute garlic in oil until golden brown.
Add water, clams with liquid, parsley, salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes or until clams are tender.
Add sauce to cooked pasta.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve.

title: sour cream icebox cookies
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Stir in flour mixture alternately with sour cream.
Add vanilla.
Make into 2 rolls and wrap in oiled paper. Place in refrigerator to chill.
Cut in 1/8-inch slices and bake on ungreased pan at 400°.

title: orange cookies
directions: Mix sugar and butter until it becomes creamy.
Add yogurt, egg white and baking powder and mix.
Put flour and orange juice in and make dough.
Make small balls and pour egg yolk on them.
Bake at 350° until they become golden brown.

title: cream green peas and onions
directions: Drain juice off of onions and put in a sauce pan. Bring to a boil. Add water if needed. Mix butter, salt and pepper in with the onion juice. Add peas and mix well. Add onions to boiling mixture. Mix the 4 Tbsp. of water with the cornstarch. Add to mixture and cook for 20 minutes.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Steam potatoes until tender.
Reserve cooking water.
Saute onion in oil.
Place some of the potatoes, potato water and onion in blender until smooth.
Return mixture to pot and add milk. Stir continuously.
Add cheese, butter, parsley and seasoning.
Do not boil.

title: pecan puff
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Blend in sugar and butter until soft.
Blend until sugar and butter are creamy.
Add vanilla. Stir in flour and pecans.
Roll dough into small balls and place on a well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 300° oven for 45 minutes.
Roll puffs in powdered sugar while hot.

title: chicken spread
directions: Blend together mayonnaise, garlic powder, onion powder and mustard.
Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill before serving. Store refrigerated.

title: steak supper in foil
directions: Place meat on foil in baking pan.
Stir together mushroom soup and onion soup mix.
Spread on meat.
Top with carrots, potatoes and celery.

title: italian bread
directions: Brush bread with olive oil.
Sprinkle with oregano and garlic powder.
Lay on cheese with a slice of tomato on top.
Lightly salt and pepper.
Sprinkle on more oregano.
Bake at 350° until light brown and bubbly.

title: cornbread stuffing
directions: Break up sausage; saute several minutes until gray.
Remove to large mixing bowl, leaving fat in pan.
In pan, saute onions 5 to 6 minutes or until tender.
Add celery and saute 2 minutes.
Add sauteed vegetables to sausage along with cornbread, white bread and eggs.
Season, go heavy on sage.
Fold in melted butter.

title: hawaiian pork chops
directions: Dredge chops in flour.
Brown in skillet. Top each chop with a ring of pineapple.
Add pineapple juice. Cover and cook slowly. Remove meat and pineapple to platter.
Pour the remaining juice over chops.
Cook on stove top 1 1/2 hours.

title: coconut cake
directions: Let cool.
Ice with Cool Whip and coconut and let cool for 2 to 3 hours.
(Better if baked a day before serving.)

title: chicken chalupas
directions: Combine soup, chiles, onion, sour cream, sliced olives, and jack cheese.
Mix, set aside 1 1/2 c. of mixture.
Add chicken to main mixture.
Fill the tortillas and roll up.
Place filled tortillas in 9 x 13 inch baking pan.
Pour remaining mixture over tortillas.
Sprinkle 3/4 c. cheddar cheese on top and garnish with green onion and paprika.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight in water to cover.
In same soaking water, bring beans to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add smoked sausage, onion, bell pepper, salt and pepper. Simmer another 1 1/2 hours or until beans and sausage are tender. Serve over cooked rice.

title: butterscotch spiders
directions: Toss peanuts and noodles in a bowl.
Melt the butterscotch pieces in top of a double boiler, stirring occasionally until smooth.
Pour over peanuts and noodles. Toss until coated.
Drop from spoon.
Chill and serve.

title: potato rolls
directions: Put mashed potatoes and sugar in bowl.
Let cool.
Add potato water and yeast.
Let set together overnight.
In morning, add eggs, butter and flour.
Knead until smooth.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Roll out and shape into rolls (dinner or sweet). Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: rolls
directions: Mix together in small pan the first 4 ingredients; heat until lukewarm.
Combine next 3 ingredients.
Sift flour.
In large bowl, put 4 cups flour; add liquids to flour and mix with spoon. Add additional flour until it can be handled by hand.
When dough begins to leave sides of bowl, turn it out onto a lightly floured board to knead.
Knead.
Fold dough toward you.
Then press down away from you with heel of hand.
Give dough quarter turn; repeat until it is smooth, elastic and doesn't stick to board.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to bring greased side up.
Cover with cloth and let rise in warm, draft free spot (80 to 85°) until doubles, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Use enough flour to shape into desired shapes.
Place in greased cooking pans.
Cover with cloth; let rise until double, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cook at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 36 rolls.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add by hand eggs, flour, baking powder and salt. Fold in sour cream and vanilla.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 1/2 mixture and sprinkle 1/2 of topping on dough.
Add rest of dough and sprinkle remaining topping.

title: country style steak and gravy
directions: Place 4 pieces of cube steak in bottom of crock-pot.
Spread 1/2 can soup and 1/2 package soup mix over steak.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Do not add water.
Cook on low setting for 8 to 10 hours or at high setting for 4 to 5 hours.
Chop after cooking.
This is great over rice or noodles.

title: fruited eggnog bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In large bowl with spoon, mix well the first 5 ingredients.
Stir in eggnog, butter or margarine, egg and rum just until flour is moistened.
Mixture will be lumpy.
Fold in pecans or walnuts and fruits.
Spread mixture in pan.
Bake 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool bread on wire rack 10 minutes.
Wrap and freeze.
Thaw room temperature.

title: no-bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring sugar, margarine and milk to a rolling boil.
Boil 3 minutes on low heat.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal, cocoa, vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix thoroughly and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Let cool until firm.
You can also pour mixture into buttered or vegetable sprayed 9 x 13 pan and let cool, then cut into squares to serve.

title: fried okra patties
directions: Drain okra and mash well.
Add egg and mix thoroughly.
Next add salt, flour, cornmeal, pepper and baking powder.
Mix well.

title: broccoli slaw
directions: Dressing: Mix oil, vinegar, sugar and chicken packet from Ramen noodles. Add to salad just before serving.

title: corn bread for two
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: company casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain grease if necessary.
Add salt, onion and celery.
Continue cooking a few minutes.
Add spaghetti, soups, mushrooms and cheese.
Save about 1/4 cup cheese to sprinkle on top of casserole, which has been buttered.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle atop with cheese and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: fried shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Dip fresh shrimp into batter and fry until golden brown.

title: yvonne's favorite wild rice pilaf
directions: In medium saucepan bring broth to a boil.
Add wild rice to boiling broth.
Bring back to a boil, reduce heat to medium-low and cook, covered, 50 minutes or until tender.
Do not overcook. Remove to large bowl.
In another saucepan, bring 2 1/2 cups water to a boil.
Stir in the pilaf, cover and bring back to a boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer 15 minutes and add to the wild rice. Add remaining ingredients and toss well.
Serve at room temperature.
Serves 8 to 12.
Can be made ahead and served hot or cold.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese and powdered sugar together until smooth.
In separate bowl, mix the peanut butter and milk.
Mix the peanut butter with the cream cheese.
Add the whipped cream. Whip all together. Put in the graham cracker crust.
Chill 4 to 5 hours.
(You may use crunchy peanut butter.)

title: diabetic peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream together margarine, peanut butter, orange rind, vanilla and artificial sweetener.
Add egg and orange juice; blend well.
Add dry ingredients gradually; mix well.
Add raisins.
Measure 1 level tablespoon dough for each cookie.
Roll to form a ball.
Place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.
Makes about 24 cookies.

title: hot fudge frosting
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Then mix cornstarch and cold water together and add to hot mixture.
Cook until thick, then add vanilla.

title: cream cheese torte
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix together the graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted butter.
In greased 13 x 9-inch pan, press the graham cracker crumb mixture.
Pour in the cream cheese mixture.
Put cherries or blueberries, etc., on top, then top with a few more crumbs.
Refrigerate a few hours.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Place 8 slices bread in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Put slices of meat and cheese and top with remaining slices of bread.

title: rhubarb torte
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until crumbly; put half of mixture on bottom of 8-inch square pan.
On top of that, put rhubarb.
Boil the next 3 ingredients together.
Pour over rhubarb and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter oatmeal bars
directions: Combine margarine and sugars and beat well.
Add egg, peanut butter, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add all dry ingredients to beaten mixture; mix until smooth.
Spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (greased).
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Immediately sprinkle chocolate pieces over top; let stand until softened and spread evenly.
Let set several hours before cutting.
Makes 36.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1/2
cup cheese and 1/2 can Durkee onions. Pour into shallow 1 quart baking dish. Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and onions. Bake uncovered 15 minutes until browned.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Saute onion in oil about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Combine 1/4 cup barbecue sauce and 1/4 cup water, add egg, stir in bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Crumble in ground beef.
Add onion and pepper; mix well.
Shape into loaf.
Bake 1 hour.
Spread remaining barbecue sauce on top and bake 30 minutes more.

title: potato ham scallop
directions: In medium saucepan, over low heat, melt butter.
Stir in flour. Remove from heat and gradually stir in milk, keeping smooth.
Cook over moderate low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Remove from heat and stir in cheese.
Fold in potatoes and ham. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Turn into ungreased casserole dish. Bake uncovered at 400° for 20 minutes.
To cook potatoes, peel and slice potatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Boil until tender.
Drain.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, onion and dressing mix.
Mix spinach with last mixture.
Chill.

title: jello jam
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Let set for 30 minutes.
Bring to boil and cook for 12 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O. Stir thoroughly and skim.
Put in hot jars.
Wax or seal as desired.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Mix Cheddar cheese, milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt and pepper. Add to broccoli, onion and green pepper.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: strawberries and cream
directions: Bake cake according to directions, in layer pans, and let cool.
Carefully slice each layer in half using a long serrated knife.
Spread each layer with strawberry jam or glaze.
To assemble, place one layer, cut side down, on plate; top with sliced strawberries, then Cool Whip.
Repeat with each layer. Spread Cool Whip on top.
Decorate with hearts and strawberries.

title: ella wright's sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper; drain off grease.
Add sauce and simmer until done, about 30 minutes.

title: crab meat salad
directions: Oil a glass bowl and set aside.
Stir all ingredients together well.
Put in oiled bowl and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Serve with lettuce and crackers.

title: banana pudding(no bake)
directions: Prepare vanilla pudding. Fold in cool whip. Layer vanilla wafers on bottom and sides of casserole dish. Slice bananas and layer on wafers. Pour pudding mixture on wafers and bananas. Crumble wafers on top.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder, mace and nutmeg.
Add to the butter mixture, alternating with the milk and rum.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until a straw comes out clean.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Fold in the flour and mace, then the vanilla.
Bake at 350° until tests done.
This recipe is over 60 years old.

title: grilled maryland soft crabs with seafood marinade
directions: Dress live crabs*; thaw crabs if frozen.
Liberally baste bottom side of crabs with marinade and carefully place, bottom side down, on barbecue grill.
Grill over fire, at least 12 inches from coals, for 5 minutes.
Liberally baste top of crabs with marinade, turn carefully and grill 5 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings, 2 crabs each.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Combine vinegar, water, salt, pepper, onion, celery flakes and pickling spice to make marinade.
Place meat in this mixture, making sure it is covered with liquid.
Cover and let stand 2 hours.
Add sugar.
Place over heat and simmer, covered, 2 hours or until tender.
Remove meat to platter.
Strain liquid to remove spices.
Return to cooking pan.
Stir in enough gingersnap crumbs to thicken gravy.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8. Serve with Potato Balls.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Cook wild rice in water until done (45 minutes to an hour). Cook bacon until crisp and crumble.
Saute onion in little bacon grease. Place potato soup in large saucepan, dilute and add all other ingredients.
Heat slowly, stirring often until cheese is melted, just below boiling point.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: tea scones(makes 16)
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add the egg and milk, stirring until dough follows the fork around the bowl.
Knead on floured surface about 15 times and cut it in half.
Shape each half into a ball and pat that into a circle 1/2-inch thick and about 6-inches in diameter.
Cut this piece into 8 wedges.

title: party punch
directions: Thaw juices. In a large bowl, blend milk, water, juices, sugar and salt. Stir until sugar is dissolved. Spoon sherbet into punch, stirring lightly. Makes 20 (1/2) cups.

title: lemon pudding cheese cake
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend with 1/2 cup milk.
Add 1 1/2 cups milk and pudding mix; beat slowly with mixer for about 1 minute. Pour at once into graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: russell's chicken casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13 inch pan with pam. Place chicken on bottom of pan, then mixed vegetables, spread the soup over vegetables, then add the cheese.
Mix the stuffing as directed on the box and spread over the cheese.
Bake in a 400 degree oven for 30 minutes. Can substitute pork chops for the chicken, cream of mushroom soup for the chicken soup and pork flavored dressing mix.

title: betty robbins' lemon butter
directions: Cook over hot water until thick.
Can be used as a filling for tarts or cakes, or as spread for toast or biscuits.
Delicious served over a spoonful of cottage cheese.

title: instant orange cake
directions: Mix together first two ingredients.
Add oil, water and eggs. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lentil salad *
directions: Wash and pick over lentils.

Put them in a pot with 1 1/2 quarts of cold water, the onion, bay leaf, salt, pepper and cumin. Bring the beans to a boil; turn off the heat and let stand 1 hour. Then simmer about 5 minutes, or until just tender.
Lentils used to take hours to cook, but most are processed now and the problem is to avoid mushiness.
(If you accidentally overcook them, you can turn the disaster in a good soup or pureed vegetable.)
Drain the lentils and discard the onion and bay leaf.
After cooling to room temperature, dress them with the vinaigrette and garnish with the eggs and parsley.

title: pineapple cheese dip
directions: Mix at room temperature cream cheese, chopped green pepper, chopped onion and drained crushed pineapple.
Mix until smooth and creamy.
Mix in seasoned salt to taste.
Serve chilled with Ritz or Townhouse crackers.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Serves 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Place cut up chicken in bottom of 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Pour can of soup over chicken.
Mix stuffing, broth and melted margarine.
Spread this over chicken and soup.
Pour milk evenly over the top.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake another 15 minutes to brown.
Makes 2 casseroles.

title: cajun gumbo
directions: Debone chicken after cooking and put back in broth.
Add other ingredients.
Make flour gravy brown, almost burned, and put into gumbo.
Cook until desired thickness.
Serve over rice.

title: fish in microwave
directions: Lay fish in casserole dish.
Pour melted butter over fish; add salt, pepper and lemon juice to taste.
Microwave for 5
to 6 minutes, depending on microwave.

title: smothered chicken-country style
directions: Cut up chicken, salt, roll each piece in flour and place in roaster.
Layer bacon, onion and celery leaves on top.
Cover with water and bake at 350° for 3 hours.

title: french cream frosting
directions: Cook on low heat to pudding stage.
Cool thoroughly.

title: gooseberry salad
directions: Let the gooseberries and sugar set for 4 hours. Mix gooseberries with 1 cup each celery (thin sliced), nuts and shredded Cheddar cheese. Top with cream cheese and Cool Whip or 1/2 cup mayonnaise.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, beat sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs and beat well.
Add flour, cream of tartar and baking soda and mix well.
In a small bowl, combine cinnamon and sugar.
Shape dough into one-inch balls and roll in cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until set.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: shoe leather
directions: After foot has already been inserted in mouth, it may be hard to swallow, but take out and add 1 cup of humility and borrow 2 cups of forgiveness.
May be done with or without shoes and socks.

title: pineapple surprise
directions: Place pineapple in an 11 x 8-inch glass baking pan.
Mix sugar and flour; sprinkle over the pineapple.
Put grated cheese over this.
Mix crackers and margarine; spread over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chalupas
directions: Cover roast and beans with water in a large pan. Add all other ingredients.

title: broccoli muffins
directions: Beat eggs; add all the other ingredients.
Pour into greased muffin pans.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium saucepan, combine first 8 ingredients and simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Add cooked meat, 3 ounces of cheese, rice and stir until cheese is melted.
Place in deep dish (Corning or Pyrex), sprinkle top with remaining 1 ounce of cheese and bake for 20 to 30 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix hamburger, rice and onion and form into balls and place into casserole dish.
Mix soup and milk together and pour over meatballs.
Cook at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Mix with sour cream, soups and cheese.
Partially thaw potatoes.
Mix sauce over potatoes.
Spread 1/2 cup grated cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together in a bowl.
Dip chicken wings in mixture; place in baking pan.
Sprinkle with 1 envelope dressing mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown. Remove to wire rack; sprinkle with paprika.
Mix remaining envelope dressing mix and sour cream in bowl.
Serve dip surrounded by chicken wings and celery sticks.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes in saucepan.
Add other ingredients and cook over medium heat for 45 minutes, uncovered, or until juice is slightly thickened.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix all together and let stand in refrigerator for at least one day.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients. Add milk alternately, about 1/2 at a time.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: liver dumpling soup
directions: Heat milk with margarine. Pour over ingredients and mix together. Chill for about 1 hour. Form balls and drop into boiling beef broth; dumpling will rise to the top when done.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Fold all ingredients together.
Pour into pretty glass bowl. Chill.
Enjoy!

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Serve warm with Tostitos.

title: "no-marinade" sauerbraten
directions: I like to double up on gravy ingredients.

title: aunt mae's chocolate gravy
directions: Mix dry ingredients together. Add milk and cook over medium heat until it boils or starts to thicken. Add butter and vanilla. Serve with biscuits or pancakes.

title: amazin raisin cake with old fashion icing
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9 in.) round cake pans.
In large bowl with mixer at low speed; beat first 10 ingredients for 2 minutes; scraping bowl frequently.
Stir in apples, raisins & nuts.
Pour into pans and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Mix soup together; chop other ingredients, reserving all liquid.
Add remaining ingredients except noodles.
Add reserved liquid to make desired consistency.
Heat on low heat for approximately 20 minutes.
Take off and serve after adding soy sauce to taste.
Serve over rice.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Mix hamburger and onion soup mix.
Shape into small balls. Brown in skillet and drain.
Mix jelly and chili sauce in saucepan.
Add meat balls and simmer for at least 1 hour.

title: rum sauce
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and egg.
Mix well.
Microwave on medium.
Stir and scrape down sides for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes until sugar dissolves and sauce thickens.
Stir in rum.
Serve warm.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix sugar, sour cream and coconut together and place in refrigerator overnight, covered.

title: almond-rhubarb coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour, salt, baking soda and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in rhubarb and almonds. Pour into 2 (9-inch) pans or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cut up eggplant.
Boil in salted water with onion and celery.
Drain well.
Mix all other ingredients, except cheese. Pour into greased baking dish.
Cover top with grated cheese. Bake in 350° oven for about 25 minutes.

title: delicious cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix together the sour cream, soup, cheese, salt, pepper, onion and potatoes.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and bake for 30 minutes more.
Easy to fix and so good!

title: pizza sauce
directions: Mix and store in covered container.

title: spicy bean, corn and pepper salad
directions: In a small bowl, combine apple juice, vinegar, salsa and black pepper.
In another bowl, combine beans, corn, peppers and scallions.
Pour in salsa mixture.
Chill for at least 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Sift the dry ingredients and mix all together.
Add a cup of raisins, dates or nuts if desired. Put in 3 greased loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: noodles romanoff
directions: In a saucepan, mix butter, sour cream and milk and heat until mixture is almost boiling.
Remove from heat and add Cheddar cheese and salt and pepper.
Pour over hot noodles.
Serve immediately or microwave later until heated through.
Serves 6.

title: dump cake
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl and beat well.
Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: cheese blintze souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients except the blintzes in the blender. Refrigerate overnight.

title: chewy brownie cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat on medium the Crisco, brown sugar, water and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture on low speed until just blended.
Stir in chips.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 2-inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake one sheet at a time
at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes.
Cookies will appear soft and moist.
Do not overbake.
Cool on baking sheet 2 minutes. Remove cookies to foil to cool completely.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; salt and pepper to taste.
Put in 5-quart Dutch oven the noodles, hamburger, peas, corn, tomato soup, ketchup and barbecue sauce.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour.

title: old fashioned lemon sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Stir together flour, baking powder, and salt; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat sugar and shortening until fluffy; beat in eggs.
Stir in dry ingredients. Add in lemon juice.
Mix well.
Chill 2 hours or overnight.
Shape into small balls, 1
1/4 inches or less;
roll in additional sugar.
Place on greased baking sheets 2 inches apart; flatten with egg turner.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: fish and fries
directions: Place thawed fish in single layer in greased dish. Cover with frozen crinkle-cut French fries. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over the fish and fries. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef, sausage and Tabasco sauce. Pour off grease and cool.
Add cheese and spices.
Mix ingredients and spread on bread slices.
Bake on cookie sheet for 15 minutes. Serve hot.

title: potato leek soup
directions: Melt butter; add onions and leeks.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Blend in flour 2 minutes; gradually add 1 cup hot water. Blend thoroughly.
Add vegetables and rest of water.
Stir and add salt and pepper.
Cook 40 minutes.
Now, add 2 cups milk and sour cream before serving.

title: brownies
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl and beat until smooth.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: thai-style chicken salad
directions: Grate enough peel from 1 lime to measure 1/2 teaspoon. Squeeze enough juice from limes to measure 3 tablespoons .

Whisk oil, ginger, curry powder, lime peel and lime juice to blend in small bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Divide greens and red bell pepper between 2 large plates. Heat dressing in heavy medium skillet over medium heat. Add chicken; toss until heated through, about 2 minutes. Spoon chicken and dressing over greens, dividing equally.
Sprinkle peanuts over and serve.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Remove pieces of chicken from broth and keep hot.
Skim fat from broth.
Blend fat and flour.
Stir in several spoonfuls of the broth and pour the mixture into the rest of the broth, stirring constantly. Cook this gravy until slightly thickened and season.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Cream shortening, egg, sugar, molasses, cinnamon, soda, salt and ginger with mixer.
Stir in flour by hand.
Roll in balls; roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: squash souffle
directions: Mix squash, margarine, sugar, flour, eggs and milk (dairy rich) in a blender.
Pour into a souffle dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350°
for one hour or until firm in center.

title: chocolate berry shortcake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine baking mix, cocoa and nutmeg in a medium bowl; mix well.
Add yogurt, honey and oil, stirring until soft dough forms.

title: easy clam chowder
directions: Mix soup and milk as instructed by soup can.
Add clams and juice.
Heat and serve.

title: spinach fettuccine(with carrots, shrimp and snow peas)
directions: Prepare
fettuccine
according
to
package directions. Meanwhile, blend
cornstarch
and
orange
juice together in a small bowl until smooth; set aside. In heavy skillet over high heat in melted butter, saute shrimp, snow peas and tomato just until shrimp curl and become opaque, about 2 minutes.
Stir in orange sauce; cook until sauce thickens, about 1 minute.
When pasta is just
about
al
dente,
toss in carrot curls, cook 1 minute and
drain.
Toss
with
sauce and mushrooms and season with fresh
ground pepper, garnish with fresh chives.
Makes 2 servings.

title: grape jelly(microwave)
directions: Combine in an 8 to 12-cup measure (with a handle) thawed juice and pectin.
Stir in water; blend well.
Cover and microwave on High for 7 to 8 minutes, stirring 1 time.
Blend in sugar.
Cover and microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes, stirring 1 time.
After jelly is boiling, stir again and microwave on High 1 minute.
Skim off foam.
This gets very hot, you must be careful, especially when removing cover.
Pour into sterilized jars.
A great Christmas gift.

title: homemade chili
directions: Heat oil in large skillet; add garlic, beef, onions and green pepper.
Pour off fat.
Add beans.
Stir in sauce, salt and chili powder.
Simmer about 45 minutes.

title: baked vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Lightly spray baking dish with Pam. Pour into baking dish. Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until heated through and slightly browned on top.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Mix butter and brown sugar; let stand.
Drain pineapple.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with butter mixture, pineapple, nuts and cherries. Sift together salt, flour and baking powder.
Beat egg yolks until lemon colored.
Add sugar and beat.
Add juice and fold in flour.
Beat and fold in egg whites.
Pour over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Tip upside down when done.

title: crustless vegetarian quiche
directions: Saute zucchini and mushrooms in butter in medium skillet until tender-crisp.
Spray a 9-inch pie pan with nonstick vegetable spray; place vegetables and cheese in pan.

title: salsa
directions: Peel and chop tomatoes.
Drain in colander.
Chop onions and peppers.
In large pot, combine all ingredients; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cook until thick, stirring often.
Pour into sterilized jars.
Pressure cook for 10 minutes.
If you like it hot, add some jalapeno peppers, chili hot peppers and/or habenaro peppers.

title: boriah's curried soup
directions: Start with 1 or 2 teaspoons of curry powder in a small bowl. Add a few drops of boiling water to dry spice.
Mix to form a "paste".
Mix the 6 cans of soup and the 2 cans of milk in a large saucepan.
Combine these slowly, a small amount at a time.
Heat gradually but do not boil.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add dates, pineapple, cherries and pecans.
Work with hands until all ingredients are blended.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 13 minutes.

title: waldorf astoria rolls(easy)
directions: Add yeast to warm water to dissolve. Add sugar, salt and well beaten eggs to melted butter. Stir in flour. Mix thoroughly (this is soft dough). Cover with wax paper.
Place in refrigerator overnight (or longer).
Divide into 3 equal parts. Roll as for pie crust, 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into wedges.
Roll up beginning with wide edge.
Put on greased pan.
Let rise 2 to 3 hours. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Makes 24 to 30 rolls.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Cook and drain bacon and ground beef, separately.
Saute onions in very small amount of oil or bacon grease.
Put in crock-pot.
Add beans - do not drain.
Add catsup and brown sugar; stir and let simmer several hours.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon; crumble and set aside.
Fry ground beef in bacon grease; stir to break up meat.
Drain grease from ground beef.
Add onion, brown sugar, sugar, ketchup, barbecue sauce, mustard, syrup, chili powder, salt, pepper, butter beans, pork and beans, red beans and bacon.
Mix and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bran refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and set aside.
Mix shortening, sugar, boiling water, all-bran cereal and salt.
Stir and cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs and yeast mixture.
Stir in flour. Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Knead and roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Cover; let rise approximately 2 hours.
Bake at 400° for about 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 50 rolls.

title: scones
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut shortening into flour mix. Beat egg and sour milk together and mix into dry ingredients quickly.
Pat out on floured board 1/2-inch thick.
Cut 3-inches in diameter.
Bake on ungreased sheet at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind first 4 ingredients and soak in 1 cup of salt overnight. Rinse with cool water the next morning.
Squeeze all water from the ground vegetables.
Mix last 6 ingredients with the vegetables.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: new year's snacks
directions: Mix cheese, meat and onion.
Cut biscuits in half and flatten. Spoon teaspoon of cheese mixture on biscuit half, fold and squeeze.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown onion, green pepper, garlic and ground beef together in a heavy frying pan.
Drain off any fat.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, salt and cayenne pepper.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Pour into a 10 x 13-inch baking dish.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In a
heavy saucepan, combine corn meal, salt and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Spoon over meat in 3 crosswise strips.
Bake 40 minutes until lightly browned.
Good served with a salad and garlic bread.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple fluff cake
directions: Take cake out of oven; make fork holes in cake.
Pour pineapple over top.
Make a mixture of cream cheese, milk and pudding.
Cover cake with this mixture.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: marshmallow creme fudge
directions: Mix sugar, Milnot and margarine together and cook until mixture comes to a boil, stirring frequently.
Boil this mixture for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from fire and stir in chocolate morsels and Marshmallow Creme.
Stir together until mixture is creamy and smooth.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan. Allow to cool and cut as desired.
Yields approximately 3 pounds.

title: easy sweet rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease a 9-inch round cake pan. Prepare basic biscuits, rolling dough into a rectangle about 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle evenly over dough.
Roll up, jelly roll fashion, beginning with long side.
Slice into 1/2-inch slices. Place slices into prepared pan.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.
Drizzle with icing.

title: frosty peach punch
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients, stirring until gelatin dissolves.
Add water, drink mix and pineapple juice.
Stir until lemonade dissolves.
Divide mixture into two 1-gallon size, heavy-duty, Ziploc plastic bags.
Seal and freeze.
Place frozen mixture in a punch bowl; let thaw partially.
Add 1 bottle lemon-lime beverage to each bag of peach mixture in bowl.
Stir gently.
Yields 2 gallons.

title: corn, pea, bean salad
directions: Drain first 3 ingredients.
Heat water, sugar, vinegar and celery seed to dissolve.
When cool, pour over drained veggies and refrigerate.
Green pepper and celery chopped fine is a nice addition.

title: pork chop bake
directions: In large skillet brown chops and drain.
In a buttered baking dish arrange potatoes and mushrooms, add pork chops.
In a small bowl combine water and soup.
Pour over meat.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, cream cheese and sour cream.
Add vanilla. For the crust, mix together graham cracker crumbs and walnuts. Add melted butter and line bottom of spring-form cake pan.
Pour in filling and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool.
Chill overnight.

title: saucy soy sizzlers
directions: Soak soybeans overnight, then blend soybeans in 1 cup water until very smooth.
Pour into bowl.
Add rolled oats and let stand 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by tablespoon and form into patties on a nonstick pan.
Brown on both sides.
Sizzlers taste delicious in sandwiches or in pita bread.

title: hickory nut pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, syrup, vanilla and oleo, adding nuts last. Pour into pie shell and bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 40 minutes longer.

title: spice cake
directions: Blend salad oil and sugar.
Whip in eggs.
Stir in applesauce into creamed mixture.
Add dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Bake in ungreased large tube cake pan.
Line bottom only with circle of waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan.
May be iced with cream cheese icing.
You can substitute canned pumpkin for the applesauce for a change.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Layer eggplant, onions and green peppers.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, basil, pepper and Parmesan.
Build up above top of casserole.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy chow-chow
directions: Bring to boil.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Pack in hot jars. Seal and process in hot water bath for 5 minutes.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into 2 rolls and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Wrap in wax paper. Slice and bake.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa and salt.
Mix all ingredients. Bake in greased and floured 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot artichoke canapes
directions: Mix mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese, green chilies and artichoke hearts together.
Put 1 teaspoon of the mixture on bite size Melba toast rounds.
Put under broiler until lightly browned on top. Makes 5 dozen.

title: shoppers quick chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion. Drain. Add tomato soup, sugar and beans. Heat 5 minutes. Serves 4.

title: graham cracker crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place whole graham crackers on baking sheet.
Boil for 3 minutes (no longer) the butter, margarine, brown sugar and pecans.
Spoon over graham crackers hurriedly. Bake in 325° oven for 9 minutes (no longer).
Let cool and break into pieces.

title: applesauce oatmeal pudding (breakfast)
directions: Combine milk, brown sugar, butter, salt and cinnamon and bring to boil. Stir in and heat until bubbles from around the pan the remaining ingredients. Place in 1 1/2-quart pan or dish (Corning Ware). Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6. Can do ahead and refrigerate. Microwave to serve.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix well and let stand overnight.

title: caramel kiss thumbprints
directions: Remove wrappers. Grease cookie sheets. Beat brownie mix, syrup pouch, cocoa, eggs, oil and water until well blended.
Cover and chill 1 hour or so (dough will be sticky).

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and bananas, then add the egg.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all but oil together.
While beating at high speed, slowly add oil.
Makes about 1 1/2 pints.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix hash browns and onion.
Melt cream cheese, oleo and mushroom soup.
Layer 1/2 potato mixture and 1/2 cream cheese mixture in glass baking dish, 9 x 13-inch.
Repeat layers.

title: southwest stew
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes.
Garnish with cheese, if desired.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook linguine noodles; drain.
Toss all ingredients and refrigerate.
Stir and serve.

title: cherry pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco
and
sugar until fluffy.	Add eggs 1 at a time and beat well.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Stir in flavorings and cherries.
Bake in floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix cream cheese with powdered sugar.
Mix Dream Whip according to directions.
Mix with mixture and place in graham crust.
Spread with strawberry glaze.
Place split strawberries on top and chill.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Melt margarine; add stuffing mix and mix well.
Spread 3/4 mixture in bottom of greased 11 x 7-inch casserole.
Lay deboned chicken on top, then mushrooms.
Mix well the sour cream, soup and 1 cup of stock.
Spoon over mixture in dish.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over top.
Pour remaining stock over top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar and spice balls
directions: Blend butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add all remaining ingredients to butter and sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Roll in confectioners sugar while still warm.

title: hungarian stuffed cabbage
directions: Saute onion and garlic in bacon grease.
Wash rice.
Mix together the ground meat, ground pork, rice, egg, onion, garlic and salt and pepper to taste.
Remove core from cabbage; in a large pot of boiling water, cook head of cabbage until tender and leaves of cabbage come loose.
When cool, remove thick vein from back of cabbage leaves.
Place small amount of meat mixture in a cabbage leaf and roll.
Repeat, using all of the meat mixture and cabbage leaves.
Layer bottom of pan with sauerkraut, oxtail (if desired) and 1/2 can of tomatoes.
Add cabbage rolls and repeat layer of sauerkraut.
Add remaining 1/2 can of tomatoes.
Pour tomato juice over the cabbage rolls, then add enough water to the pot to cover the cabbage rolls.
Cover pot; simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Makes about 10 medium stuffed cabbages.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels. Add sugar and melted butter. Bake in ovenproof dish for 7 minutes at 400°.
Remove from oven and let cool.

title: pizza dogs
directions: Split rolls; toast lightly.
Cut hot dogs into thin circles. Mix cheese, tomato paste, sugar, oregano and garlic salt.
Spread on rolls.
Overlap hot dog circles on cheese spread.
Broil for 5 minutes.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Flatten with a fork that has been dipped in cold water. Bake on ungreased cookie sheets for 12 minutes at 325°.

title: homemade rolls
directions: In small bowl mix sugar, salt, 1/3 stick butter and water. Stir to dissolve sugar.
In large bowl sprinkle yeast in lukewarm water; stir to dissolve.
Add to this egg and 1 cup of flour. Beat on medium speed until smooth.
Add remaining flour slowly to make a soft dough. Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Roll out the rolls, put in pan and pour melted butter over.
Let rise for 2 hours.
Bake at 400° for about 8 to 12 minutes.

title: lemon chicken
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in shortening; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover; simmer 45 minutes or until done. Stir often.
Makes 4 servings.

title: kansas cowhand cookies
directions: Melt butter; blend in sugars, eggs and peanut butter.
Add oats, flour, soda, dates and chocolate chips.
Mixture will be sticky.
Drop on greased cookie sheet with ice cream scoop or a large spoon.
Flatten slightly; each cookie should be about 3-inches in diameter.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove to cooling rack.
Makes 2 dozen big cookies.

title: banana muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Blend together oleo, sugar and egg; mix well with other ingredients.
Bake in small muffin tins for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and put in deep dish (1 1/2 to 2-quart).
Mix flour, sugar and 1/2 cup of milk; beat until smooth.
Add rest of milk.
Pour batter over butter; don't mix! Place fruit in center of batter.
Cook 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add ground beef to remaining ingredients.
Cook on low for 30 minutes.
Top with grated cheese and serve with Fritos chips.

title: junk salad
directions: Mix all together and let stand 2 hours in refrigerator.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: deep-dish apple pie
directions: Line pie plate with half of the pastry, rolled to 1/8-inch thickness.
Set aside.
Cook apples in water in a heavy covered pan 5 or 6 minutes, or until apples are about half cooked.
Drain and cool.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Turn the apples into the pie plate.
Mix the sugar, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon together. Sprinkle over apples and dot with butter.
Roll out top crust. Place over apples; trim, turn under bottom crust and flute.
Cut vents in top.
Sprinkle with additional sugar.
Bake 10 minutes before reducing oven to 350°.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes until crust is nicely browned.
Serves 8.

title: sambal chili paste dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and then blend all together.

title: chow mein burgers
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add chop suey vegetables.
Add soy sauce, water and cornstarch.
Cook two minutes until thickened. Spoon onto hamburger buns.
Sprinkle with chow mein noodles.

title: cauliflower puff
directions: In blender, whirl until smooth the cauliflower, egg yolks, milk, salt and pepper.
In medium bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually fold in the cauliflower mixture, onion and Cheddar cheese.
Spread over the bottom of a buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Drizzle with the margarine and sprinkle with the Parmesan. Bake in a preheated 375° oven until golden brown and set, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter; add powdered sugar and mix well with flour and nuts.
Put teaspoon each on cookie sheet; bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool on rack and coat heavily with powdered sugar.
(Sift powdered sugar first, if lumpy.)

title: frankfurters, cheese and bacon
directions: Split cocktail frankfurter and insert a piece of Cheddar cheese.
Wrap with a third slice of bacon tightly to seal in cheese and secure with a toothpick.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until bacon is crisp.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix these ingredients and use with strawberries, honeydew melon, grapes, watermelon, cantaloupe, chunk pineapple or most any fruit.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift flour with sugar, salt, soda and cocoa.
Add mayonnaise, water and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Frost with white or chocolate frosting.
Great when you're out of eggs or oil.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Drain asparagus, reserving juice.
Add enough water to make 2 cups.
Combine juice, sugar, vinegar and salt and bring to a boil. Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add hot mixture.
Stir until dissolved.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Add remaining ingredients except lettuce.
Mix well and pour into an 8-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: old fashioned meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Press firmly into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan or shape into loaf and place in 8 x 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake 55 to 60
minutes; drain.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate refrigerator dessert
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add nuts and flour; mix and press into bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool. Mix cream cheese with powdered sugar.
Add vanilla and 1/2 container of Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Mix pudding with milk. Pour over whipped cream layer.
Spread with remaining Cool Whip. Sprinkle with nuts, chocolate chips or cherries.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes.
Soak bread in 1 cup milk.
Saute onion in 1 tablespoon butter; add to bread with parsley.
Beat potatoes with bread and milk mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add remaining milk.
Add eggs; beat well.
Pour mixture into greased casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fudge nut brownie cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease cookie sheets.
In a large bowl, combine brownie mix, flour, water, oil and egg.
By hand, stir with spoon until dough is formed.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful 2-inches apart onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes. Cool 1 minute. Remove from cookie sheets. Cool completely. Frost cookies with chocolate fudge frosting.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Put all ingredients in food processor or blender.
Refrigerate overnight.
Place in greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: fresh mushroom bisque
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until mushrooms and onion are tender (4 to 5 minutes).
Stir in flour and pepper until smooth and bubbly (1 minute).
Add chicken broth and carrots.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until carrots are crisply tender (8 to 10 minutes).
Add half and half and hot pepper sauce; continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until heated through (7 to 9 minutes).
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: old fashion tomato soup
directions: In saucepan, combine first 6 ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Heat cream in top of double boiler (until warm).
Add to tomato mixture just before serving.
Serves 8.

title: spicy baked fish
directions: Bake fish at 350° in a greased 9-inch baking pan for about 20 minutes.
Drain cooking liquid from fish.
While fish is baking, cook onion and green pepper in oil until onion is clear.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper to cooked onion and green pepper.
Cook 20 minutes to blend flavors.
Pour sauce over drained fish.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Serves four (about 110 calories each).

title: tomato aspic
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Simmer uncovered 5 minutes. Strain.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Add wheels, rotini and mostaccioli to boiling water; cook according to directions, drain and add to hamburger mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add the onion, garlic, salt, chili powder, tomato sauce, consomme, corn, parsley and olives; heat to boiling in an iron skillet.
Stir in 7 ounces of corn chips.
Scoop this into a 2-quart greased casserole dish; sprinkle with the Cheddar cheese and chopped olives.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Prayer is
the
key to use in the morning to unlock the day and the key to lock up the day at night.

title: bombay turkey
directions: Melt butter. Add curry.
Heat for 3 to 4 minutes. Stir in onion and saute. Add flour, salt and pepper.
Add broth.
Cook and stir until it boils.
Cook 2 minutes longer. Add turkey and lemon peel.
Heat to boiling.
Serve over rice.

title: trash
directions: Mix seasonings in melted butter and drippings.
Pour over cereals.
Mix well.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.
Makes a lot!!!!!!!

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Divide all ingredients into thirds and assemble into 3 layers in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
End with spaghetti sauce.
Reserve 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese for top.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Simmer at 50% for 30 minutes.
Top with reserved cheese and microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes.
When using turkey, salt and pepper may be added while browning.

title: fresh spinach salad dressing
directions: Mix in jar and refrigerate overnight.
Pour over salad of fresh spinach, fried bacon, fresh sliced mushrooms and chopped hard-boiled eggs.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Make cake mix according to directions and bake in 2 layers. Use a thread and split each layer.
This will give a 4-layer cake. Make a filling out of the sour cream, sugar, coconut and a little of the Cool Whip.
Spread between layers.
Mix the remainder of the Cool Whip in the sour cream mixture and frost the outside of the cake.
Cover and let set in refrigerator for 3 days before serving (probably won't last that long).

title: orange salad
directions: Cook Jell-O and pudding in the juice/water until boiling. Stir in marshmallows and pineapple; let cool.
Fold in Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: pumpkin pineapple loaf
directions: Cut in 1/2 C. lard, do NOT substitute other shortening.
Add 1 cup thick buttermilk (all at once).

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Cook chicken in salt water with carrots and onions for one hour.
Debone chicken and mix with other ingredients. in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Take out one hour before baking.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for one hour.

title: strawberries in snow
directions: Mix yogurt, extracts and sugar.
Fold in strawberries.
Spoon into sherbet glasses and refrigerate several hours.
Serves 4.

title: you're lucky if there's anything left
directions: Do not use directions on pudding package.
Beat pudding with milk until set.
Spread on second layer.

title: christopher's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape like a - what else - meat loaf.
After cooking about 1/2 hour in 350° oven, pour the can of tomato sauce over meat loaf and cook another 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cajun spiced potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil. Cover and cook on low until tender with half of gravy cooked down. (This is very spicy hot; may need to cut spices to 1/2 tablespoon.)

title: parmesan puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Dip biscuit tops into butter, then cheese.
Place cheese side up on baking sheet.
Bake until golden, about 8 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate macaroon cookies
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Add sugar and beat again.
Fold in rest of ingredients.
Drop on waxed papered cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for around 12 minutes.
Remove immediately.

title: grapefruit baked alaska
directions: Cut grapefruit in halves; remove cores.
Cut around each section, loosening fruit from membrane.
Sprinkle lightly with sugar; chill.
When ready to serve, preheat oven to 500°.
Add salt to egg whites and beat until foamy throughout; gradually add 6 tablespoons sugar, beating until very stiff and glossy.
Add vanilla.
Remove grapefruit halves from refrigerator.
Place heaping spoonful of ice cream in center of each half.
Cover with meringue.
Place in preheated oven until lightly browned, about 1 minute.
Serve at once.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: In a blender or food processor, process cranberries until coarsely ground.
Pour into a bowl, add sugar.
Cover and chill for 1 hour. Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 c. of juice.
In a large bowl, combine pineapple, juice and marshmallows.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Add cranberry mixture.
Add whipped topping; add walnuts if desired.
Transfer to two 8 inch square dishes.
Cover and freeze for up to 2 months.
Remove from freezer about 45 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.

title: beefy-cabbage soup
directions: Saute ground round and onions.
Pour into crock-pot, along with salsa, tomato sauce, beans and seasonings.
Fill salsa jar and tomato sauce cans with water; add to pot.
Stir well.
Add chopped cabbage.
Simmer for several hours on low or for about 2 hours on high.
Serves 6.

title: blackberry pudding
directions: Cream 1 cup sugar and butter until light and fluffy. Add flour, baking powder, salt and milk. Mix well and spoon batter into a 3-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle blackberries and 1 cup sugar over batter. Add water. Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until done. Serve warm; top with ice cream. Makes 6 servings.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, margarine, cooked rice, bread and milk (it is best to pour milk over bread and let soak).
Pour in Pam sprayed casserole.
Cook until it begins to thicken.
I let mine be a little soupy, then when it gets cool, it thickens.

title: polly doodles
directions: Melt caramels with 3 tablespoons water in double boiler.
Add pecans and stir.
Dip with tablespoon and drop on greased cookie sheet.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin. Dip caramel mixture into chocolate and cool on wax paper.

title: gorgonzola pizza
directions: Note: This diet is designed to help you cope with the stress that builds up during the day.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Combine butter and crumbs; press into a pan.
Layer with chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and coconut.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Pour Eagle Brand milk on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Three dozen marshmallows, one cup thick cream, 1 small can pineapple, sugar, nut and maraschino cherries.

After the pineapple has been run through a food chopper, mix it into the cream which has been whipped. Clip each marshmallow into six or eight pieces, then pour the cream and pineapple over the marshmallows.
Sweeten to taste.
Pile in sherbet glasses and sprinkle the top of each with crushed nut meats and a maraschino cherry.

title: traditional pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix everything in large mixing bowl. Pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes; reduce oven to 350°.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: honey wheat germ bread
directions: In a large mixer bowl, measure 1 cup unbleached flour and stir in dry milk, wheat germ, salt, yeast and hot water.
Add vegetable oil, honey and 2 cups whole wheat flour.
Beat 3 minutes at medium-high speed with mixer.
Stop mixer.
Add 1 cup whole wheat flour and 1/2 to 1 cup unbleached flour, 1/2 cup at a time, first with a spoon and then by hand.
Knead 5 to 8 minutes until smooth and elastic.
Put dough back into mixing bowl and pat top with greased fingertips.
Let rise 1 hour or until double.

title: calzone
directions: Mix up yeast dinner roll dough and refrigerate overnight.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and roll into a ball.
Use as a spread for crackers.

title: nathan's corn casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into a buttered, 9 x 9-inch pan or casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake until the cheese melts (about 10 minutes).
Serves 8 to 10.
Makes a quick and easy delicious side dish.

title: taco dip
directions: Each item is one layer.
Spread in a cake pan as listed.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Mix all ingredients well, roll in balls about size of walnut. Chill for 1 hour.

title: magic fudge pie
directions: Combine chocolate, butter and eggs.
Stir until creamy.
Add flour, sugar, vanilla and pecans.
Pour ingredients into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.

title: artichoke crab dip
directions: Combine first three ingredients in food processor.
Pulse just until combined.
Pour into casserole dish and mix in shredded crab.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with tortilla chips while still warm.

title: chips and chetchup
directions: Put chips on plate.
Squirt ketchup on plate but be sure not to let the two touch.
Dip chips in Chetchup and eat.

title: individual egg nog serving
directions: Break eggs into blender.
Add sugar and bourbon.
Mix well. Add other ingredients and blend.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Drink it.

title: creamy white frosting
directions: Mix milk and flour.
Cook over heat until thick.
Cool completely, stirring occasionally.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl.
Add cooked mixture.
Beat 15 minutes on high until fluffy.

title: best ever sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Divide in half.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Cut in shapes; place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 6 minutes at 350°.
Can be doubled.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter biscuits and shake them 8 at a time in a bag with 3/4 cup sugar and the cinnamon.
Put biscuits in a greased angel food or Bundt pan.
Boil 1 cup sugar and oleo.
Pour over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from pan and let cool.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
This dip is good for apples and strawberries.

title: butterhorns
directions: Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt; cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in water and add to other liquid; stir well.
Add eggs, then flour.
Mix to smooth soft dough.
Knead lightly on floured surface.
Place in greased bowl, cover and let rise until at least double.
Divide in thirds, roll each on floured surface to 9-inch circle.
Brush with melted butter.
Cut in 12 to 16 wedges; shape pieces.
Roll and brush with butter.
Arrange on greased pans.
Cover and let rise until very light.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: mexican waistbasket soup (great lo-cal soup)
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot.
DO NOT DRAIN canned vegetables.
Simmer one hour; add water if needed.
Cube cheese and put in bottom of each bowl.
Top with soup.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and butter; add boiling water.
Bring to the boiling point; add sugar, then syrup, vanilla and salt.
Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables about 5 minutes. Drain.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Put in a 6 x 9-inch pan.
Place the onion rings over the top and bake about 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chow mein
directions: Cook meat about half hour.
Cut it in small bits.
Save juice for stock.
Saute meat in large boiler with 2 tablespoons butter or oleo.
Add celery and onions.
Let boil about 10 minutes after you pour in the stock.

title: cream cheese and chives mashed potatoes
directions: In medium saucepan, cook potatoes in 2 inches boiling water, covered, about 12 minutes until tender; drain thoroughly.
Mash potatoes with electric mixer or potato masher.
Mix in cheese until melted.
Mix in remaining ingredients (do not overbeat).
Stir gently over low heat just until heated through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: super krispy treats(adapted from rice krispies box)
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add marshmallows and, stirring frequently, cook over low heat until completely melted.
Remove from heat and add cereal.
Mix until well coated.
Quickly stir in chips.

title: sausage stuffing broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Meanwhile in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook sausage until brown.
Spoon off fat.
In a large bowl, combine cooked sausage, cooked broccoli, croutons and cheese.
Arrange mixture evenly in a greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
In the same bowl, stir soup until smooth.
Beat in eggs and milk.
Pour over sausage mixture, covering all ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes or until set in center.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving. Cut into squares to serve.
Serves 9.

title: microwave cabbage stuffed with beef
directions: Place the cabbage leaves in a microwave-safe dish.
Add water and microwave, covered, on High for 3 minutes. Rotate the dish and cook for an additional 3 minutes. Drain and set aside.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Put crescent roll dough on a cookie sheet, pressing seams together. Bake as directed.
Cool.

title: cherry pie
directions: Drain cherries, reserving juice (1 cup).
Mix cherries and 1/2 cup sugar and set aside.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and salt in a medium saucepan.
Stir until all lumps are dissolved; gradually add cherry juice.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thick.
Remove from heat and stir in cherries.
Add margarine and almond flavoring.
Pour into pie crust.
Cover with top crust.
You can butter top crust to make it brown better.
Cut slits in top crust.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Place in 350° oven for 7 minutes to partially thaw.
Stir in rice, chicken, soup, milk and half of cheese along with the onion.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cover and bake 45 minutes.
Uncover and continue to bake until browned.

title: apricot bread
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and egg. Mix other ingredients in order given. Pour into a greased bread pan. Let set 20 minutes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all together and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not cover.

title: wikiwiki walk away dessert
directions: Soften cream cheese and use mixer; gradually blend in 1/4 cup milk.
Add remaining milk and pineapple; beat 1 minute.
Chill; just before serving, spoon into ice cream cones.

title: old fashioned hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar.
Beat until light and foamy.
Add flour sifted with baking powder and salt.
Place butter and milk in saucepan and bring to boil.
Pour immediately over batter.
Add flavoring and mix well.
Grease and flour pan(s).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan, 20 to 25 minutes in 9-inch layer pans for 3 layers or 10 to 15 minutes in 9-inch layer pans for 6 layers.
Cool layers and then frost with favorite icing.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, eggs, buttermilk and oil together; beat 2 minutes.
In Bundt cake pan (greased and floured), sprinkle pecans and chocolate chips in bottom of pan (reserve some of the chocolate chips for top of cake).
Pour cake mix into pan.
Add rest of chocolate chips on top of cake mix.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rolls
directions: Mix together and bake.
Makes 6 rolls.

title: mushroom sauce
directions: Melt the butter in the saucepan and saute onion over low heat for 5 minutes.
Add the mushrooms.
Cover and let steam for another 5 minutes.
Stir in the flour and add the beef broth and sherry, stirring constantly.
Season with salt and pepper.
Simmer for 5 more minutes.
Remove from the heat and stir in the sour cream and parsley.
Serve with chicken.

title: crunchy rhubarb cake
