directions: Cream 1 1/2 cups sugar and shortening.
Add egg and beat.
Mix in next 5 ingredients.
Add rhubarb to batter; mix well.
Combine remaining 1/4 cup sugar with cinnamon for topping on batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, until golden brown. Bake longer if using frozen rhubarb.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix the gelatin in a bowl with 2 to 3 cups of boiling water until dissolved.
Pour into a lightly greased pizza pan with edges.
Place in the refrigerator and chill until firm.
Spread with the whipped cream and garnish with fruit.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain.
Saute chopped onion and celery in butter until onion looks clear.
Mix well with other ingredients. Pour into buttered 3 quart baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 10-15 minutes.

title: home remedy
directions: Mix well and drink one glass daily.
Makes one serving.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, sugar, apple (including peel) and orange (including peel) all together in grinder.
Refrigerate.

title: classic baked beans
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook bacon to crisp.
Drain.
Crumble bacon.
In 2-quart casserole dish, combine bacon, pork and beans, onion, ketchup, molasses, brown sugar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Bake, uncovered, 45 to 50 minutes or until thickened and bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: apple crumb
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Lightly butter a 9-inch square baking pan or a casserole of the equivalent size, then dust it with flour.
Peel, core and slice the apples and arrange them in the pan.
In the bowl of an electric mixer, blend the oats, brown sugar, flour, butter, cinnamon, salt and allspice on low speed until it forms a coarse meal.
Crumble the mixture evenly over the apple slices and sprinkle with the juice.
Bake for 35 minutes. Serves 6.

title: butterscotch delight cake
directions: Cook pudding with milk until it boils. Add to cake mix along with oil and mix well. Pour into slightly greased 9 X 13 pan. sprinkle chips and nuts over top and bake at 350 degrees for 35-40 minutes until done. Quick & Easy!

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl.
Roll into 3/4-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done (about 45 minutes).

title: rave review coconut cake
directions: Blend the first 5 ingredients and beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in coconut and walnuts.
Pour in 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pans 15 minutes before removing.

title: canned green beans
directions: Snap green beans small in size.
Wash green beans thoroughly. Wash jars in hot, soapy water, rinsing very well.
Fill jars with green beans, packing tightly.
Add 1 teaspoon plain salt.
Cover with hot water.
Use a rubber spatula to get out air bubbles. Place flats and lids on jars but don't screw on too tightly. Place jars in canner and process for 15 minutes on 15 pounds.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix well.
Turn biscuits onto a well floured surface.
Knead until dough is no longer sticky.
Roll out and cut.
Place in baking pan.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: hot chick salad casserole
directions: Mix all except butter, croutons and almonds.
Place in a casserole.
Melt butter; add croutons and almonds.
Toss.
Put over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat until smooth. Bake in a 350 degree oven about one hour in an angel cake tube pan.

title: angel cookies
directions: Mix together in order given. Roll in balls. Dip in water and then sugar. Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hello dolly cake
directions: Place each ingredients in 11 x 13-inch pan in order given. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Serve.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Steam broccoli until just tender; season and add all remaining ingredients.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: 4-layer dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Pat into oblong pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix next 3 ingredients and spread over bottom layer.
Spread pudding mix over cream cheese mixture. Spread remaining Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle finely chopped pecans on top.
You can use pie filling instead of pudding and last add Cool Whip.

title: chicken-leek soup
directions: Rinse chicken, then cut into bite size pieces.
Heat all ingredients, except leeks, in a Dutch oven or large kettle to boiling point.
Skim off any scum.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add leeks and cook 15 or more minutes, until barley is tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Add water if soup becomes thicker than desired.
Serves 6.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Combine first nine ingredients in large pot. Bring to a boil. Cover and reduce heat, simmer 15 - 20 minutes. Gradually stir 1/4 c. milk into flour to make a smooth paste. Stir paste into soup and add remaining milk and cheese. Cook over medium heat until thickened.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Stir in flour.
Cook over low heat, stirring until foamy.
Remove from heat; add mashed pumpkin, chicken broth, curry powder, salt, ginger, nutmeg and pepper. Return to heat.
Cook mixture, stirring with a fork until thick and smooth.
Combine egg yolks, lightly beating with sweet cream.
Add this mixture to hot mixture.
Bring soup to boiling point but do not boil.
Sprinkle soup with chopped parsley and serve.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Boil water and mix with jello.
Cool slightly.
Mix pie filling, blueberries and pecans; fold into jello.
Refrigerate for about 3 hours.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients; beat until smooth.
Spoon into greased shallow 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle topping over it.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and roll in small balls. Freeze. Cook, frozen, at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 20 minutes.
Drain.
Stir together the soup, mayonnaise, onions and cheese.
Add to the broccoli.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle with bread crumbs on top.
A few pats of margarine may be put on top of the crumbs.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in 350°
oven.

title: to make sweet pickles
directions: Drain brine off of pickles.
Add the sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Put this over pickles.
Add the alum to make crisp. Let stand overnight and will make own juice.
Makes delicious sweet pickles.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Stir up all ingredients and drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: simple beets salad
directions: In a large bowl, put together beets and garlic. Add enough mayonnaise to just coat beets and garlic. Season with salt and pepper. Add almonds and toss until well mixed. Chill before serving. Serves 6 to 8.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello.
Let cool until it is partially jelled.
Add grated cream cheese.
Mix in pineapple and Cool Whip.
Mix with a mixer. Chill until set.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Sprinkle a little nutmeg and cinnamon on top.

title: lemon basil tea loaf
directions: Cream butter and 1 cup of the sugar.
Add milk, eggs, lemon extract and lemon rind.
Add combined dry ingredients; pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: In double boiler, cook sugar, boiling water and salt until thick.
Add lemon juice, cornstarch, butter and yolks.
Pour into baked pie crust.

title: date cake with choco-nut topping
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a pan.

title: seven layered salad
directions: Prepare salad in large bowl.
Add ingredients, one at a time as given, each in a separate layer.
Do not toss.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.
Will keep one or two days.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook meat until done.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Next morning, remove all the grease and tear apart.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Add meat and cook in sauce until done.

title: ham and cheese omelet
directions: Butter bread on one side. Place 6 slices buttered side down on a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle ham and cheese on top. Put top layer of 6 slices bread buttered side up. Pour over top the beaten eggs, milk and mustard all beaten together. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 325°, covered, for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake 45 minutes longer.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes; cool and dice.
Mix onion, mayonnaise and cheeses.
Put potatoes in 9 x 13-inch pan; top with cheese mixture.
Sprinkle olives and bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: skillet ranch chicken
directions: Heat iron skillet and melt butter. Put Ranch dressing in a bowl and dip chicken. Place chicken in medium hot skillet and brown both sides. Super with wild rice.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Lightly brown ground beef in a small amount of oil; drain off excess fat.
Combine all ingredients in a large pot.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour or more.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cut carrots and slightly cook (crisp) in salted water; drain. Mix carrots and all other ingredients together.
Marinate at least 24 hours.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a roaster.
Lay chicken pieces on top of the mixture.
No seasoning needed.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Don't open roaster while baking.

title: sweet potato dump cake
directions: Mix together extract, sugar and potatoes.
Place orange slices in bottom of baking dish.
Spread potatoes over slices. Pour a box of yellow cake mix over potatoes.
Melt margarine or oleo.
Drizzle all over cake mix, then put pecan halves over mix and bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes or until cake is done.

title: ma's pickled beets
directions: Pour off
the liquid from the beets.
Add Sweet 'N Low, a little black pepper and cover with vinegar.

title: sesame seasoned salt
directions: Toast sesame seed in large skillet, stirring about 5 minutes until light brown.
Add salt; stir 5 minutes longer.
Cool.
Place seed and remaining items in blender for about 1 minute, until pulverized.
Use for salads, dressings, cottage cheese, cooked vegetables and meats.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and 1 1/2 cups of sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Mix and shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons of sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: white trash
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Add next 4 ingredients. Mix together.
Place in a grocery bag with powdered sugar and shake vigorously.
Delicious!

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Mix instant pudding by directions and add 2/3 container of Cool Whip.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs and oil.
Add sugars.
Stir in zucchini.
In another bowl, mix flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and pecans.
Add to first mixture.
Put into greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel and quarter apples into 20 pieces. Roll each biscuit out and cut in half. Wrap each piece of apple with dough and lay in baking dish that has been greased. Bring other ingredients to a boil and pour over the apples. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and egg yolks.
Add syrup, vanilla and pecans; stir well.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour mixtures into unbaked pastry shell and bake slowly at 325° for 1 hour, until custard like in consistency.

title: italian bread
directions: Remove skin from sausage links and brown in oil.
Chop Mozzarella and Muenster cheeses into 1/4-inch chunks.
Beat eggs and add cheeses and sausage.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan (glass if you have it) with 1/2 of crescent rolls over bottom and up the sides like a pie.
Pour mixture on top.
Cover with rest of the rolls. Brush a beaten egg over the top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Don't separate the rolls, just sort of pat them in and on the casserole.

title: egg bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and beat. Add cooled butter and beat. Add yeast dissolved in 1 cup warm water.
Add flavoring and orange peel.
Add flour, one cup at a time.
Knead. Cover and let rise until double in size.
Bake at 325° on third shelf until golden in color, about 25 minutes.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts until fully cooked.
Shred into small pieces into a 2-quart casserole.
Thoroughly mix soup and sour cream.
Combine with shredded chicken in casserole.
Finely crush all of the crackers and sprinkle over sour cream chicken mixture. Melt stick of butter and drizzle over casserole.
Generously cover casserole with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion and carrots in oil.
Add bouillon and water.
Cook until cubes are dissolved, about 15 minutes.
Add raw noodles. Add chopped broccoli.
Add salt.
Bring to slow boil.
Add garlic. Before serving, add milk and Velveeta.
Cook until cheese melts.

title: dripped beef
directions: Place seasoned roast in roasting pan.
Add water and bouillon cubes.
Cover and cook at 200° to 250°, 10 to 12 hours.

title: applesauce cake with fruit
directions: Heat applesauce, shortening, soda, salt, spices and sugar. Put flour on raisins and dates; stir.
Stir applesauce mixture and fruit into floured mixture.
Pour into prepared baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: russian wafers
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and add flour and 1 1/2 cups finely chopped pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on a cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm; these are very rich and have to be handled carefully.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10 x 4-inch angel cake tube pan.
Preheat oven to slow 325°.

title: devil's food pudding
directions: Mix water and sugar and boil until sugar has all dissolved. Pour solution into very large Pyrex dish.
Mix cake, add nuts, and pour into dish on top of sugar solution.
Bake about 35 minutes. Serve with whipped cream.

title: turkey divan
directions: In a
flat Pyrex dish put a layer of broccoli and then a layer of turkey.
Prepare sauce by mixing remaining ingredients.
Pour sauce over broccoli and turkey.
Top with bread crumbs and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
This can be made ahead of time and heated.

title: indiana basket party cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix next 3 ingredients together and pour on top of cake layer.
Sprinkle nuts on top of all.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
When cool, dust with confectioners sugar.

title: rolo cookies
directions: Prepare cookie mix according to directions.
Roll a tablespoon of cookie dough around 1 Rolo candy.
Roll in nuts or powdered sugar.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake!
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Melt Jell-O in 2 cups water (hot).
Add cranberry sauce; mash up with hands.
Put 1/2 in a 6 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Let jell in refrigerator.
When completely jelled, spread sour cream over the jelled cranberry mixture.
Add the remainder of the unjelled.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: irish coffee
directions: Fill cup
with
hot,
strong coffee and brown sugar and stir well.
Add whiskey.
Balance spoon on top of this and add 1/2 inch of
cream
by
pouring on spoon.
Enjoy!

title: lime punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar, pineapple and enough water to make 1 gallon. Chill.
Mix punch with ginger ale before serving.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Add water.
Add pumpkin; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Makes 3 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add to well beaten eggs and pineapple.
Add marshmallows.
Cut 7 to 8 slices bread into small cubes.
Melt 1/4 pound butter or margarine in large frying pan and add bread.
Stir until saturated, then put bread mixture on top of pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour until bread is toasted.
Good with ham, turkey or chicken.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water; let set in refrigerator until it starts to congeal.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add pecans. Mix in pineapple and Cool Whip.
Spread evenly in container; refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: aunt gen's sweet potato pie
directions: Drain potatoes; mash slightly.
Cream with sugar, butter and spices.
When smooth, add eggs and milk.
(Mix will be soupy.) Pour in prepared pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Serve hot or at room temperature with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: true sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick.
Add water and continue beating. Gradually add sugar and both extracts.
Sift salt and flour.
Fold 1/4 of flour mixture over the eggs.
Use 10 strokes to fold in rest of flour by "fourths."
Beat egg whites to foamy stage.
Add cream of tartar, then sugar gradually.
Beat until peaks form and bend over!
Fold yolk and white mixtures until completely blended. Do this quickly to avoid excessive air loss and damage to texture.

title: some more's(delicious)
directions: Heat corn syrup and sugar until melted.
Add remaining ingredients except Hershey bars; mix together.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put Hershey bars on top.
Put in oven until melted.
Spread evenly over top of mixture.

title: rhubarb pies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in an unbaked pie crust until golden brown (about 30 to 40 minutes) at 350°.
(Top crust is excellent with this pie; sprinkle with sugar and milk.)

title: pasta salad - fat-free
directions: Prepare rotolini per package instructions.
Rinse in cold water and set aside.
Combine tomatoes, cucumbers, onion, peas and salad dressing in large Tupperware bowl.
Add one-half bottle of dry salad seasoning and mix well.
Stir in black olives. Refrigerate overnight and stir well prior to serving.
Extra dressing may be added if needed.

title: party fruit punch
directions: Thaw frozen ingredients; mix and freeze.
Set out of freezer 30 minutes before serving.
Pour ginger ale over punch and serve.

title: peach barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients except the peach filling and bring to a full boil.
Add the filling and place into a glass jar to store in cooler.

title: rice and pepper soup
directions: In Microwave:
Heat olive oil in a heavy soup pot that is heat resistant.
Add onion, carrots and garlic.
Saute, covered, over low heat until vegetables are tender and lightly colored, about 10 minutes; stir occasionally.
Uncover and add chicken broth. Increase heat to boiling.
Reduce, cover and simmer in microwave for about 15 minutes.
Add rice, bell peppers and seasonings to taste.
Simmer, partially uncovered, for about 20 minutes, or until rice is tender.
Serves 4.

title: zesty taco salad
directions: Combine oil and garlic in small bowl, let stand 1 hour at room temperature.

title: chicken continental
directions: Saute chicken, mushroom (stems and pieces) and garlic in oil. Add remaining ingredients. Add rice last.
Simmer and serve.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, sugar, cocoa and salt.
Blend together water and mayonnaise.
Mix liquid into dry ingredients gradually, beating until smooth.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well, cover and chill overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: brandy alexanders
directions: Combine in blender and blend (ice cream should be firm, but not rock solid).
One ounce liquor for 1 serving.
You can make about 4 servings in 1 blender.
Top with nutmeg after mixture has been poured in glasses.
Nice for Christmas Eve, or holidays.

title: chicken tonight
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Pepper chicken and brown in butter. Mix sour cream, milk and soup mix together and pour over chicken. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove lid and top with noodles.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes more.
Serve hot.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in a large baking pan. Mix in 3/4 pound butter (melted). Add the red pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Sprinkle celery salt and garlic salt over mix. Cover and bake at 250° for 1 hour. Stir every 20 minutes. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes longer. Stir after 15 minutes.
Mix in 2 cups nuts.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook brown sugar, evaporated milk and salt until mixture forms soft balls.
Remove from fire.
Stir in vanilla and peanut butter; stir until stiff.
Pour into pan or drop by spoonful onto wax paper.
Cool and serve.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix together lemon Jell-O, water and 7-Up.
Set it partly.
Add drained pineapple, marshmallows and bananas.
Chill.
In separate bowl, mix together sugar, flour, 1 cup of the pineapple juice and egg.
Cook until thick.
Chill.
Fold in packet of Dream Whip.
Put over top of set Jell-O mixture.
Chill.

title: quick apple crisp
directions: Peel and cut up apples.
Put pieces in a 9 x 9-inch pan or a pie pan.
Put salt, flour, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg in a bowl. Pour melted butter in the bowl and mix with a fork.
Spoon mixture over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve in small dessert dishes.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Sprinkle a little nutmeg
over top.
Add 1/2 cup water, or slightly less.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes or until most of the liquid is gone.

title: peach bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In one bowl, mix flour, sugars, salt and baking soda.
Drain mashed peaches; put in a large bowl.
Add beaten egg and melted margarine.
Stir in raisins or nuts; stir in flour mixture.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch greased and floured loaf pan. Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes; remove. Cool bread in pan for 15 minutes; remove and finish cooling on wire rack (okay to freeze next day).

title: supreme baked corn
directions: Mix well and pour in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with 1 cup shredded cheese.
Bake for an additional 25 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and eggs. Sift flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Mix until well blended.
Chill. Form into balls the size of walnuts. Roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip mint cake
directions: Pour extract over chocolate chips.
Let set while batter is being prepared.
Blend other ingredients except chocolate chips. Fold drained chips in by hand.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Add others together, then heat enough to dissolve sugar, then pour over cooked carrots, onion and green pepper.
Refrigerate.
Will keep 3 to 4 weeks.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water (as directed on box) and cool.
Add mayonnaise.
Break up corned beef and add to mixture.
Then add celery, green pepper and onion flakes.
Chop boiled eggs fine. Mix together.
Put in mold or large bowl.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off tops of green peppers; remove seeds.
Mix raw beef, chopped onion, uncooked rice, salt, pepper, garlic, 1/2 can of soup, egg and water.
Arrange peppers snugly in 3-quart casserole. Stuff with mixture; top with remaining soup.
Cover.

title: "beary" good snack mix
directions: Mix together in a large bowl.
Store in a plastic bag or covered container airtight.
Have fun!!

title: ham, cheese and potato quiche
directions: After cooking the noodles, butter a casserole dish.
Combine all ingredients well.
Cover with plastic wrap and let melt overnight in the refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a knife inserted comes out clean.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Toast pecans on baking sheet at 300° for 8 minutes. Mix sugar, cinnamon, salt and 5 tablespoons water in saucepan.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and pecans. Stir until mixture cools.
Spread on waxed paper. Separate pecans.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Add sugar and egg. Put the melted butter in a cup; add enough orange juice to make 3/4 cup total and add.
Add cranberries and nuts.

title: hamburg stuffing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix together.
Add to saucepan and cook slowly over low heat until meat is browned.
Add to turkey or serve as is.

title: beefy casserole
directions: Brown ground meat, onion and seasonings.
Drain.
Add cream cheese until melted.
Add corn and soup.
Cook macaroni and drain. Add to soup mixture.
Place in casserole dish and bake until hot at 350°.

title: pralines
directions: Mix brown sugar, granulated sugar, Karo syrup and milk in heavy saucepan.
Cook to boiling point, stirring constantly.
Cook until soft ball forms in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Cool at room temperature until lukewarm, without stirring.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Stir until candy holds shape.
Drop onto waxed paper to form patties.

title: tom cruise cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan according to package directions.
While cake is still warm, poke 15 to 20 holes in cake with the handle of a large wooden spoon.
Let cool slightly.
Pour sweetened condensed milk and topping into holes.
(This takes a while; you have to wait until it soaks in before you can pour all of the topping and milk in.)
Let stand a few minutes, then spread Cool Whip over the top.
Sprinkle with crushed Heath bars or Heath Sensations.
Serves 12 to 16.
Best kept in the refrigerator until serving.

title: easy pizza cups
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Stir in tomato paste, onion and seasonings (mixture will be thick).
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Press biscuits with hand or roll to cover bottom and sides of greased muffin tin.
Spoon about 1/4 cup of meat mixture into biscuit-lined cups and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes, or until golden brown.
Yields 12 little pizzas, just the right size for kids or parties.
Also can make toppings using pepperoni, olives, mushrooms or to your liking.

title: pineapple strip pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Roll out half and line cookie sheet.
Reserve half for top.
Mix pineapple, sugar, tapioca and lemon juice together.
Spread on dough.
Roll out; reserve half and cut into strips for top crust.
Bake until light brown; cool.

title: skillet chicken with wine
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, slice onions. Cut potatoes into 2-inch chunks. Remove skin and fat from chicken thighs. In nonstick 12-inch skillet over high heat, in hot olive or salad oil, cook chicken thighs until browned on both sides. Add onions, potatoes, chicken broth, white wine, thyme, black pepper and olives; over high heat, heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer about 20 minutes or until juices run clear when chicken is pierced with a knife and vegetables are tender. Stir in spinach; cook 1 to 2 minutes until spinach just wilts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Combine Wesson oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Now, add flour, soda and salt.
Stir in buttermilk.
Add bananas and nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fish fillets with horseradish sauce
directions: Clean fish with damp towel.
Put into baking dish.
Mix mayonnaise, horseradish and lemon juice.
Spread on fillets and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 12 minutes in a 425° oven.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add eggs with oil and water; beat.
Stir in pumpkin.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Makes two loaves.
Enjoy!

title: peanut clusters
directions: Pour morsels in microwaveable bowl.
Heat in microwave about 5 minutes on Medium to High heat, until melted.
Remove from microwave and pour in peanuts.
Mix well and drop onto waxed paper by teaspoonful.
Let stand for about 3 hours.
Refrigerate. Clusters may be frozen for later use.

title: hot taco rice
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Add salsa, tomato sauce and bouillon cubes and bring to a full boil.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 5 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Place cream cheese into an approximately 10 x 10-inch casserole dish.
Soften in microwave for 1 minute or so.
Take out of microwave and spread evenly all around.
Pour jar of salsa on top of cream cheese and spread evenly, then spread 6 to 8 ounces of the shredded cheeses on top of salsa.
Cook in microwave for 7 minutes or until shredded cheese is completely melted.
Enjoy!

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: You will need 1 baking sheet.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix together sugar, cornstarch and water. Cook 1 minute over medium heat. Remove from heat; add lemon juice and margarine and mix well.

title: mom's tender spareribs
directions: Pour bottle of barbecue sauce in electric skillet. Fill bottle with water, shake and add to barbecue sauce in skillet.
Mix well with fork and place spareribs in skillet.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients (by hand).
Form into a ball, then roll the ball in chopped pecans until covered.
Chill overnight before serving.
Wrap in Saran Wrap before chilling.

title: spicy pecans
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients until brown sugar melts. Remove from heat; add pecans and stir thoroughly to coat. Transfer to a cookie sheet. Heat in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until toasted. Cool and store in an airtight container.

title: hash browns
directions: Chill cooked in jacket potatoes, peel and shred to make 4 cups.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Melt butter or drippings in 10-inch skillet.
Pat potatoes into pan, leaving 1/2-inch space around edges.
Brown 10 to 12 minutes on each side until golden brown.

title: chilled cucumber soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine in saucepan until tender.
Blend in flour and salt; stir in milk and cream gradually.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Combine cream sauce and cucumbers in blender container.
Process until smooth.
Chill thoroughly. Serve in chilled bowls.
Set in ice.
Garnish with thinly sliced, unpeeled cucumber.
Yields 6 servings.

title: festive apples
directions: Peel, core and cut in half the apples.
Place in baking dish. Spray with Pam.
Fill each cavity with brown sugar and a tab of butter.
Sprinkle lightly over all.
Add a little water.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Transfer apples to serving platter; reserve all juices and pour into saucepan.
Mix cornstarch with a little water and add to saucepan, stirring until creamy smooth over medium heat.
Add a touch of red food coloring and mix well. Pour over apples and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: veal chops with basil
directions: Dredge chops lightly with flour.
In a large skillet, brown chops.
Remove them and set aside.

title: fruit candy bars
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over water; allow to soften for 5 minutes. Heat and stir until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Combine apricots, raisins, pecans, flour and orange peel in blender or food processor, working until finely chopped.
Add to gelatin mixture.
Add rum extract and stir to completely blend.
Line 8-inch (20 ml) square pan with plastic wrap or waxed paper. Spread fruit mixture evenly into pan and set aside to cool completely until candy is firm.
Turn out onto cutting board, cut into 24 bars and wrap individually.
Yield: 24 bars.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup soup, raw hamburger, onion, egg, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Press into pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cream potatoes and place on top of meat.
Top with remaining soup and cheese.
Sprinkle top with real bacon bits. Bake 10 minutes.

title: skiers french toast
directions: In a sauce pan heat syrup, butter and sugar until syrupy. Pour into a 9 x 13 pan. Lay bread slices on top of syrup. Beat eggs, milk, vanilla and salt, pour over bread. Cover and put in refrigerator overnight. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Reserve 1/3 cup pizza sauce for topping.
Combine remaining sauce with seasonings, pepper, corn flake crumbs and egg.
Add beef, shape into loaf in shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes.
Brush on 1/2 of remaining sauce.
Bake 20 minutes more. Brush on remaining sauce and sprinkle on cheese.
Bake 10 more minutes or until done.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Add all ingredients, mixing well after each.
Bake 25 minutes at 400° in preheated oven.
Add topping and bake 10 more minutes, until topping is golden brown.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Grate carrots.
Chop onions and bell peppers. Mix all together.
Bring to a boil oil, vinegar, sugar and salt. Pour over cabbage, onions, peppers and carrots.
Let chill for 8 to 10 hours.

title: pauline's special salad
directions: In Dutch oven put pineapple with juice.
Sprinkle in orange jello.
Heat until it reaches a full boil.
Stir constantly.
Turn off heat and cool completely.
Add buttermilk and stir.
Add Cool Whip and stir.
Combine nuts and marshmallows.
Pour into large rectangular pan and chill completely before serving.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in mixing bowl and beat for 20 minutes, set on high speed
Add walnuts after mixing.
Pour into a tube pan, greased and floured.
Place tube pan in cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes until done.

title: sugar pie
directions: Put sugar in crust and add flour and salt.
Mix it a little with your fingers.
Add vanilla to milk and pour over the sugar and flour without stirring.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°, then at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt.
Cook 4 minutes on High. Remove and stir and cook 4 more minutes.
Add butter and vanilla and cook 2 minutes on High.
Add soda and pour out on a greased baking sheet.
If you use roasted salted nuts, omit salt and add peanuts after first 4 minutes of cooking.

title: italian chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken (cubed) and 1/2 cup Italian dressing in large glass baking dish. Cook at 350° for 20 minutes. Add chicken broth, seasoning, rice and frozen veggies. Add rice first. Cook for approximately 40 minutes at 350° or until rice is done and casserole is not too soupy.

title: beet jelly
directions: Cook beets, enough for 6 cups juice. Stir together in large kettle the beet juice, lemon juice and Sure-Jell. Bring to a boil; stir constantly. Boil 1 minute. Add sugar and Jell-O. Cook for 6 minutes or to soft ball. Pour in jars and seal.

title: mississippi pound cake
directions: Mix salt with flour.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour, a little at a time, mixing well.
Add flavoring.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Coat carrots, nuts and raisins with flour.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
This will make 3 large loaves.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk.
Add cherries. Cook on low heat until thick.
Add vanilla.
Refrigerate.

title: kandace's chili
directions: Brown the hamburger meat, chili meat and onion, drain. Combine with the remaining ingredients in a large stock pot and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: baked custard
directions: Combine eggs, salt and sugar.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.
Pour into custard cups.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Place in pan of hot water and bake at 350 degrees for 30 - 35 minutes or until knife can cut center.
For large mold bake for 40 - 45 minutes.

title: santa's tangy punch
directions: Mix Tang, sugar, water, cranberry juice and almond extract; freeze until mushy. Add ginger ale just before serving. Tang mixture may be frozen ahead of time, then thawed to a mush. Yields 30 punch cups.

title: shrimp bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in order listed.
Serve on crisp lettuce leaf with small amount of salad dressing.
Yields 4 servings.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar and stir in eggs, one at a time. Add milk, vanilla and cocoa.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour in a 9-inch pie crust and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well.
Bake in oblong dish or pan at 300°.
Watch closely; it burns easily.
Let brown lightly and cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cover with Pepperidge Farm stuffing.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms.
Remove
stems and tops.
Cook stuffing according to directions.
Mince
crabmeat.
Mix
into stuffing. Stuff mixture into mushrooms.
Dip
into melted butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated throughout.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.

title: taco salad cups
directions: Crumb vegeburger into mixing bowl or casserole dish.
Cover tightly and microwave at High for 3 to 5 minutes (may need to add a little oil to dish).
Stir in barbecue sauce, onion and sugar; set aside.

title: layer salad
directions: Drain cans well.
Arrange the first five ingredients in layers.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Let stand overnight.
Next day, drain well.
Add Hellmann's mayonnaise.

title: brownie chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan. Make brownie mix as package indicates.
Bake 35 minutes until set. In large bowl, beat cheese, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in chips.
(If mini chips unavailable, chop regular chips in food processor.) Reduce oven temperature to 300°.
Pour batter over baked brownies. Bake 50 minutes or until center is set.
Cool, then chill thoroughly.
Remove from pan, cheese side up.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl; add eggs and salad oil stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup nuts and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place half of bread cubes in a greased casserole.
Then add chicken and seasoning.
Place remaining bread cubes on top.
Beat eggs.
Add milk and broth.
Pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla.
Boil 3 minutes.
Let cool 20 minutes.
Add vanilla and beat until thick enough to stay on cake (about 2 minutes).

title: chicken thighs parmigiana
directions: Wash chicken, drain and dry well.
In large skillet, saute thighs in hot butter, skin side down, for 5 minutes or until golden.
Add onion and garlic.
Cover and saute 5 minutes.
Push chicken to one side.
Add spinach.
Sprinkle with salt and basil. Simmer covered for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook spaghetti as directed; drain.
Turn chicken right side up.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Blend spinach with onion and butter.
Simmer covered 10 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve on spaghetti.

title: granola cereal
directions: Mix oatmeal with orange juice.
Broil on a cookie sheet until brown, stirring often.
Cool.
Combine all ingredients. Store in airtight container.
Serve dry with milk.

title: smoked salmon dip(low-fat and low-cholesterol)
directions: Combine cheeses, yogurt and hot sauce in food processor and process until smooth.
Fold in the smoked salmon. A teaspoon or more skim milk can always be used to thin the cheese if necessary. This can be a vegetable or cracker dip.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery.
Layer ingredients (first 10) with sharp Cheddar cheese on top.
Put one can of Ro-Tel tomatoes on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until creamy. Add sugar, flour, melted butter and milk; blend thoroughly.
Fold in raspberries.
Pour raspberry filling into pie crust.
Bake at 325° until filling is thick. Remove from oven.
Let cool.
Chill in refrigerator. Serve, topped with sweetened whipped cream.

title: breakfast souffle(serves 8)
directions: Grease a 4-quart pan (13 x 9-inch) or a foil pan (13 x 9-inch).
Add bread, sausage (cut up) and cheese.
Add milk and soup to beaten eggs.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Add green peppers and pimentos (optional).
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.

title: ann's awesome potatoes
directions: Mix hash browns, cheese, melted butter, onions, soup, salt and sour cream.
Mix well. Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika to serve, if desired.

title: pudding cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix together all ingredients.
Roll the batter into balls and place on ungreased, nonstick cookie sheet(s) 2 inches apart.
Flatten the cookies with a fork and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake for 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat thoroughly. Combine flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Gradually blend dry ingredients into cream mixture.
Chill dough.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Mix cinnamon and sugar; roll balls in mix. Place 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cookies will puff up at first, then flatten out with crinkled tops.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: waybury hot fruit compote
directions: Preheat the oven to 250°.
Combine prunes, pears, peaches and pineapple with applesauce.
Arrange in a casserole.
Add cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg, lemon juice and rind.
Cover the casserole and place in the oven.
Bake for at least one hour.
The longer it bakes the better it is.
Serve as a complement to meat or fowl.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine.
Mix all ingredients in casserole.
Top with grated cheese and bake until cheese is melted.

title: face paint
directions: Stir together in an empty yogurt container.
Make several batches using different colors.
Paint designs on face with a small paint brush or sponge.
Remove with soap and water.
The paint may be stored in tightly closed container.

title: layered salad
directions: Tear lettuce into small pieces and place in dish.
Layer rest of ingredients in order given.
Mix sugar in mayonnaise and spread over salad as frosting.
Top with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: whipped cream cake
directions: Grease a 9-inch square pan, unless Teflon.
Line bottom with wax paper and grease paper.
Preheat oven to 325°.

title: something special casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni dinner as directed on package.
Add corn (drained), tomatoes, parsley and soup mix.
Put half of macaroni and cheese dinner in bottom of well-greased dish, using 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add 1/2 meat cubes, then remaining cheese mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350° and serve hot.

title: tara's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, Crisco, brown sugar and sugar.
Mix eggs and vanilla together; add to creamed mixture.
Mix oatmeal, chocolate chips or raisins and pecans together; add to other. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: wheat germ muffins
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients.
Mix together all wet ingredients and add to dry.
Beat well.
May add dates, raisins or nuts.
Fill muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and softened butter in a 9-inch pie plate.
Distribute mixture evenly, pressing onto bottom and sides of plate.
Bake crust 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: mmmm chicken pot pie
directions: Mix quickly; roll with floured pin.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Combine all ingredients except pineapple.
Stir well.
Cook over medium heat, uncovered, 15 to 30 minutes or until cranberry skins pop.
Stir in pineapple tidbits.
Reduce heat.
Cook an additional 30 to 45 minutes, stirring often.
Yield:
3 pints. Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: green chile quiche
directions: Beat together in blender the eggs, cottage cheese, baking powder, Tabasco and flour.
Add cheese, green chilies and butter to mixture.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 25 to 30 miutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: chicken breast diane
directions: Place chicken breasts between sheets of waxed paper or plastic wrap.
Pound slightly with mallet.
Season with salt and pepper. Heat 1 tablespoon each of oil and butter in skillet.
Cook chicken over high heat for 4 minutes on each side.
Transfer to warm serving platter.
Add chives or onions and lime or lemon juice, parsley and mustard to pan.
Cook 15 seconds, stirring constantly. Whisk in broth.
Stir until sauce is smooth.
Add remaining butter and oil.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Serve immediately.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until almost set, about 20 minutes.
Test with a toothpick.
Do not overbake.

title: lemon curd
directions: Melt margarine and sugar.
Add juice and grated rinds of lemons.
Add well-beaten eggs.
Stir over a low heat until it thickens.
Pour into warmed clean jars.
Cover and label.

title: mint chocolate squares
directions: Mix 1 stick of margarine, sugar, eggs, chocolate syrup, flour and salt.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool.

title: stuffed bread
directions: Split loaf of bread lengthwise.
(Can use 2 hoagie buns.) Cut or scoop out bread from center of each piece. Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread and fill in scooped out cavities of both pieces.
Place together and wrap tightly with plastic wrap. Refrigerate 4 to 8 hours.
Slice 1/2-inch thick and place on serving plate.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: japanese grilled chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
In a bowl, combine all other ingredients.
Add chicken and mix well.
Let stand 30 minutes or longer.
Thread on skewers and grill or boil for 2 to 3 minutes on each side until well browned.
Do not overcook.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole.

title: oriental ribs
directions: Mix all ingredients together in pan and add ribs (cut into pieces).
Add water to cover.
Heat to boiling and cook for about an hour until done.
Thicken sauce with flour and serve with rice.

title: strawberry fruit dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and marshmallow cream until smooth and creamy.
Slice fresh fruit, dipping into juice to keep from turning brown.

title: aunt mick's angel kisses
directions: Boil dates, brown sugar and butter for 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Roll into bite size balls.
Then roll them in powdered sugar.

title: picante sauce
directions: In a large kettle, mix and bring all ingredients to a boil. Turn to a simmer and cook until reaches desired thickness. Taste; if not hot enough, add more jalapeno peppers.
Place in hot pint jars and seal.
Hot water bath for 10 minutes.
Makes 14 to 15 pints.

title: quick caramel icing
directions: Cook butter and brown sugar over low heat for 2 minutes.
Add milk; bring to a boil.
Cool until warm, then add sugar to make frosting of consistency to spread.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine; add the broccoli, cheese, mushroom soup, water, Minute rice and water chestnuts.
Put into greased casserole and bake at 350° at least 40 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in tightly covered container.
Put in refrigerator and chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: old-fashioned potato salad(makes 6 servings)
directions: Several hours ahead, combine all ingredients; refrigerate.

title: crescent chicken casserole
directions: Mix cubed chicken and 1/4 of the cheese.
Put chicken in crescent rolls and roll up.
Place in casserole dish.
Heat soup, half of the cheese and milk in saucepan until melted.
Pour over chicken rolls.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cover top with remaining cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Mix the first 5 ingredients together to make the topping.
Press the biscuits thin on ungreased sheet or tray.
You can spray oil if you like, then scoop the topping on the biscuits and press them lightly.
Bake the biscuits in the oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until the cheese melts and the biscuits become light brown.
Remove from the oven.
Cool for 2 to 5 minutes and eat in good health.
Makes a good snack for kids.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix juices and water in punch bowl. Add ice cubes.
Pour in ginger ale. Garnish with lime slices.
Makes 60 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: turkey-tortilla casserole
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, heat the oil over medium heat. Saute onion and garlic about 5 minutes.
Add turkey, chili powder, cumin, cayenne, oregano and vinegar.
Cook until the turkey is no longer pink.
Stir in the black beans and remove from heat.

title: eggplant roast
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into slices.
Cook in small amount of salted water.
Mash and add to remaining ingredients.
Mix well and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine in medium size bowl the first 3 ingredients.
Mix well.
Press mixture into the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes or until lightly toasted.
Remove to a wire rack and cool completely.
Beat together the cream cheese and 10x sugar in a large bowl.
Fold in the Cool Whip and miniature marshmallows.
Spread mixture with a spatula over the crust in an even layer.
Bring water to boiling in medium pan.
Add jello and stir to dissolve.
Add strawberries and pour over second layer.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: strawberry bread
directions: *Can use 1 cup if less sweetness desired.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Chill 1 hour (optional).
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Great dough for rolling, cutting or sculpting coils, flattened balls, etc.

title: chicken enchilada pie
directions: Combine soups, green chilies and spices with chicken broth. (You may need additional broth to get desired consistency.)
Blend well.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from caps and rinse with cold water.
Marinate caps in soy sauce for 2 hours.
Combine remaining ingredients, including the chopped stems of the mushrooms.
Drain the caps. Use teaspoon to fill each cap with meat mixture.
Mound filling 1/2-inch high.
Brush top of each with soy sauce.
Broil 8 to 10 minutes, then bake at 350° for 8 to 10 additional minutes.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast in water and let dissolve.
Add oleo, sugar, egg and flour.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Put in an airtight container and store in refrigerator.
Fill muffin pans 1/2 full. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken chili
directions: In stockpot with cover, cook onions in olive oil over medium heat until pale golden (about 10 minutes).
Add garlic, chili powder, cumin, oregano and cayenne pepper.
Cook, stirring, 2 minutes.
Do not let burn.
Stir in chicken broth, tomatoes, beer, sugar, salt and bay leaf.
Bring to boil; simmer, partially covered, 40 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
(Can be made up to 2 days ahead, then refrigerate.
Bring gently to simmer before continuing.)
Slowly dust cornmeal into liquid without forming lumps, then add with chicken and zucchini; simmer for 30 minutes. Add beans and corn; simmer 5 minutes more.
Serve with mini muffins.

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour juice from fruits
(drain
well)
into a saucepan. Mix pudding mix and Tang;
add
to juice and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add cherries, pineapple and oranges; mix.
Chill before serving.
Will keep several days.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs until creamy. Add sugar slowly and beat after each addition. Add oil and beat again. Now add slowly the sifted dry ingredients. Lastly fold in apples and nuts. Bake in 350° oven until done, about 45 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: fudge
directions: Place sugar, margarine and canned milk in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil mixture at medium heat for 6 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Take off heat.
Stir in chocolate chips, peanut butter, marshmallows and vanilla.
Continue to stir until all marshmallows are melted.
Place in buttered pan and allow to cool.
Cut in 1-inch pieces.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops from peppers; discard seeds and membranes.
Cook whole peppers and tops in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Invert to drain well; save water.
Sprinkle inside of peppers lightly with salt. In skillet, cook meat and onion until meat is browned and onion tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Add tomatoes, uncooked rice, salt, Worcestershire sauce, bouillon cube and pepper.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir in cheese, if desired.
Stuff peppers with meat mixture.
Place in baking dish.
Add 2 tablespoons pepper water to each pepper and put tops back on.
Add a little of the water around the peppers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve the sugar in the water.
Add all of the other ingredients.
Then add ice.
Serves approximately 25 (6 ounce glasses).

title: toll house cheesecake
directions: Follow Toll House recipe on back of package.
Put 1/2 in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Put on top of mixture in pan, then take the other half of the dough, put on top.
(You will have 3 layers.)
You can put chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Beat eggs well in a large mixing bowl.
Add milk, sugar, salt, baking soda and vanilla.
Warm shortening and add it into the bowl with other mixture and beat well, then begin to add the flour to make a very stiff dough.

title: salami soup
directions: Saute onion, celery and carrots in butter for about 5 to 7 minutes.
Add salami and continue to saute for another 5 minutes. Add cabbage to mixture and saute 5 minutes more.
Add chicken broth to pot and simmer for 1 hour.

title: chewy caramel turtles
directions: First, butter some wax paper and let set.
Unpeel caramels; take one pan of water about 1/2 full, then take a smaller pan and put it in the water and then put on stove and heat about low-medium temperature.
Put caramels in the pan.
Let melt slowly and then stir in 3 tablespoons butter and cook until melted.
Once melted, stir in 1 bag of pecans and then drop by teaspoonfuls onto buttered wax paper.
Let harden.
Then with two more pans, melt chocolate and dip turtles in and put on wax paper.
Let harden, then serve.

title: dirt cake
directions: Finely crumble Oreo cookies; set aside, then cream together margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix together milk, French vanilla instant pudding and Cool Whip, then blend together the margarine and pudding mixtures.
Firmly press 1 inch cookies into bottom of flower pot; add pudding and margarine mixture. Continue to layer with a layer of cookies on top.
Add flowers and gummy worms and serve with a shovel.

title: mississippi cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour mix into a 9 X 11 baking dish or pan that has been sprayed. Bake at 400° until brown. (Slightly brown on top and sides. Test.)

title: peppered parmesan pull apart bread
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Dip each roll into butter mixture.
Arrange in a well greased bundt pan.
Bake at 375 degrees for 25 minutes.
Invert on a serving platter.
Pull apart to serve.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Preparation: 30 minutes.
Cooking Time: 20 minutes.

title: fudge nut pie
directions: Micro butter and chips in a 2-quart glass bowl for 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Mix in pecans, coconut and sugar.
Stir in eggs. Pour filling into pastry shell.
Micro on Medium (50) for 4 minutes, then on Medium-high (80) for 4 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn at 2 minute intervals (if using any microwave other than a carousel).
Stir once after 4 minutes and again at the end.

title: nut roll *
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.
Mix all other ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well. Form into log roll, using the 1/2 cup crumbs to sprinkle over roll.
Refrigerate.

title: cranberry pineapple tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Makes about 5 quarts. Good served iced or hot.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well, form into ball or log and roll in chili powder.

title: stuffed hot dogs
directions: Cook potatoes and mash.
Add onions and mustard to taste.
Mix together.
Cook hot dogs; when cool, slit in half without cutting all the way through.
Spread apart and put the potatoes in the slits.
Top with cheese.
Put in oven at about 400° until cheese is brown.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Salt and pepper the fryer.
Cover and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: white trash
directions: Combine all ingredients except almond bark in large plastic bowl.
Melt almond bark in microwave.
Pour over remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spread out to a single thin layer on wax paper until bark rehardens.
Break into pieces.
Enjoy!

title: key lime cheesecake pie
directions: In small saucepan, soften gelatin in lime juice for 5 minutes. Blend in sugar and eggs.
Over medium heat, bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Boil gently 3 minutes, stirring constantly. In small bowl, combine cream cheese and butter; beat well.
Pour in hot lime juice mixture.
Beat until smooth and well blended. Refrigerate until cool, about 45 minutes, stirring occasionally. In medium bowl, beat whipping cream until stiff peaks form.
Fold in cool lime juice mixture and grated lime peel.
Spoon into pie crust.
Refrigerate until firm, about 2 hours.
Garnish with whipped cream and lime slices as desired.
Store in refrigerator.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Sift together 3 1/2 cups flour and salt. Combine orange slices, dates, walnuts and coconut with 1/2 cup flour.
Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg. Combine soda and buttermilk. Mix with flour mixture. Beat well. Fold in candy and nuts; mix well.
Turn into 10-inch tube pan, greased well and floured. Bake at 250° for 2 hours and 25 minutes.

title: texas pecan pralines
directions: Combine first five ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, beating until creamy.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper; cool.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: harvest cinnamon beans
directions: In 2-quart casserole, combine fresh or thawed green beans, water, onion, bouillon granules and cinnamon.
Microcook, uncovered, on High, until beans are crisp-tender (15 to 20 minutes for fresh or 10 to 12 minutes for thawed), stirring 2 or 3 times during cooking.
Drain bean mixture, reserving 1 teaspoon of liquid.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream crisco and sugars, then mix in the eggs, canned milk and vanilla, then alternate by adding flour, soda, and salt until completely mixed. Stir in walnuts and chocolate chips. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour or overnight. Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet, bake at 350 degrees for 10-12 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Blend together.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to egg mixture, plus vanilla, zucchini, nuts and coconut.
Grease and flour 3 (3 x 7-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt, cut shortening into flour until resembles coarse cornmeal. Beat egg with wire whip and combine with vinegar and water. Combine with flour tossing lightly with fork. Makes 2 - 2 crust pies. Bake at 475° to 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add sugar, shortening, egg and vanilla.
Mix until smooth. Add oatmeal and nuts. Shape dough into rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill.
Slice 1/2-inch thick.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Thaw spinach souffle.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Place in greased baking dish (9 x 13-inch or 10 x 17-inch).
Bake at 400° until knife inserted in center comes out clean (25 to 30 minutes).

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with snack crackers, Melba toast rounds, etc.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Pour half of the batter in skillet. Top with half of the cheese.
Spoon rest of batter on top as not to disturb cheese. Top with remaining cheese. Bake 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt and spice; beat well. Blend in pumpkin. Add cream and beat well. Pour into pie shell. Bake in oven preheated to 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350° and continue baking for 45 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean. Cool. Garnish with whipped cream.

title: holy smoke
directions: Mix together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: curried beef
directions: Cook rice or noodles and set aside.
Place oil in electric skillet or a skillet to set over blaze with tight lid.
Heat oil, then brown onions in oil until slightly brown.
Remove from skillet and set aside.
Add a small amount of oil to skillet, if needed. Roll beef cubes in flour and lightly brown in skillet on all sides. Remove any excess oil.
Sprinkle curry powder, salt and pepper over meat.
Spread browned onions over meat.
Pour consomme over all. Cover with tight lid.
Bring to boil, then simmer about 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until gravy is slightly thickened and meat is tender. Place cooked rice or noodles in large bowl.
Pour meat mixture over.
Wait until meat is almost done before cooking rice.
Water or more consomme may be added, if needed.
There should be a generous amount of gravy to pour over rice.

title: sunday breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; crumble and drain.
Put bread cubes in bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Sprinkle sausage over bread cubes.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt, dry mustard and cheese.
Pour mixture over bread and sausage.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or when knife inserted comes out clean.

title: pastierra
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Place in bowl.
Heat milk with Cream of Wheat, add to noodles.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Could be used as hors d'oeuvre if cut in 1-inch squares.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill before serving.

title: summer salad
directions: Mix dressing and serve over spinach with fresh strawberries.

title: cookies and cream ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients except cookies in ice cream machine. Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Freeze as directed on ice cream machine.
Add cookies immediately after freezing in machine.

title: deep dish pizza
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add tomato sauce, onion and green pepper and cook until tender.
Stir in pizza sauce and herb spice mix; simmer 15 minutes.
Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pizza dough as directed on package.
With fingers greasy, press onto bottom and halfway up the sides of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with half Mozzarella cheese and meat sauce.
Repeat with remaining cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Pat crescent rolls out on pizza pan to form crust.
Layer as follows:
sausage, hash browns and cheese.
Beat eggs and milk together; drizzle over top.
Bake at 425° until potatoes are done and cheese is melted.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding in milk; blend 2 minutes. Stir in Cool Whip.
Line a 13 x 10-inch pan with graham crackers. Spoon in half of the pudding.
Place another layer of graham crackers.
Spoon in remaining pudding mix and top with another layer of graham crackers.
Frost (frosting can be heated to make it more spreadable).
Chill for 24 hours. Cut into squares.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: sally lunn
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Combine egg and milk.
Cream shortening and sugar together and add flour alternately with liquid mixture.
Place in greased loaf pan or muffin pans and bake in over at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf or 12 muffins.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in sweetened condensed milk, ReaLemon lemon juice, rind and food coloring.
Pour into prepared crust; bake 8 minutes.
Cool and chill.
Spread with Cool Whip.
Garnish as desired.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pineapple salad dressing(for fruit salad)
directions: Heat juice and add a little to eggs.
Then add remainder.
Mix sugar, flour and salt together and moisten to a smooth paste with juice mixture.
Add to juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until the consistency of custard.
Cool.
Fold into fruit.

title: meat and potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes, sliced, in bottom of casserole.
Mix other ingredients and spoon over potatoes.
Cook 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and lemon rind.
Toss lightly with a fork to mix. Set aside.

title: soldiers bread
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a bowl; cover and stand overnight.
Next morning, combine sugar, cinnamon and flour; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat together the eggs and vanilla.
Add the flour mixture to this and beat well.
Stir in the raisin mixture and nuts.
Pour batter into 3 well-greased 1-pound coffee cans and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Place the cans on a cooking rack and cool completely before removing the bottom of the can with a can opener.
Push the loaf out of the can.
Slice and serve with butter or cream cheese.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef and seasonings to taste.
Add herb sauce and italian cooking sauce, simmer while cooking twists.
Drain twists, add egg and margarine.
In large casserole dish, place 1 layer of twists, 1 layer hamburger sauce and sprinkle 2 cheese layers.
Add second layer twists, second layers of hamburger sauce and sprinkle with 2 cheeses.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli to package instructions.
Drain.
Arrange broccoli in greased casserole dish.
Spread chicken over broccoli. Add a mixture of mayonnaise, soup, lemon juice and curry.
Top with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serves 4.

title: babe ruth bars
directions: Mix brown and white sugars and Karo syrup together in pan on stove.
Remove immediately when mixture begins to boil.
Add peanut butter, Spanish peanuts and corn flakes.
Mix well.
Press down into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Melt Hershey bars and spread over top.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: flora raper's hot slaw
directions: Cut cabbage; salt.
Let stand.
Bring other ingredients to a boil.
Let cool.
Pour over cabbage that has been squeezed.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant until tender, drain well and mash.
Add all other ingredients except cheese, cracker crumbs and butter.
In greased medium-size casserole, layer the eggplant mixture, cheese and cracker crumbs, using about half of each in each layer.
Top with crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: speedy spinach lasagne
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl and add Ricotta cheese, spinach, salt and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Lightly grease bottom of a large baking dish.
Cover with a little sauce.
Layer noodles, half of the cheese and half the cheese-spinach mixture, half the Mozzarella cheese and half of the spaghetti sauce.
Repeat layers, ending with spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 of Parmesan cheese.
Cover dish with lightly greased sheet of aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 8.

title: sausage spaghetti
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Saute pepper and onion.
Add tomato paste, water and spices, mixing well.
Add sausage and cover skillet.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti. Serves 4.
Quick, easy and good.

title: oriental chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid. Melt butter in a large skillet. Add mushrooms and onion.
Cook over medium heat until onion is transparent. Remove from heat. Sprinkle evenly with flour, salt, pepper and curry powder.
Stir until blended. Add enough water to reserved mushroom liquid to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Add to mushroom mixture slowly, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Blend in evaporated milk. Cook, stirring over medium heat until thickened.
Add chicken, asparagus and noodles. Toss lightly to mix. Turn into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: quickie
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with a few crushed potato chips.
Bake one hour in a 350° oven.

title: honey carrots
directions: Combine all in saucepan. Cover, cook over low heat 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first six ingredients together.
Combine next 5 ingredients in a separate bowl.
Add wet ingredients to dry and mix well. Pour into 2 (5 x 8-inch) oiled loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 70 minutes.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla and pecans.
Cook slowly to soft ball stage on candy thermometer.
Add nuts about half way during cooking.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Beat candy until texture is thick and no longer glossy.
Drop onto greased waxed paper.

title: pink sparkle punch
directions: Combine sugar and water; heat over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a boil; boil for 8 minutes.
Let cool.
Add juices; chill.
Pour over ice in a punch bowl; add ginger ale. Garnish with pineapple and orange slices.
Yield:
50 servings.

title: walnut torte
directions: Beat egg yolks, add powdered sugar, mandarin peel, brandy and walnuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff, carefully fold into egg yolk mixture.
Bake in 8-inch springform at 350° for 1 hour. Frost with Butter Cream Icing.

title: strawberry ginger soup with berries
directions: Combine strawberry juice, ginger juice and banana in blender; blend until smooth.
Place mixture in attractive serving bowl or soup tureen.
Add berries and stir to combine.
Serves 4.

title: molded orange salad
directions: Also, can add celery and nuts, cut small.

title: mom tyers 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add beaten egg yolks. Sift flour and baking powder and salt together.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Fold in vanilla.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: salad monterey
directions: Combine lettuce, apples, oranges and celery; toss lightly. Sprinkle with peanuts, raisins or cereal.
Serve with dressing.

title: baked ham
directions: Pour jar of salsa and sliced apples over ham.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Wrap in tinfoil or roaster pan, covered.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add cream cheese and stir until melted.
Add remaining ingredients, including crabmeat.
Serve hot with snack crackers.

title: super bee meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Shape mixture in a loaf in shallow baking dish.
Press 2 thin green pepper rings and an onion ring atop meat loaf, if desired.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix cucumber with sour cream and dill weed.
Salt to taste. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serves 4.

title: doritos hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain fat. Mix soup, taco sauce and chillies with meat and onion. Into a casserole, put a layer of Doritos and add a layer of meat mixture, then a layer of cheese. Repeat. Use chillies according to taste. Bake at 350° until bubbly or about 25 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts together. Form into ball. Chill. Roll in pecans.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice.
In saucepan, combine juice, sugar and beaten eggs.
Cook until thickens (it doesn't get very thick).
Allow to cool.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Freeze in 9 x 12-inch dish or use individual muffin cups.
Serve frozen.

title: pork chalupas
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Combine beans, roast, chilies, cumin, salt, garlic and oregano in a large Dutch oven; cover with water. Cover and simmer 6 hours, stirring occasionally, adding water as needed.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate for 1/2 hour. Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Can be frozen and then baked.

title: apple spice oatmeal cake
directions: Mix water, oats and butter.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Add all other ingredients except apples.
Mix well.
Fold in apples and pour into a greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix 2 tablespoons each flour and sugar.
Add 1 teaspoon each cinnamon and melted butter.
Sprinkle over top of cake prior to baking.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour in crust.
Let
set overnight or all day.

title: gooey buns
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with margarine.
Put in frozen dough balls.
Sprinkle with nuts, brown sugar, cinnamon and dry pudding. Take margarine and slice into pieces over dough and mixture.

title: barbecued franks
directions: Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Melt butter in saucepan and cook onions until soft.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Split franks lengthwise.
Place in a greased shallow baking pan.
Pour sauce evenly over franks.
Baste frequently with sauce.

title: fruit dip
directions: In small saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch; mix well. Stir in pineapple juice.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat to medium and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat; stir in yogurt.
Let cool, then cover and refrigerate. When ready to serve, sprinkle with cinnamon and serve with fresh fruit.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, peanuts and salt in a 2-quart glass dish.
Stir well.
Microwave on High for 8 to 9 minutes; mixture will be light brown in color.
Add vanilla and butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Microwave on High for 1 to 3 minutes.
Stir in baking soda quickly.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Let cool at least one hour.
Break into small pieces.

title: pumpkin butter
directions: Put pumpkin, Sure-Jell and spice in large saucepan and mix well. Place over high heat and stir until mixture comes to a hard boil. Immediately add sugar and stir. Bring to a full rolling boil and boil hard 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; ladle into glasses and jars, cover with 1/8-inch hot paraffin at once. Makes about 7 (6 ounce) glasses or jars.

title: oven fried parmesan chicken
directions: Dry chicken.
Dip in butter.
Roll in mixture of remaining ingredients.
Press crumbs on chicken and place in a shallow, foil lined pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not turn chicken.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Wash chicken, remove excess fat, put on large pot and cover with water.
Add al ingredients except noodles, cook until chicken is done.
Remove chicken and vegetables, retaining liquid.
(You may wish to dice carrots and return to pot for color.) Reduce heat to warm.
When chicken cools, remove skin, fat and bones and shred chicken.

title: easy turkey or chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and place in the bottom of a 1-quart casserole dish.
Layer turkey or chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix together remaining ingredients except cheese and spread on top.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese bubbles.

title: tennefos family thanksgiving fruit cocktail
directions: Peel, section and de-membrane oranges and grapefruit.
Wash and separate grapes.
Cut cherries in half, reserving the juice.
Mix fruit in large bowl.
Cover with orange juice and add maraschino cherry juice.

title: cucumber salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar, dill and salt. Mix well. Add cucumbers and onions; toss. Cover and chill for at least 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the Crisco and the 2 sugars together; add eggs and mix well.
Add the flour, soda, salt and cinnamon that have been sifted together.
Add vanilla; stir in oats and nuts.
Drop by small teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: brownie trifle
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Spray bottom of 13x9x2 pan with nonstick cooking spray.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix together; form in balls.
Press down slightly with glass dipped in sugar, if preferred.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: corn for freezer
directions: Boil 10 minutes.
Cool with ice.
Pack for freezer in pint bags.

title: artichoke salad
directions: Cook rice as directed on box, except omit butter. Cook dry in skillet. Remove from heat and cool. Add onion and pepper to rice. Drain and add sliced artichokes to rice. Save liquid. Add curry powder and mayonnaise to artichoke liquid. Mix well. Add to rice. Chill overnight.

title: southern style cooked dried beans or peas
directions: Sort and wash beans or peas; cover with water and let soak 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
Drain beans or peas and put in large heavy saucepan; cover with water.
Add salt and pork.
Boil gently on medium to low heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add chopped onion the last 15 or 20 minutes of cooking.
At this time, test beans to see how tender they are.
The time of cooking depends on the kind of dried beans you use.

title: brown kraut casserole
directions: Fry bacon and onion until bacon is crisp and onion browned. Crumble bacon and drain well.
Put kraut in casserole dish.
Add sugar to taste of individual. Add onion and bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no-bake strawberry bottom cheesecake
directions: Slice berries and place on paper towels to drain.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well. Spread thin layer of glaze over bottom of crust.
Place strawberry slices on glaze and cover with another layer of glaze.
Gently spoon mixture over glazed berries in crust.
Cover with inverted dome and chill until set at least 4 hours.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil; set aside.
Mix flour, spices and soda; add to egg mixture.
Add baby applesauce, apricots and carrots, then mix in nuts.
