Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix egg yolks with milk.
Add lemon juice to mixture.
Pour 1/2 mixture into each pie crust.
Bake in 325° preheated oven until you can smell the pie.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown and season pork chops.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Put sliced onion over chops.
Add cooked macaroni.
Pour tomato soup over all and add 1 can water.
Break cheese into pieces and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Put milk in 3-quart boiler.
Add marshmallows, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Crush crackers and cut up fruits and nuts.
Add milk mixture to this and coat good.
Put in loaf pans or tube pan and let set for two or three days.

title: jello mousse
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed on box.
Before it jells, mix in the Cool Whip and blend well.
Chill until it sets.

title: christmas candy
directions: Use a toothpick to dip candy into chocolate mixture.

title: carmen's fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Mix flour, sugar, milk and baking powder. Pour over melted butter.
Put about a quart of fruit on top. Bake until golden brown at 350°.

title: congealed buttermilk salad
directions: Heat gelatin and pineapple just until gelatin is dissolved, but do not boil.
Allow to cool.
Prepare whipped topping according to directions on box and add buttermilk, gelatin mixture and nuts.
Mix until well blended.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: cheesy spinach lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef until brown, stirring to crumble meat.
Add onion, mushrooms, oregano, basil, 1/2 salt and pepper.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Stir in V-8 juice.
Combine milk and flour. Mix well and stir into skillet mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly until thick and bubbly.
Combine cottage cheese and 1 egg.
Mix well and set aside.
Drain spinach well.
Combine spinach and 1 egg and the remaining salt and pepper.
Mix well and spread evenly in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer 1/2 of noodles, 1/2 of cottage cheese, 1/2 of cheese slices and 1/2 of meat mixture over spinach; repeat layer.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle lightly with parsley.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Make pastry and line pie pan.
Place prepared rhubarb on crust.
Mix flour with sugar and sprinkle over rhubarb.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust and bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 375°.
Cook 30 minutes.

title: greg's nachos
directions: On large plate, layer nachos and cheese.
Heat in microwave for 1 minute and 20 seconds.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw the spinach, chop it finer and drain.
Add all the other ingredients and mix.
Place, covered, in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours before serving.
This may be served with crackers or fresh, raw vegetables

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix chili, cumin, salt, pepper, tomatoes in bowl. Mix sour cream, scallions, chiles in second bowl. Spread 1/2 c. tomato mixture in 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish. Arrange 2 tortillas to cover bottom; use pieces from another tortilla to fit corners if needed. Top with half the sour cream mixture, half the chicken, half the corn, 1 c. tomato mixture, one third of the cheese. Repeat layering, ending with tortillas, tomatoes. Sprinkle remaining cheese around edge. Bake in 350° oven 35 minutes, until bubbly. Let stand 15 minutes. Garnish with olives and scallions.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cut chicken breast into pieces.
Spray pan with Pam.
Add chicken.
Cook until chicken is white on both sides.
Season with salt, pepper, garlic powder and Italian seasoning to taste.
Pour in salsa.
Cover and simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Cook Spanish rice according to package.
Pour chicken over rice.

title: peanut butter and jelly
directions: Take dough.
Make it in a circle and put tomato sauce on it. Also, put pepperoni, cheese and hamburger.
Put it in the oven and after it is done, eat it.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Cook the potatoes in chicken broth until soft, about 20 minutes.
Mix gravy mix with water and add to potatoes, stirring constantly.
Cook until desired consistency.
You can add a little shredded cheese on top when you serve it and it is YUMMY.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Add salt.
Mix ketchup, vinegar, brown sugar and mustard.
Drain liquid off the beans and add to the mixture.
Then add ground beef and onion. Mix all together and put into baking dish.
Preheat oven to 325° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: crawfish pie
directions: Saute crawfish tails in margarine for about 5 minutes.
Remove tails and add onion, garlic and bell pepper.
Saute for about 10 minutes.
Season crawfish and add to mixture along with the soup. Cook at least 20 minutes.
If too thick, add a little water. Place mixture in pie shell and cover with top.
Bake at 300° until brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: apricot-glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Place apricots in saucepan and cover with apricot nectar and water.
Let stand 1 hour.
Cook over medium heat and simmer, uncovered, until apricots are tender, about 40 minutes.
Cool and drain, reserving the liquid.
Scrub sweet potatoes.

Place on baking sheet and bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes until tender. Cool, peel and cut into lengthwise slices about 1/4-inch thick. Arrange a layer of potatoes in a lightly greased 2-quart (7 x 11-inches) baking dish.
Layer apricots; repeat alternating layers of potatoes and apricots.
Sprinkle top with brown sugar.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Microwave on High approximately 2 minutes, stirring in between.
Remove from microwave and stir well; add 1 cup chopped nuts.
Pour in baking dish and refrigerate to harden.

title: grandpa's high hat
directions: Combine sugar, butter, cream of tartar, molasses, baking soda, cinnamon, allspice, cloves, raisins and currants.
Add milk and enough bread crumbs to absorb milk while mixing.
Slowly add flour until mix is consistency of gingerbread.
Put in buttered 3-pound Crisco or coffee can with lid.
Steam 3 hours in water at 3/4 level of can (add water as needed).
Mix butter and confectioners sugar to make hard sauce.
Brandy or whiskey is optional.
Form into 1-inch balls which can be rolled in colored sugar.
Serve.

title: pudding pie
directions: Mix chocolate pudding in bowl as directed on package.
Mix vanilla pudding in bowl as directed on package.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar, vanilla, water and egg until light and fluffy.
Mix together flour, soda and salt.
Blend into butter mixture.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: jenny chambers' rolls
directions: Let rise 3 times once in pan.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer in order given.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar.
Spread over mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover.
Put in refrigerator 12 to 24 hours.
Toss before serving.

title: scones
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and add enough buttermilk or sour cream or plain yogurt to make a soft dough.
Pat out on floured board to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into wedges and brown on a flour griddle over medium heat.
Turn to brown other side.

title: cowboy's beans
directions: Add all ingredients together in a crock-pot and cook all day long.

title: sally lunn muffins
directions: In mixer bowl, cream butter and sugar until thoroughly blended.
Add eggs and mix well. Combine baking powder and flour. Add to the creamed mixture alternately with the milk, starting and ending with the flour.
Spoon into greased muffin tins filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes or until tests done. Remove from tins and place on rack.
Best served right away. Yields 12 muffins.

title: sauteed doves
directions: Saute doves in butter 5 minutes until browned.
Add wine, onion, celery, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer over low heat 20 minutes.
Add tarragon and simmer uncovered 15 minutes or until tender.

title: georgeanna's hamburger special
directions: To Serve:
Place 1/4 of each thing on each plate in this order:
Rice, hamburger mix, lettuce and tomatoes, then Fritos. Sprinkle with cheese.
A light dessert and beverage will make a meal.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Spread pineapple
evenly
into	a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pans. Spread cherry
pie filling on top of pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix on top
of
pie
filling.
Pour
melted margarine on top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until done.

title: fluffy butter icing
directions: Cook milk and flour until it forms ball.
Cool.
Take sugar, oleo and butter.
Beat until creamy.
Add dough ball.
Beat until nice and creamy.
Will ice a 2-layer cake.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix.
Dip fresh strawberries. Wonderful!
Tastes like pie.

title: easy pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in hot water, then add oil and honey; mix well. Add flour and salt.
Knead dough on a floured surface.
Place in an oiled bowl and cover; let rise.
Shape dough and bake with favorite toppings.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cook the next day, adding enough water to cover.
Add a little salt.
Cook until tender.
Add tomatoes. Cook 15 to 30 minutes.
Lightly fry onions in butter; add to pot. Let pot simmer for an hour or more until sauce thickens.
Add tamari or soy sauce, Miso, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder and cumin powder in equal quantities (2 or 3 teaspoons each), oregano leaves, basil, bay leaves and thyme.
Lightly fry sliced mushrooms and green peppers.
Add to pot and simmer at least 1/2 hour. Cooked rice may be added now, if desired.
Soup gets better second and third day.
Tamari and Miso sauce may be obtained at health food stores or Oriental grocers.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thinly slice peeled apples and coat with 5 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Coat well. Mix all other ingredients together in separate bowl.
Mix well. Grease and flour tube pan.
Alternate layers of batter and apples. Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: rice pudding
directions: In double boiler, add water, rice and salt.
Let cook until rice absorbs water (2 hours).
After 2 hours, add in separate bowl the sugar, eggs and vanilla. Mix.
Add this mixture to rice and stir for 5 minutes.

title: banana orange shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend on high for 30 to 45 seconds or until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Serves 1.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix first five ingredients in a large bowl.
Place in a 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pan.
In a sauce pan over medium high heat, mix remaining ingredients and cook until thick.
Reserve 3/4 cup for table; pour remaining on top of ham loaf and bake in a preheated 350 degree oven for 2 1/2 hours, basting with reserved sauce occasionally. Slice ham loaf.
Re-warm reserved sauce and pour over ham loaf slices.
Serve immediately.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.
If you would like a chocolate pound cake, add 4 tbsp. cocoa.

title: three day coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed, bake and cool.
Split layers.
Mix coconut, sugar and sour cream for filling to go between layers. Frost entire cake with La Creme Cool Whip and cover with coconut. Cover loosely.
Place in refrigerator and leave for 3 days before serving.

title: chocolate christmas cake
directions: Follow directions on box and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
After baking, poke holes in cake surface and pour 1 can of Eagle Brand milk over the cake.
Immediately pour caramel ice cream topping over that and let cake cool completely.
Ice with Cool Whip and sprinkle with ground up Heath bars.
Refrigerate.

title: grandma sauder's knepply soup
directions: Boil potatoes in small amount of water and salt.
When almost tender, add ham broth.
When boiling, add the Knepply.

title: busy day rice casserole
directions: Combine rice, bouillon, soup and butter in 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 1 hour or until moisture is absorbed.
Yields 6 servings.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Saute onions in butter in skillet until tender.
Spread in pie shell.
Beat eggs with evaporated milk, salt and pepper in bowl. Pour over onions.
Bake at 425° for 18 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: jezebel appetizer
directions: Combine ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour desired amount over cream cheese.
Serve with crackers.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: glazed chicken
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Pour over chicken in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Can also be used when broiling or grilling.
Baste meat frequently during last 30 minutes of cooking.
Also good on spareribs, chops or frankfurters.

title: oatmeal gingersnaps
directions: Stir together first 6 ingredients and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Blend in shortening, molasses and egg.
Beat well with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Let stand 1 minute.
Cool on rack.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients. Stir into creamed mixture.
Use spoon to stir in apples and nuts. Pour into greased 9 x 13 in. pan.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: taffy candy
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients to hard crack stage.
Add vanilla and butter. Pour into buttered platter until cool enough to handle. Pull until light.
Cut into pieces with kitchen shears.
Dip each piece in powdered sugar.

title: lime cucumber pickles
directions: Stir lime and water until lime is dissolved.
Pour over cucumbers.
Soak for 24 hours.
Drain and wash several times until clear, then cover with ice water for 3 hours.
Drain.
Make syrup.

title: crunchy squash casserole
directions: Cook the squash until crisp and tender, about 10 minutes in boiling water.
Drain the squash and combine with the rest of the ingredients.
Place in a buttered casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: veggie-ghetti
directions: Place the cooked vegetable spaghetti squash in a lightly oiled pie plate.
Mix the tomatoes, herbs and oil
and spoon onto the squash.
Top with cheese and broil until cheese is melted.

title: cranberry-orange loaf
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt, sugar and orange rind; mix thoroughly.
Stir in cranberries.
Combine egg, melted butter and orange juice.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until blended.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken; save broth.
Pull chicken off bone.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan and pour rice in pan.
Pour 2 to 3 cups chicken broth over rice.
Place boned chicken in dish.
Mix soups and sour cream together and pour over chicken.
Top with crushed buttered crackers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spiced shrimp
directions: Boil water, caraway seed, black pepper, pickling spice, cayenne, bay leaf, mustard, 4 teaspoons salt and celery leaves for 20 minutes before putting in shrimp. Shrimp must be put in the boiling spice water and cook 10 minutes after water starts to boil again.

title: my favorite cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Cream together sugar and butter. Add egg
yolk, vanilla, salt, almond extract and sifted flour. Grease shallow
x
11-inch
pan and press the cookie dough flat. Beat
egg
white
with
sugar
until frothy.
Spread on batter. Pat
nuts
into
dough.
Bake
1 1/2 hours; cut while warm. Remove from pan.
Makes about 36.

title: spiced cranberry catsup
directions: Put berries in saucepan with 3/4 cup water.
Cover, cook 10 minutes or until berries are soft.
Force through a sieve.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 12 minutes until thickened.
Put into jar and cool.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields 2 cups.

title: four bean salad
directions: Drain and rinse beans.
Add thin onion slices and slivered or sliced green pepper.
Bring to boil the sugar, cornstarch, oil and vinegar.
Cool until just warm.
Pour over beans and marinate overnight or several hours.
Add salt to taste.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, vanilla and water.
Add flour, salt and grated nuts.
Chill about 1 hour in refrigerator.
Form into small rolls about the size of a finger.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: honey-mustard glazed chicken
directions: In small bowl, combine mustard, honey, lemon juice and garlic. Grill or broil chicken 45 minutes or until done, turning occasionally and brushing with mustard mixture.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ham and potatoes casserole
directions: Cube potatoes and put in buttered casserole dish.
Put ham cubes over potatoes and pour cheese sauce over all. Grate more cheese on top and place in oven until slightly brown.

title: skillet biscuits
directions: Stir mix and milk together.
Spoon onto hot lightly greased skillet.
Cook for about 10 minutes, turning once and pressing down lightly.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix the sugar, cocoa, syrup and milk.
Boil until it forms a soft ball in cool water, 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour into buttered plate. Cool, then cut into squares.

title: taco dip
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread bean dip.
In small bowl, mix sour cream, mayo and taco mix.
Spread mixture over bean dip.
Add onions, olives and tomatoes.
Over entire top, sprinkle Cheddar cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: nell's chicken casserole
directions: Combine sour cream and undiluted soup.
Mix with chicken and water chestnuts.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle crackers on top.
Drizzle butter on top.
Sprinkle with paprika and/or parsley. Bake in conventional oven at approximately 350° or microwave until bubbling along sides of container, approximately 2 to 3 inches in toward center.

title: cheese n' everything
directions: Reach under the hen and get the eggs.
Get a bowl and a fork and a chair.
Crack the egg and take out the pieces of shell. (Don't let Autumn fall off the chair if she's helping.)
Scramble the egg and put in bits of cheese.
Zap it in the microwave until it's fluffy.
Stir the edges into the middle when it's half done. Put it in the freezer to cool off a little.

title: baked pheasant(skinned)
directions: Salt the pheasant lightly.
Stuff the bird with your favorite dressing.
Place breast-up in medium-size roaster.
Cover breast and legs with a mixture of melted butter or margarine and pepper to your taste.
The amount of flour and butter will vary with the size and number of birds.
I start with 1 cube of butter to 2 birds, taking care not to make the mixture too dry.
Add 2 cups water and bake until tender at 300°.
Add a small amount of water occasionally as needed.
When finished, the pheasant will be very moist and there will be delicious gravy in the pan.

title: cactus country meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, mix tomato bits, corn meal, garlic and water. Set aside 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix to blend thoroughly.
In shallow baking pan, form loaf about 12 x 4-inches. Sprinkle with about 1 tablespoon corn meal.
Bake in 375° oven 50 minutes to 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: jewish braids
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
When it bubbles, add salt, sugar and butter.
Blend in 3 cups flour and add the eggs.
Beat thoroughly. Now, add the rest of the flour and mix it in with your hands. Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in a buttered bowl and let rise until doubled.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix in a large mixing bowl (2-quart).
First add soda to buttermilk.
Mix well with beater.
Add eggs and mix.
Add 1 cup flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add other cup of flour; mix well.
Pour on hot griddle approximately 1/4 cup batter, or more if you want larger pancakes.
Makes light and fluffy pancakes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pudding parfaits
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat milk and pudding until thickened. Refrigerate for 10 minutes. Spoon half of the mixture into 4 chilled glasses. Top each with 3 tablespoons cherry pie filling and 2 tablespoons granola. Repeat layers. Garnish with whipped topping. Delightful.

title: blueberry snack cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour and sugar, cut in butter until crumbly and set aside 3/4 c. for topping.

title: chicken cutlets
directions: Four to 24 hours before cooking, marinate chicken.
Place the garlic, ginger, onion, green chili, parsley, lemon juice, salt and pepper in a blender.
Add a tablespoon of water and blend to a smooth paste.
Prick chicken all over with a fork.
Pour the marinade paste over chicken and rub into the pieces.
Cover and refrigerate 4 to 24 hours.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a jar.
Shake well.
Before using, keep refrigerated.

title: hamburger-barley soup
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain well.
Combine all ingredients except peas.
Bring to a boil and simmer for a couple of hours, checking vegetables for tenderness.
Add the peas during the last half hour of cooking time.
Also, check the flavor of the soup and add more seasonings, to taste, if necessary.
Tastes best if made a day ahead.

title: confetti candy
directions: Heat milk slowly in heavy saucepan, stirring to avoid sticking. Add all other ingredients and stir well.
Pour into Pyrex dish that has been sprayed with Pam and covered with wax paper.
Let cool and then cut.
Do not let set overnight before cutting.

title: oatmeal apple cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon, set aside. Cream together oleo and brown sugar and beat until fluffy.
Beat eggs into oleo and sugar, beat until fluffy. Add flour mixture and blend until smooth.
Add oats, raisins, apples and nuts, and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on a non stick or
lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: honey baked lentils
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil in saucepan. Cover tightly and reduce heat. Simmer 30 minutes. Do not drain. Discard bay leaf.
Combine the next 6 ingredients separately, then mix with lentils in oven-safe casserole dish. Pour honey over all.
Cover and bake 1 hour.

title: reuben chicken
directions: Layer in pan in order given.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: onion honey butter
directions: Peel and thinly slice onion, separating into rings.
Should measure 3 to 4 cups rings.
In skillet, cook onion rings in butter or margarine, until soft, but not browned.
Add sugar and honey. Cook slowly until onions are glazed and liquid is well cooked down.
Serve warm with meat of any type.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cousin cookies
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar, sugar, eggs and peanut butter together.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking soda, salt, oats, nuts and chocolate chips to wet mixture.
Drop by teaspoonful on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Cut bananas, strawberries and grapes into pieces.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl and mix.

title: spice cookies
directions: Cream
shortening and butter;
add sugar and eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir
in
milk and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir into creamed mixture until well blended.
Wrap dough in foil and refrigerate until ready to bake.
Start oven at hot 425°.
Roll dough about 1/8-inch thick.
Makes about 8 dozen cookies.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into thin strips, dust with flour, salt and pepper and brown.

Add onions, bell pepper, mushroom soup and beef broth. Cover and cook on low heat for 1 1/2 hours until meat is tender. When ready to serve, gradually stir in sour cream and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli according to directions and drain. Saute onion
in
butter.
Mix Cheez Whiz and soup.
Pour over rice and broccoli.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli and cauliflower bake
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower in boiling salt water until stems are almost tender, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain.
Place in ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Heat oven to 400°.
Beat soup and milk with hand beater until smooth; pour over vegetables. Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix baking mix and margarine until crumbly. Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake until crumbs are light brown, about 20 minutes.

title: picadillo
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Saute onion, olives and garlic.
Mix in ground beef.
Drain tomatoes but save the tomato juice.
Add tomatoes to beef.
Add spices.
Add some of the reserved tomato juice, if needed, and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve with rice and black beans.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut beef into strips.
Heat oil in large skillet; add beef. Cook, turning frequently, until brown, about 5 minutes.
Stir in water, onion, garlic salt and ginger.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 12 to 15 minutes for round steak, 5 to 8 minutes for sirloin.
Add green pepper during last 5 minutes of simmering.
While beef is simmering, cook rice as directioned on package.

title: baby back ribs
directions: Boil ribs in Dutch oven until fork-tender with a small amount of salt.
When tender, take from pan.
Put on cookie sheet.
Put salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce on ribs.
Bake in oven at 350° until brown, turning once.
Serve with barbecue sauce on the side.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna until tender.
Cook frozen vegetables according to package; drain water.
Add mixture to mushroom soup.
Add water and milk.
Stir in tuna and drained can of mushrooms.
In lasagna pan, layer noodles, mushroom soup mixture and layer of cheese until all ingredients are used up.
Top with 4 slices of cheese. Cover; bake at 325° for a half hour.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Stir in brown sugar.
Cool.
Stir in eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
In mixing bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Spread in well-greased and floured baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: super potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in skins.
Cool several hours.
Remove skins and grate.
Cook butter, cream and salt until butter melts.
Place grated potatoes and most of cheese cubes in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour sauce over potatoes and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°. Last 15 minutes, sprinkle a little of cheese over top.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine tomatoes, peppers, onions, pickles and bacon.
Drain off excess juice and combine with mayonnaise.
Crumble cornbread and combine with vegetable mixture.
Toss gently.
Spread mayonnaise over top.
Cover and chill overnight.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: baked onions with liver
directions: Place liver in boiling water for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove skin and chop in food chopper or food processor.
Chop bacon in small chunks and fry until crisp. Mix liver, bacon, celery and seasonings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, spices and butter.
Mix well, then add nuts. Soak raisins in water, while mixing other ingredients, then dry and add flour.
Add to other ingredients.
Add applesauce with soda, heat and stir well, then add to other ingredients.
Pour in a greased tube pan (waxed paper in bottom of pan).
Cook 1 hour at 325° or until toothpick comes out clean.
(Don't overcook.)

title: 4 day pickles
directions: 1st Day (Morning):
Place cucumbers in large container and cover with boiling water.

title: chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken and onion together until chicken is done.
Remove chicken and debone.
Cut in bite size pieces.
Return to stock. Add all other ingredients.
Cook until done.
Before removing from heat, add 1 can cream-style corn.
Stir.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; add egg, vanilla and sour cream and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Chill dough well before rolling out.
Bake at 400° for approximately 7 minutes.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Press 1 can of crescent roll dough into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix all other ingredients and spread onto dough.
Press other can of dough onto waxed paper.
(Make sure all seams are sealed.) Turn onto mixture and remove paper.
Brush top with egg white and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°, until golden. Cut in squares.

title: cheesecake
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 cups water; let sit until begins to thicken.
Cream together the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add thickened jello.
In separate bowl, mix cold condensed milk and lemon juice; add to jello and cheese mixture.

title: batter bread
directions: Gradually blend water in corn meal and cook 3 to 5 minutes until very thick.
Remove from stove, then add other ingredients in order (butter, salt, milk and eggs last).
Cook 25 to 30 minutes at 350° until brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Place bananas, eggs, butter, buttermilk or sour cream, lemon juice and sugar into a blender container or work bowl of food processor fitted with steel blade.
Whirl until smooth.
Mix together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Pour banana mixture over flour mixture and stir just until flour is moistened.
Stir in the nuts.
Turn into greased 9 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch bread loaf or into a 3 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch nut bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until bread tests done when a skewer is inserted in the center.
Allow to cool 5 minutes in pan, then turn out onto wire racks.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cook peppers, celery and onions in oil until almost tender. Set aside.
Run steak through tenderizer and cut in thin strips (cuts easier if partly frozen).
Brown strips where vegetables were browned.
Add water, flour, salt, soy sauce, sugar and tomatoes.
Simmer at least one hour.
Add vegetable combination and simmer at least another 30 minutes or until steak is very tender.
Serve over rice with 1/4 teaspoon ground ginger added to each cup of rice.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix sweetened condensed milk, powdered sugar, peanut butter and melted butter together; roll into small balls. In double boiler, melt chocolate bits and paraffin wax; keep double boiler on stove on low. Drop balls into chocolate mixture and then place on waxed paper.

title: peanut butter banana muffins
directions: Combine oatmeal, flour, margarine and brown sugar.
Sprinkle evenly over batter in cups.
Bake 16 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.

title: coconut sheet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: walnut apple cake
directions: Flour and grease Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
In large mixing bowl, combine first 8 ingredients.
Add vanilla, oil and eggs; mix well.
Add soaked apples, spooning in to include some of the liquid for moistness.
Fold in the nuts.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or to clean toothpick.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes. Turn out on large plate and glaze while still warm.
Garnish with halves.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Blend flour and salt into small bowl. In a large bowl, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs and extracts well, then stir in flour and salt. Divide dough in half and color one half with 8 drops of red food coloring.
Refrigerate, wrapped in plastic, for 2 hours.
Working with 1 teaspoon of dough at a time, form 5-inch long, pencil-thin cylinders of each color.
Twist 1 of each cylinder together to look like a candy cane.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: beef and broccoli
directions: Blend sherry and soy sauce, 4 tsp. oil, sugar and five spice powder.
Combine with meat.
Marinate in the refrigerator for 1-2 hours.
In wok, saute ginger and garlic in remaining 1/2 c. oil, tilting wok to coat with oil.
Stir fry broccoli 3 minutes, remove from pan.
Stir fry beef 2 minutes just until brown.
Return broccoli to pan.
Stir in cornstarch and stock.
Cook 1 minute longer until thick.
Serve over rice.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl; mix well and refrigerate. Dip should be made the day before serving to allow flavors to blend well.

title: easy chicken loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pack in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Serve with hot gravy.
Freezes well.
Great for leftover chicken pieces or turkey.

title: mom's pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl; mix well.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake for 75 minutes in a preheated 350° oven, or until it tests done.
Let cool and serve.
Also good with sweet potatoes (cooked).

title: old fashion devil's food cake
directions: Cream well shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat very well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix well and add boiling water at once into cake mixture.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° in 3 well-greased and floured pans for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and melted butter; add eggs one at a time. Add pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: texas chocolate sheet cake
directions: In large bowl, sift sugar, flour, soda and salt; set aside. Melt the margarine, water and cocoa in saucepan and bring to rolling boil; set aside a few minutes.
In small bowl, beat eggs lightly; add buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat into bowl of flour, sugar mixture; beat in hot cocoa mixture.
Turn into floured and greased large cookie sheet with sides (17 x 12-inch pan).
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Frost while warm.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Combine sugar and cornstarch in medium bowl.
Add eggs and mix. Add corn and milk; mix well.
Turn into baking dish.
Dot with butter (about 1/2 stick).
Bake until center is almost firm, about 1 hour.

title: fudge-nut cake
directions: Make batter for devil's food cake as directed, except fold in 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake as directed.
Cool.
Frost with Chocolate Butter Icing.

title: easy chicken and pasta
directions: Saute cut up pieces of chicken in olive oil with garlic.
Add chopped sun-dried tomatoes and mushrooms.
Saute until chicken is tender.
Add red wine vinegar, oregano and basil.
Pour in a half cup of chicken broth and cook until broth is heated.
Pour over angel hair pasta.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Combine eggs and sugar in mixing bowl.
Beat with mixer until thoroughly blended.
Add milk and butter, mixing well.
Combine 3 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to liquid ingredients, stirring just until all are moistened.
Combine blueberries and 2 tablespoons flour.
Stir well, folding berries into batter. Pour into greased and floured pans and bake at 350°.

title: creamy corn
directions: In a saucepan, combine cream cheese, milk, butter and onion salt.
Stir over low heat until the mixture melts.
Add corn. Heat through and serve.

title: cheesy salmon loaf
directions: Combine and bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ice cream sandwich dessert
directions: Cut one sandwich in half.
Place one whole and one half sandwich along short side of 13 x 9 x 2 pan.
Arrange 8 sandwiches in opposite direction in the pan.
Spread with 1/2 Cool Whip. Spoon fudge topping onto whipped topping.
Sprinkle with crushed Heath.
Add another layer of sandwich, Cool Whip and Heath (pan will be full).
Cover and freeze for up to 2 months.
Remove from freezer 20 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: mrs. himrod's chili sauce
directions: Put ingredients in a large kettle; bring to a boil for at least 20 minutes.
Cook slowly to desired consistency.
Can and seal while hot.

title: elvis presley cake
directions: Make cake as directed; use butter instead of oil. Heat pineapple and 1 or 2 Tbsp. sugar. Poke holes in cake and pour pine apples over cake. Mix powder sugar and cream cheese. Spread over cooled cake.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix cornbread, soup and all other ingredients, except squash and cheese, together. Add cheese and squash last. Pour into Pyrex. Bake at 400° about 30 minutes, until brown.

title: carly's mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased 9 x 13 casserole dish. Bake at 350 F till golden brown.
Top with salsa, if desired.

title: uncooked relish
directions: Grind vegetables with coarse blade.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain off all juice.
Cover with sugar, celery seed, apple cider vinegar and prepared mustard.
Mix all together. Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: spicy percolator punch
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in percolator.
Place spices in basket.
Perk as for coffee.

title: potato candy
directions: Prepare potato as if making mashed potatoes.
Put in 2-quart mixing bowl.
Add vanilla; gradually mix in confectioners sugar until it has formed into soft dough.
Sprinkle counter with extra confectioners sugar, roll out dough and spread a light coating of peanut butter all over.
Roll like a jelly roll.
Slice about 1/2 inch thick like pin wheels.
Put in cookie tin and place in refrigerator.
Keeps forever. For the holidays vary the colors with food coloring.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Scald milk; add sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add enough flour to make a thick batter.
Mix well.
Add yeast and eggs and beat well.
Add more flour to make a soft dough.
Place dough in greased bowl; brush top with soft lard or shortening.
Cover tightly.
Refrigerate until doubled or until needed.
To use, punch down, cut off amount needed and form into shape.
Let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Bake at 400° about 10 to 15 minutes. Serve.
Can be kept 1 week, covered, in refrigerator.

title: chili cheese log
directions: Let cheeses stand at room temperature to soften; combine cheeses, lemon juice, garlic powder and a dash of red pepper. Beat with electric or rotary beater until light and fluffy.
Stir in finely chopped pecans.
Shape in a roll about 1 1/2-inches across.
Sprinkle roll with mixture of chili powder and paprika. Chill several hours.
Before serving, let stand at room temperature about 10 minutes.
Slice and serve with crackers. Servings:
Serving Size:
1 slice.

title: cinnamon toast
directions: Take bread, spread butter on bread, sprinkle cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 100° until brown.

title: cookie crust pie shell
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine flour, sugar and lemon peel in medium bowl.
Cut in margarine with pastry blender.
Stir in egg yolk and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.

title: summertime fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate.
Serve with melon, pineapple, apples, grapes, or any fruit of your choice.

title: cottage cheese cookies
directions: Soften Butter and blend with Cottage Cheese until creamy and fluffy.
Add Vanilla and gradually add Sugar; beating until well blended.
Add Eggs.
Mix well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 for 10 - 12 minutes or until delicately brown.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix zucchini, onion, peppers and salt.
Cover with water and let stand overnight.
Drain.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Mix all ingredients, except candy Kisses, in a large bowl until a large ball is formed.
Shape into small balls.
Roll ball in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Press Kisses on cookies while warm.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: pea and cheese salad
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients. In a small bowl, combine the mayo, relish and seasonings. Stir into pea mixture. Cover and refrigerate until serving. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: west virginia pie crust
directions: Into 1 cup measuring cup, add egg, vinegar and enough water to make 1 cup liquid.
In a large bowl, mix flour and margarine with a pastry blender.
Mix liquids and flour all at once.
Makes 3 to 4 crusts.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes; 375° until pie is done (45 minutes).

title: green pepper steak
directions: Heat oil in wok.
Cut steak while frozen into thin strips; cook in wok 2 to 3 minutes.
Cut pepper and onions into strips; cook with meat 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour gravy mix and 2 cups water into wok.
Simmer until thick.
Serve over rice.
